column3: 2/20, 100 Feet Ring Road, BTM 1st Stage, BTM, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  Sorry to say but this place served completely raw chicken with biryani. When I asked for refund they ignored. There are many better option then wasting your money in raw chicken.'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Not good at all and Not recommended. We ordered to test for regular orders. But not a good taste at all. I don't recommend for anybody and packing also not up to the mark."), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  Only if the picture says it all
Watery Dal Fry
Parson ki Bani Roti
Dustbin mein daaldo Jeera Rice.
Wasted my money on it, BEWARE, Better options available'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Ordered panner manchurian gravy, gravy was good but panner was too hard, it was fried so it was hard. Didn't like the panner . Quantity was good."), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  I ordered paratha instead of that I'm getting chapathi..and side one is kadai panner real photo ....both like rubber.. so worst don't order in this restaurant."), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  The quality of delivery was bad.. instead of packing in cover should have packed in a box as it?s all leaking over the cover,, so better change the way of packing food as we pay for it and do not get it for free. M a vegetarian n I got chicken pieces in the paneer curry what u guys think of ur self m raising a consumer complaint for cheating me, shameless people disgusting,,'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  #Very Bad service , no one cares which cust is coming in his counter , no proper service very bad experience I never ever suggest this place'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  food was spoiled. would never order again'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Really this is a nice restaurant. The food here is also delicious. I mostly order from this. Quantity is also good. I mostly order from this. Quantity is also good.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Food was good, but we ordered Roti but received phulka! There is a difference between phulka and roti!! Kindly review the menu and keep Customer well informed.'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  I didn't like my order..am not at all happy with my order...i felt like i wasted my amount for this order..am sorry to say this...bcoz it doesn't have good taste to eat..."), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  Worst food'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Food is good with quality, quantity and price. The taste of food is owesome. Food is good with quality, quantity and price. The taste of food is owesome.'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  Daal mangayi thi,shit aur daal me pharak nahi pata chal rha, It was my worst decision to order food from this restaurant, I request everyone not to do that.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Good food home like food clans cool about one time come and see test nice place I eat chicken chilliy and roti or partha and lase I file home')]

column3: 21, 1st Cross, Lakshmi Layout, Oppsite DEJA Apartment, Mico Layout, Arekere, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  Road side food is good than ur restaurant food, plz do not provide. I started vomiting because of ur restaurant food. Simply we wasted our many.'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  We ordered grill chicken but the chicken is not cooked properly and the sides what they have given it's spoiled really very bad experience I had with them"), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  I always liked food here but today their so called zinger burger was very bad..i never had burger tasted such bad in all my life...
stone like bun n 2 small pieces of fried chicken in it'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  Ordered French fries online for my orthodox brahmin mother alongwith other items but the order delivered contained chicken popcorn alongwith French fries in the same container. This has offended the religious sentiments of my mother who does not eat even garlic.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Good food. Biriyani was really tasty. Ordered kabab also. But I feel that the food quantity is less in both biriyani and kebab.
But tasty food.'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  Had ordered full grill for 130 today but received only 4 small pieces had a bad and worst experience with the restaurant very less quantity for Raising. 130'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Food is not up to their pricing... arabian cuisine taste is not good... delivery was on time the food quality is not upto the mark... also the parcel was not neatly packed'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Great kababs, and combos as well a must try place for everyone, must order once atleast from here'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  biriyani was not good ,I liked kabab ,nad straw was missing for my two drinks'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Worest restorent, they using expired products and delivered expired food items, don't go health is important for every one.
Zomato and this kind of restorents cheating coustomers"), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Food was awesome, but not much according to the price, the quality should be increased
But I love the taste,, all the masalaa quantity was good I love zomato delivery was upto the time not late'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Loving to have food in arabian mexico.
I had Biriyanis, grilled and Faham chickens, having freshness always. Love it ?
A nice place

THANK you'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Loved the food would order again soon!
Food came fresh and even the drinks tasted good. Highly recommend this place. 5/5 for everything.
Thank you Arabian Mexico'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  I ordered Biryani and chicken kebab, biryani rice was good no point and biryani?s chicken was dry but still eatable but the chicken kebab I ordered was not cooked (rubeery chicken)
and was having a lot of fat'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Wow.
What a wonderful food.

Iam enjoyed @ all.
Shawarma is different taste.

Iam first time eated these type grill chicken.

Broasted chicken was big quantity.

Thank you ARABIAN MEXICO
Thank you zomato')]

column14: [('Rated 1.0', "RATED\n  This is the worst place to get cakes,had ordered a chocolate truffle 1 kg cake from here and that was the worst cake I ever ate. The cake was very hard to eat,not fresh,having some bad smell,the chocolate cream on the top was also very hard the cake was so hard that it was tough to cut it with a knife and it wasn't sweet and I don't like it at all and the delivery was also slow I will definetly not recommend this place to anyone and I'm very disappointed with CakeZone."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED\n  Ordered Ferero Rocher Jar Cake from here. column14:
[('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  The food could have been better... Oil was a little too much also... I think improvement in the cooking will be a great step forward. Best of luck'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Ordered chicken tikka masala, chicken biriyani and prawns biriyani. Prawns Biriyani, you bet, man, that's every worth your penny. Still makes my tastebuds go dancing when I think of it. That P biriyani was PARADISE."), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  not at all good we asked prawns Biryani... wrong food delivered not testy also'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Today i tried kadai chicken and paneer butter masala with butter naan from the restaurant. The food was excellent and tasty also. I ordered for two people by zomato, but it's more quantity than for two people. The food is fine quality and tasty one, for delivery its take little lag.")]

column3: 144/1, 22, 22nd Cross, 24th Main Road Marenahalli, JP Nagar, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  If someone loves Bengali fast food please...dey serve such good food ?? I have ordered twice n both the time it was worth ordering .reminds me of Kolkata'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  The panner roll was cold.'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  even I have paid for double chicken egg roll ...the roll seems to very small and very less chicken in it, and this happened to me 2nd time... nothing extraordinary as taste also'), ('Rated 2.5', 'RATED
  Rolls and Biryani is quite good!!
Kebab was nt at all fresh. ...# disappointing...

Tip: The ambiance always goes for a toss... maintain it constant .. serve good, gain good...'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I just love chicken biriyani... Egg chicken kathi roll and chicken noodles. Amazing quantity and tastes pretty good. I prefer take away as the place is little congested and cannot accommodate a crowd.'), ('Rated 4.5', 'RATED
  Recommended food is chicken fried rice, chicken Manchurian/ chicken 65. The quantity they served is very good. Also, as per the name.... chicken egg roll ( wheat) is most yummiest one. Rest of the dishes I have tried but never liked it. Coming to the ambience it is a sub standard outlet. I prefer home delivery or take away though seating capacity of approx 10 people is available.'), ('Rated 4.5', 'RATED
  Its economic n good in taste.... Chicken egg wheat roll... Chicken fried rice and manchurian chicken is what i prefer.. But in delivery i feel they give not so fresh n in less quantity.. Last time i ordered chicken fried rice.. I had to throw that all.. Coz i felt it to b only rice... Being a college student n its close to our place... So i prefer eating from there.. I hope they come up with the modification.')]

column3: 37, Diagonally Opposite Ranga Shankara, 2nd Phase, JP Nagar, Bangalore
column12: Neer Dosa, Coffee, Pav Bhaji, Khali Dosa, Panipuri, Masala Dosa, Tea
column14:
[('Rated 2.0', "RATED
  Visited this place for breakfast recently and had mixed reviews about it. The ambience has sort of a vintage aura to it with stone slabs as seating arrangement. The service was decent and staff was courteous. We ordered butter masala dosa but the taste wasn't upto the mark, the kottekadubu that we ordered was plain and did not taste like one! It was a letdown. We ordered Gobi Manchurian which was really good. It was crisp and had less masala to it. Loyd | Wheretomunchblr

Ambience - 3
Food - 2.8
Service - 4"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Fast Food !!!

This Restaurant has facility for both service as well as Self Service.
Though the place for self service is limited,its manageable.

The Food is good.
can be visited for a quick snack or coffee.')]

column3: 16, 17, 18/2 Sarakki Lake, 24th Main, 6th Phase, JP Nagar, Bangalore
column12: Pasta, Fries, Cheesiano Pizza, Veggie Pizza, Cheesy Garlic Bread, Peri Peri Paneer Pizza
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Delicious pizza and AMAZING price if you've got the Zomato gold.
It's a well topped up pizza and they offer few interesting flavors.
Give it a try!"), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Had been here last weekend, taste wise it was ok not up to taste as i expected.
Bit cozy environment and only on billing counter was there if it's crowded it'll take time to bill your order

Coming to the food we have ordered pizzas
The cheese was good and the curst was also good enough.

Double cheese margarita pizza was so nice
But I didn't like that bbq mushroom pizza and
Taste of chilly garlic veg pizza was not up to the taste i have expected
Drinks was giving different tastes ok with that"), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Oh my God. It was worst pizza ever. If I call to this branch for enquiry, simply those staff talking we are not responsible and all, don't no is it pizza or what, some bad smell in pizza. And no taste nothing is there, I don't how people gave good rating on this?
Humble request, don't try on this.
But to be frank Pasta was good and spicy. I love the chilli garlic pasta.

Food 1.5/5
Taste 2/5"), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Cheesiano Pizza is the first outlet in Namma Karnataka and a Friend brings this joint to Namma Bengaluru City.

The restaurant has functional interiors and friendly staff. And not forget they serve good food.

We tried Cheese Garlic Bread & Chicken Keema Garlic Bread for starters and Margarita & Chicken Temptation Pizzas.
Slightly on the expensive side, but is good on quality.
See You soon Cheesiano.
All the Best.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  We came here for the first time, it's located beside Hotel Empire in JP Nagar. Had two pizzas and they were good! The toppings were given generously and the taste was good too. :) Cheers!"), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Not up to the mark, i had ordered the pizza home, well the delivery was really fast less than 30 minutes, thx to zomato. The garlic bread was really crisp and on point, while the pizza were not too good, it was okay, i had ordered a thin crust and i got a regular crust pizza, and it wasn't upto the mark, the desserts, the brownie cake was really good while the choco lava cake didn't taste that good, i felt the chocolate inside it wasn't tasty enough and the the other layer wasn't crisp enough. But on the overall experience, it was okay, not too great."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Incredible pizzas! Absolutely fresh and soft base, yummy cheese and loads of toppings. They have got offers running every day and it's steal. Much much better than the international brands. The vegetarian pizza I tried had an Indian style pizza sauce which was a bit odd, however everything else was just perfect."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Pizzas are have become a routine for us, every now and then one would want to have pizzas for breakfast, lunch, and dinner. Pizzas come in all sizes and prices, some thin, some thick, some gigantic, none the less they all take a toll on our tummies. One such place that offers amazing pizzas is Cheesiano Pizza. Not very well known, this place in JP Nagar offers some of the best budget friendly pizza combos and their pizzas are soft and tasty. I have been here a couple of times and I have absolutely enjoyed their offerings. ...
Read full post on ondufullmeals.com'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Bakasura hasn't actually been here. But got it delivered.
So not a review of the ambience but just the food.
Surprisingly had a very good pizza after a long time. The base was good, the cheese was good and the toppings were just great. Looking forward for such pizzerias.
Recommended."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  So had a crappy craving for a pizza, and didn't want to order same ol' Domino's or Pizza hut's pizza, with all obvious less expectations I ordered from Cheesiano's. This place is actually not that bad. You get super good pizza, bread is fresh you can taste the difference, cheesy enough to melt you for a moment! French fries needs a lot of work (not up to mark at all)
I ordered so packaging was good, they did goof up with my order but it was all taken care in the end so no complaints on that. Overall 3.7/5 ??? will check out the actual place soon. Cherrio! ?
(P.S. don't mind okiesh pic included not that good at food pics)"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Had seen this place while crossing it on numerous occasions but never got a chance to taste the pizzas. But one day the trip was made and the mind was blown away. I have a lot of pizza but crust as fresh and soft like this ? NEVER!! A must try for all Pizza lovers and the prices are astonishing,

My report card

Price ? 8/10

Taste ? 8/10

Portion size - 7/10

Service ? 6/10

Ambiance ? 6/10

Cleanliness - 7/10

Value for money ? 8/10

Will I go back ? Absolutely'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  The place is located next to empire in jp nagar. Pretty decent place, nice and clean. Wide variety of pizzas, but they all have a desi touch to it. The medium pizza is delicious and more than filling for an average person.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Had ordered farmers choice and veg spicy pizzas.
Both of them were really good...we liked the farmers choice more.
There's nothing much in the ambience just a small place to sit and eat...good for a casual outing.
They make really good authentic thick crust pizzas..definitely better than dominoes and Pizza Hut.
The pizzas are well priced (especially if you have Zomato gold) and they have really good offers where u get buy one get one free on specific days(wed and Mon).
Staff:6/10
Food:8.5/10
Ambience:7/10"), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Cheesiano Pizza has their menu layout the exact same way as Domino's does - however the pizzas here are really good. Well known for their deep dish pizzas, their quantity and rates of pizzas are very reasonable and are nothing but heaven in your mouth! We tried some of their tier 1 pizzas, and extremely liked them - especially the insane amounts of cheese on them! Service was also good here, however they seemed a little unclear about Zomato Gold and how the policy works. Otherwise, it's a great place to drop by if you're ever bored of the regular pizzas at dominos or pizza hut!

foodforlife24x7.blogspot.com"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  The place is better than expected!!!
We were too full to try out the pizzas. So we just ordered potato pops and French fries. French fries even though hot were a little soggy!! The place is neat and clean. Prices are sooo affordable!! Starting price of pizza is 99 and french fries is 79!!! If you are put up somewhere around Jayanagar DO VISIT!!!'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  A very nice new pizza joint. Loved their Pizza base. Though thick its soft and even and can finish without ignoring sides. Time taken to execute order is good enough. Place is neat can be more neat.

Had been for lunch and started with Cheese Garlic Bread. Its good. Portion size is nice and fine.

Loved the Farmers Choice Pizza with onion toppings capsicum and Diced Tomatoes.

Veg Delight is good too with olives onion Jalepenos. But just felt name is not going with toppings.
But pizza really good.

Paneer Peri Peri Pizza was yum and spice level was good. Consisted of Peri Peri Paneer Onion Capsicum Tomatoes Jalpenos.

Walnut Brownie could have been more soft and Choco lava cake missed the oozing chocolate or else taste was good.

Give it a try and u will love for sure.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  One of the best pizzas I have ever eaten in Bangalore. It's worth every penny. There are a lot of new places serving pizzas , but this is a standout. They serve different bases apart from the normal crusts that we have already tasted. They have very good offers which makes it very pocket friendly.
The staff are very friendly and work for customer satisfaction."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Happened to discover this pizza studio , next to our office at 24 th main . Ordered fiery chicken and spicy chicken pizza ... And it was the best pizza I have ever in any of the branded outlets. The crust was fluffy , crisp on top , just right amount of cheese, butter and sauce. Chicken was succulent with nice flavours. Try this one guys it's not worth missing if you are a pizza lover ?."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

Visited this place on a weekday. Not that crowded yet. We ordered mushroom n barbecue pizza and chilli garlic pasta. The crust of the pizza was really fluffy. That is something they specialize at. Pasta did justice to my taste buds. The only drawback was the size of the portions. Comparatively less according to the price Cheesiano Pizza'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This new restaurant on 24th Main Road serves amazing fresh pizzas topped up with generous amount of cheese and you get to chose crust too. Coming to their pasta, We tried their chilli garlic veg pizza and it was different with pineapple pieces and gave a new flavor to pasta! Their name suits them well.')]

column3: 15, Bannerghatta Main Road, JP Nagar, Bangalore
column12: Chicken Biryani
column14:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Very good Arabian style restaurant and very awesome food and it's verities are approachable.
We usually go here for official lunch, also with a very good ambiance. Do visit here"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Great ambiance and some great food but not the Arabian cuisine though. Rest, the food, service and ambiance is really good! Would recommend this place for some good food in and around J P Nagar'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Can this really be called an Arabian restaurant? No. The menu is mostly filled with typical Indian/Mughlai and Chinese dishes, and the Arabian share is limited to some barbecues. Honestly I was pretty disappointed with their barbecues. It was undercooked and missed the fire character. Though the marination was good, it tasted raw. Surprised that they served Rumali Roti as the side for barbecue instead of Kubboos or any Arabic bread, and the roti was hard and rubbery, inedible. Restaurants like Zaitoon and Fattoush serve absolutely delicious barbecues, even Empire would be a better choice. On the other hand, prawns were delicious and soft like silk.

Ambience is great. Neatly and tastefully done interiors. Pretty good for large groups and families. Service is very good too.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  If you have a craving for Middle Eastern delicacies, now your taste buds would find a justification at Least Arabia. Superb interiors and courteous attendants. The foods are great, specially, the Arabian Shawarma, Nawab Chicken and Irani Kebab are a must try.')]

column14:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  We know the military hotels in and around Bangalore right? They are amazing because of their legacy, the stories you hear from the owners, and also mainly because they nail the brief when it comes to preparing only a few dishes, but preparing them very very well. Dande's is NOT such a place. They have a wide variety, but seldom get it right.

That said, their Dande's Special Chicken Biryani is amazing. Don't be taken aback especially after what I wrote in the previous paragraph. Another analogy for Dande's is like watching Meryl Streep in the movie "The Iron Lady". Their special chicken biryani is exactly like that. They serve really good rice with boneless chicken that are mixed with scrambled eggs. Their taste is really really good and goes amazingly well with the rice. This is a Biryani that you can always eat. The best part is that you don't feel super-heavy after binging on it.

So if you feel the urge to visit this place, do so, but you know what to order. :-)'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  okay ,so this review is only based on special veg biryani. however this place is more popular for non veg items.
veg biryani was too spicy .it had gobi, ? potato,paneer , beans, ? carrot mixed and fried properly. enjoyed eating. you get raita and biryani masala with it.
there is onion and lemon salad with it.

ratings::
Food: 4/5
Packaging: 3/5 ,container would have been better
Quantity : 5/5 ,more than enough for 1 person
spicy: 4/5'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Biryani was good in taste ordered special biryani quantity was more quality was good still the biryani rice need to be cooked well but chicken was good'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Ordered a boneless chicken biryani.  It was ok ,  no complaints or compliments. Yet to try out other dishes to form a opinion. Will try in future.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  I am a Biryani Lover..Ordered Dande's Hyderabadi Boneless Chocken Biryani, Boneless Chicken Manchurian and Chicken kabab.. the Biriyani and Chicken Manchurian was really yummy but the Kabab not up to the mark.. delivery was was very fast by Zomato people..."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Boneless Chicken biriyani is the best option here and very much similar to Hydrabadi biriyani house but dont try lemon chicken and other options it was not at all up to the mark')]

column14:
[('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Unhygienic place , chicken did not taste fresh

Pizzas were ok ok

Management should consider repainting the place and get some better people in place

Thanks'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  There's no point in keeping 'name of the week' (NOTW). This outlet had no pasta for the NOTW.
And the menu for NOTW is so restricted. No more choices were left for us to choose. We ordered 2 pizzas, berry cheesecake and a coke. They all tasted fine. Service was so so slow."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Had ordered pizzas for delivery and they were really quick and the pizzas tasted good too.

1 pizza can fill your hunger and is open even at late nights to satisfy your pizza cravings!

They also have veg and non veg buffets and good deserts to accompany that.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Had ordered veg Mexican delight pizza and wedges for the dinner.the taste was good, liked potato wedges.the delivery was done on time.the experience was good.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  It was extremely busy on 31st night. We had to wait for 20 minutes to get a table. Maybe for the rush, the service got little clumsy. We order- Chicken Pasta, Chicken cheese stuffed pizza, Fried chicken with peri peri sauce and Tiramisu for our dinner. Onesta serves Cafe cuisine, so potion sizes are quite small. Pasta was very much over priced.
All the food item was tasty.
Abhisek Gayen'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Tried Schezwan Chicken Pizza, Barbecue Chicken Pizza and Chicken Tikka pizza. Chicken Tikka tasted the best of the three, followed by Barbecue Chicken. Service is good, place needs to up its ambience game. I found it to be cramped with no special feel to to it. Dessert was average, the Mojito was good.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  If you are between 30 to 40 years old, the perception you have of pizza growing up is Dominos and Pizza Hut, and of course from your local bakery which knew only to serve Amul cheese, capsicum, tomato base and onions. I mean these were the early days. Pizza baking in India has evolved quite a bit since then. Look at the varieties you get now. Onesta does complete justice to serving pizzas for 1. They are immensely flavored especially because of their pizzas having just a couple of ingredients. Less is More with Onesta.

I like their Margherita pizza and their Bacon Prawn pizza. The reason I don't feel a 5/5 is because when they deliver, the pizza isn't served warm, thereby requiring me to use the microwave oven to heat it back up."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  To start with, the place has a loootss and looottss of verity of pizzas. The ones even you wouldn't have even heard of.

Tiny pizzas , in many different shapes and decorations. Tasty and flavorful. Very good crowd. Service is moderate to good, depending on the crowd. Value-for-money place.

Table booking on weekends ,is highly recommended.
If more place is available, then would be better. And wish that, there would be small size pizzas, to taste First and then order, so that , for tasting the new ones, people need not order a complete pizza and waste if they don't like it."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  We have unlimited buffet . It was crazy and pizzas r good full of cheese n thin crust !! So go for it all the pizza lovers don?t miss it !!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Looking for an unlimited pizza menu? Then onesta is definitely one of the best places to chose. Their unlimited menu for amazing pizza and desserts is what that attracts people. Their pizzas are just mouth watering with unique spice and sweet flavours. Love the Chocolate pizza over here which is topped with banana. Each bite just cracks you up! They have amazing spread for desserts too.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Place with a nice impressive range of pizzas and desserts, along with nice offers from time to time ! Went for the non veg unlimited pizza offer this time and they didn't disappoint ?

Would recommend the lemon cilantro fish and chicken bacon prawn pizzas.

The choco mocha cake deserves a special mention !!!

Was a little disappointed that the rooftop sitting was closed..."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  We ordered a few pizzas, pastas and bruschetta from this place.
By the time the pizzas came home they got a bit soggy and lost their crisp and taste.
The pastas were really good. Special mention to the makhni sauce pasta, the arabbiata was also tangy and full of flavours.
The bruschetta however was horrible and had a smell to it.
The price point is very reasonable but the food could be better.

Verdict : can give it a try but better pizza joints around.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Food - 4/5 ( Ordered assortment of cake pieces)
Delivery - 3.5/5 ( Huge delay in delivery through Uber Eats)
Price - 4/5 ( Seemed reasonable)
Hygiene - 4/5


I am otherwise I huge fan of onesta chain. But this delivery I had ordered for a special occasion and the cakes were packed in worst way in a huge pack possible. Not only the stuff was damaged but was delivered in very bad shape. Upon that despite me having given proper address and geo location, the driver was very confused on arriving where he needs to arrive.

Honestly taste was not that bad, but the cake got mashed against each other which made the entire experience a sour one.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Incredible place. Fell in love with the pizzas and service and their happy hour prices. Truly delicious pizzas topped with great service at affordable prices. Their happy hours will literally make you happy! Try the unlimited option if you have lots of space in your stomach. Don't miss it. If you don't have a sweet tooth, do not try their tangy or sour pizzas, it could possibly ruin your taste buds."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Place with a nice impressive range of pizzas and desserts, along with nice offers from time to time ! Went for the non veg unlimited pizza offer this time and they didn't disappoint ?

Would recommend the lemon cilantro fish and chicken bacon prawn pizzas.

The choco mocha cake deserves a special mention !!!

Was a little disappointed that the rooftop sitting was closed..."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  We ordered a few pizzas, pastas and bruschetta from this place.
By the time the pizzas came home they got a bit soggy and lost their crisp and taste.

The bruschetta however was horrible and had a smell to it.

Verdict : can give it a try but better pizza joints around.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED

column14: [('Rated 4.0', 'RATED\n  Go here for the dosas and South Indian breakfast food in general and skip all the North Indian stuff! column3: 986, 1st Block, Vijaya Bank Layout, 4th Stage, BTM, Bangalore
column12: Tea, Vada Sambar, Masala Dosa
column14:
[('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  So we ended up here on a late lazy Sunday afternoon breakfast.I ordered the paneer masala dosa and my friend ordered paddu.The dosa they make are really good crispy and a beautiful golden colour it has.I was expecting the aloo to be replaced to paneer masala as stuffing but it turned out to be paneer grated on to aloo masala.which I felt could have changed,the paddu took really long time but can't blame them because we went at around 12 for breakfast but when it came burnt on one side which they called it extra fry it was a disappointed .
Must Try:Definitely the Masala dosa(Not paneer ;) and palak Paneer which we always order from this place(Keep it up)
Paddu:50rs (6 pieces big one)
Paneer masala dosa:70rs
Location:This is actually in Vijaya bank Layout
Rating is based on truelly the above instance."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Ambience - 3/5  Food - 4/5  Service 3/5  VFM - 4/5  Parking - None

This is a long pending review one of the popular Darshinis at Vijaya Bank Layout. Been there  for breakfast. They don?t have much of seating space, only a single bench and some standing tables.Food was good as expected. we had Mallige Idli,vada and Masala dosa. Food was good and tasty. I?d recommend this place for their breakfast if you happen to be nearby')]

  Since a few months, I have started craving for Donne Biryani as I have gradually developed a taste for it. I have had donne biryani at some famous and legendary restaurants and military hotels in Bengaluru. However, when it comes to delivery, I was not aware of a good donne biryani joint that delivers to our doorstep.

I recently ordered from Aramane Donne biryani and really liked the taste and quality. The biryani is aromatic and as you open the parcel, you can smell the aroma of spices. It's really delicious. The mutton is very well cooked and if you add a few drops of lemon juice on top of biryani, the flavour reaches to a next level. It's definitely a must-try item to have it from this restaurant. Their Egg biryani is also too good."), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED

column5: ""RATED\n  Yet another place close to my office meaning it was bound to be one of our lunch spots sooner or later. They serve Donne Biryani with a selection of side dishes. I found the Biryani to be quite dry
column6: maybe it is supposed to be like that but I am not so sure. Need to have Donne Biryani's from some other places as well before I can comment on that
column7: or maybe I am spoilt by the choice of Hyderabadi Biryani's available in Bangalore. Anyways
column8: their Biryani wasn't anything worth writing home about but their side dishes
column9:
well that was on another level all together.

I found the side dishes here to he very rich and each side dish had a distinct taste which might not be the case at many other places. Their 65 tasted like a 65 and their ghee roast tasted like how a ghee roast should taste.

Even though the place is called Aramane Donne Biryani
column10: I felt that the side dishes were the real stars here. Do not miss out on any of their side dishes if you happen to visit this place!"")

column14:
[('Rated 2.0', "RATED
  Ordered Chilli cheese sandwich and choco milk shake. The packaging was good and I actually didn't expect the milk shake to come in a shake bottle; liked it. They also kept my request of making the sandwich in the brown bread.
However, the rating is purely on the taste of the food and I was disappointed.
1. One would expect the chilli cheese sandwich to have bell peppers with cheese, but here I got ONLY chopped green chillis with cheese, and that too loads of chopped chillis (see one of the photos). My mouth was literally on fire.. I couldn't take more than two three bites..
2. Choco milk shake was too sweet for my taste and was very thin in the consistency..
Overall didn't quite enjoy the experience."), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Are you kidding me???

I was so hungry, on a sunday, and decided to order this Chilli Cheese Sandwich & Chocolate milkshake, and this is what i get??

When i opened the sandwich, all i find is Tons of chilli, and almost no cheese, and damn...its so dry. The bread was not buttered enough / at all before grilling, and it was literally just bread and chilli...!!!

And see the milkshake...there is a thick layer of cream floating... which feels weird to the pallette, but apart from that, the milkshake is very low on chocolate flavour...feels like a very light boost...:/

Very dissapointed. And this is not the first time, all my previous orders were like this. I am usually not one to give a negative review on the first shot, but guys,.... thid was the 3rd or 4th time i'm ordering.

Will not be ordering again, if this is the quality you manage to put out. Please improve the quality guys. Come on!

-Abhishek Bhaskar.")]

[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Quality Biriyani but nothing special in it, I am hard core biriyani lover and I had seen good reviews about mani?s and ordered thorough zomato, it was warm but the chicken taste was very average, nothing much to talk about this biriyani and its flavour. I can see good reviews in zomato but when i check online order reviews almost everyone rated less than 3 star, is there any difference in online orders ? Strange'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Heard about this resturant in past which is famous for its Biryanis. Thought to give it a try so ordered a Chicken Biryan Full. The packaging was good and quantity was good for two moderate eaters. It had 3 pieces of chicken and 1 egg.

Coming to the taste, it was average. It was bit dry and there was a slight taste of raw ginger. I liked it but there was nothing special about it.'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Not a biryani I would crave for. I ordered chicken 65 biryani in turn I got biryani with two chicken kebabs and a boiled egg in it. Taste of biryani was also kind of ok.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Have heard much about Mani?s Biryani and all things were true. Found it of the best restaurant for Biryani in Bangalore.
Taste - 5/5
Pricing - 4/5
Portioning - 4/5'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Ordered very biryani. It won't blow your mind. Average taste. Too much masala and the delivery was pretty quick. Not impressed much. Will have to try other variants too"), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Tried Mani's Dum Biryani for the first time. I am a vegetarian.. hmm I know you guys are already judging me on vegetarian biryani review.. however it was brilliant. Taste 9 on 10, quantity 10 on 10 and cost 8 on 10. Combos are worth purchasing. They are running a brilliant offer on takeaway."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED

column14:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Food quality is okay.
Rui macher jol was good. Chicken curry was too watery. And shorshe ilish was bitter.
Loved the mishti doi.
Price is cheap.
Ambience is okay.
Aloo posto was good too.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  We ordered breakfast from here.. koraisutir kochuri with alurdam and luchi and chole dal...

It tasted very good... loved both the dishes... but.. 1 negative point... quantity of both cholardal and alurdam was very very less... the bowl was not even half filled..

Mgmt.. please take care of this... you know u can do that at the same price'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  I have been a regular customer to this place since a long time. The food is not out of the world but has homely taste. Also is very economical with an amicable staff. I know even though the hygiene level is not to the higher extent I choose to continue eating here coz of the taste.
But today?s event completely changed my perception about this place. Saw one of the new guys sharpening the knife used in the kitchen on the steps of the restaurant. Told him and the other guy to wash it before he uses it but to my astonishment the guy simply started chopping veggies ignoring my as well as the other staff?s advice. Instead he asked to pull the curtain to the kitchen.
Not visiting the place ever. Hope the msg reaches the owner and he ensures hygiene to some extent is maintained. Attaching image of the steps highlighting the spot where it was sharpened.'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  Had been there on their opening day, and so wanted to check how they were faring. And the less said the better. The quality of food was terrible, along with the packaging(ordered take away). Though I usually don?t judge a book by its cover, it?s not a bad idea when it comes to Bengali restaurants in Bangalore. The amount of oil floating on the top of every curry was scary. Thankfully this was a hard hitting nail on the coffin, so as to get it sealed in one go itself. Never repeating it.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I had ordered luchi alur dom it was fabulous and worth of money full of bengali taste without any doubt. I also had ruhi jhol, katla kalia fish items with rice and aloo posto which was mouth watering what else we bengali need, and ending with kejur er chutney. Below is the picture of alur dom'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  It is a small Bengali food joint having 18-20 sitting capacity and located in btm near Vega Mall.
Ambience is ok... Cleanliness needs improvement...
Let's talk about food. Typical bong food like sukto, dhokar dalna, pui saak diye chocchori, jhuri aloo vaja, dim(egg) kosha etc. are available.
We ordered Chicken cutlet, rice, kucho chingri jhal and MISTI doi. Also took parcel sukto, aloo Posto, dim kosha, chicken curry...
Taste of all of them are just perfect as we cook in home... Dim kosha was too good... And the most important is the value for money... All these we had by paying below 500 bucks...
I would recommend this for those who wants to have regularly...
Cheers..."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  It?s a small place serves Bengali food at an affordable price. The interior of this place is nice. Visited this place few times and had a mixed experience. First time I had Thali and fish items it was below average. Next time I had biryani it was good. The service is slow.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  There are few bangoli restaurant in BTM and it is one of them, which provide almost all type of bangoli food.... taste was good and simple... and the prices were also reasonable....
for simple bangoli food you can definitely try this place....
Suggestion to management : you can add Thali in your menu...
Edited the rating from 3 to 4 star')]

column14:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  One of the best biryanis ... Mutton Biryani is the best.. the pieces arent too bony... Veg biryani is pretty good as well, chicken Biryani is between ok and good.. starters are tasty, over all limited options, but these options are pretty good..however if Ur not used to spicy food take ur ant acids before u go to bed...the day u eat from here'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  The taste is priority than ambience, I loved the taste of Redddy's hot and Birinz special bone less biryani they both taste awesome after a long time I had my kind of biryani."), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Repeated counts of wrong delivery service, be it via any delivery app, these guys just don't seem to understand the order placed and send wrong orders without even confirming with the customer. Prawn Biryani order becomes Paneer and Chicken Biryani becomes boneless chicken biryani without even asking you. The point is, if you can't deliver the right order.. just make sure you call the customer and confirm it.
Being a foodie, I have had good feedback about you guys but the recent orders have forced me to rate you to this."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  After pondering where to order my Biriyani from and debating all the options available around jayanagar I decided to go with birinz this weekend. We ordered the butter chicken Biriyani and Andhra chilli chicken. The hot and spicy chilli chicken complimented the rich butter chicken Biriyani. We polished off the entire serving and literally didn?t even leave a grain of rice.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Visited this restaurant with few of my friends for a weekend lunch. Had heard a lot about their biryani and the varieties of toppings they provide. The ambiance of the place is normal. Located on the btm main road. You won?t find much difficulty to locate the place.
We started with some dry starters which had chef special chicken starters, Prawns dry fry, and coke, for the main course we ordered a Hyderabadi chicken biryani, Butter chicken biryani and boneless chicken biryani. Everything was up to the mark.butter chicken biryani I had tried for the first time but to my surprise it was not at all sweet. Was very buttery and and yummy in taste.i would love to visit again and also get the biryani homedelivered'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  This is located in BTM and I guess if your looking to have a variety of biriyanis.. this is really the go to place!!
We went as a group of 10 so I guess we ordered atleast 5-6 starters and almost all the chicken fish and prawn biriyanis available on their menu..
For the biriyani the rice is same for all and it?s good too.. just the masalas change for each type.. so I really don?t know which biriyani is the best!
But the staff is not very friendly.. you need to keep asking them if you need something which was something at times we got a bit irritated
My overall rating
Food 5/5
Ambience 4/5
Staff behaviour 3/5
Value for money 5/5

This is available in Zomato Gold as well!! And a good option in that area for biriyani cravings ?'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  If you are a biryani lover, you must visit this place. Not much of any ambience or anything. But it definitely has a lot of options for biryani starting from chicken to mutton to fish biryani?s. We ordered mutton shorba, which was one of the best I?ve ever had. Then we ordered mutton mughlai biryani and gongura mutton biryani. Both of them were awesome, rich and flavorful taste. I would definitely go back here to try out the remaining ones.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Their menu listed Ulavacharu Biryani and says open till mid night which prompted us to visit this restaurant on Sunday night. To our disappointment the dish was not avaialble but the waiter recommended Reddy's Red Hot Biryani, Other dishes we ordered were Egg Biryani with Dum rice and baby corn starter. Their recommendation was top class and still tasted fresh, one of the best biryani I have had for a long time. Other dishes were above average. My son wanted ice cream which was not available but they allowed us to get desserts from a shop Immeidate next to it. Have not taken pics this time as we were busy hogging food?. Ambience was nice and Staff were super friendly and service was excellent which made me give a 4/5. Next visit will be with a group of friends and I'll update feedback.

Like I said I went for 2nd visit with friends and we tried pretty much all the chicken starters including their biriyanis. Yes, Ulavacharu Biriyani too."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Had one of the finest hyderabadi biriyani from there. Good quality basmati rice with succulent pieces of nicely cooked chicken on top. Flavours were outstanding. Also had their starter "Maharaja Chicken". It was again a very good dish. Decent seating arrangements. Good service.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Was in Bangalore for a day , order our dinner from Birinz , We ordered for :
Paneer Sholey: Paneer pieces tossed in ginger ,garlic onion, coloured pepper . really enjoyed the flavors.

Reddy?s Chicken Biryani : Boneless chicken biryani . Flavors were beautiful but then i found it a little too spicy, it was served with raita and a gravy to go with.

Over all i liked this restaurant will definitely order everytime i am in Bangalore.

Cheers.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Birinz has been a delivery only Biriyani place for years. And now this is a restaurant which they have launched recently. They serve 10/12 different varieties of andhra biryanis. The rice remains the same in all , the long basmati rice with nice aroma which you get in all andhra biryanis. Considering the food alone, it?s 5/5 any day. But as a restaurant, it think there is scope for improvement on service and ambience. ACs were not switched even with all the seats occupied on a Sunday afternoon. There is continuous clamour at the reception with a huge crowd for delivery orders and the staffs runnings around for that. They can manage their delivery system in a better way so that it doesn?t affect the restaurant ambience or service.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Everyday is Biryani day and today was no different !!! Drove almost 20kms to find this place. The first thing was the restaurant ambience and I was in dual mind to sit or leave but for the love of Biryani I was glued here.

Ordered almost every Biryani on the menu. The masala in each of these were unique but the Biryani rice was just same for everything. Ordered some andra starters and they were good too

Definitely the restaurant needs an overhaul #thinditheertha'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I would give 4.5 from my side!
Birinz which started as delivery since 6-8 years now turned into restaurant in BTM is one perfect choice for lunch and dinner with your loved ones. Both veg and non veg they have a lot of varieties to treat your tummy. You must try their biryani. We had chicken patyala, chicken 555, Birinz special biryani, butter naan, lassi and lime juice.
Starters were amazing and biryani tasted delicious! Love how they cook in firewood  and the outcome is so perfect! 
Ambience is just like other family restaurants but what is worth your money is the tasty food they serve.
Just one correction is that lassi could have been better but rest all is just perfectly correct!
Overall a must try place!'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED

  This place has a lot of options on biryani. Visited this place once recently and loved their service and ambience. But just yesterday got it delivered home. I'm glad they delivered the food from btm layout to Vijaynagar. Their packing was excellent. Their biryanis are cooked on firewood which amplifies the taste. I ordered
? Chicken Maharaja - Excellent. It consisted of bell peppers , onion and chillies.
? Hyderbadi dum biryani - Very good. The pieces were perfectly marinated and the rice was flavoured with spices. This biryani is a must try and is for people who love spicy food.
? Reddy's biryani - Very good.This biryani rice is topped with Andhra gravy and is less spicy when compared to Hyderbadi dum biryani."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  I tried this place recently on my visit to BTM. Mr. Chandu was generous enough to serve us with his special biryani and starters. We tried 5 different biryani and the flavours of the meat and spices subtle bringing out the rice in its full glory. The masala tickled your palate. A touch of tanginess that flirted with your senses.
In addition to the uniform garnishes, each variant is lavished with aromatic whole spices such as clove, cinnamon and bay leaves.
Another interesting fact about this place is that they use firewood to cook their biryani.
I highly recommend this place for some good and affordable biryani.
We tried -
Paneer Biryani
Reddy's Special Biryani
Ghonghura Biryani
Chicken biryani
Chicken shorba
Chicken Cashew Fry
Papad chicken
Andhra style Chicken"), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED

column3: Survey # 81/4A, Cave Temple Road, Opposite Meenakshi Mall, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column12: Fries, Whole Meat Shawarma
column14:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Today was the first time I tried Shawarma from here and was happy with it. Though there were some issues yet overall it tasted nice. I wanted to give it 3.5 but Zomato does not offer that option nowadays. Having to choose between 3 and 4, had to settle with 3 because of the pita bread.
I had ordered Whole Meat Shawarma with extra cheese and was not disappointed with the filling. The chicken was well cooked and the filling had enough moistness because of the extra cheese. The chicken also had good smokiness because of the grill which I loved.
However, the pita bread needed a little more time in the oven. 
I would have loved some smokiness added to it from the brown spots and blisters of a well-cooked bread. 
That would have added so much to the overall taste of the dish.

But not a bad option to order your food from when your taste buds are looking for something middle eastern!'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Quick grab? Call just shawarma. Less spicy but juicy chicken? Call just shawarma. Thanks for today's delivery. It was raining but the zomato delivery guy reached on time with the food. Good job guys!"), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  Unsatisfactory!

I dropped down here on a Saturday night to pick up a Shawarma roll. Just when I started is when I realized that I shouldn?t have stopped by. The roll was too dry and also the filling was not up to the par.')]

  it was cold'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  This place is named similar to the famous and iconic Hyderabad Biryaani House. Basically a cheap tactic to steal customers. To add to the confusion, Zomato has mapped this place and the Bannerghatta Road branch of Hyderabad Biryaani House at same location on the map which is actually a location of this place. Happened to send someone to pickup Vegetable Biryani from the Hyderabad Biryaani House but they ended up here.

The biryani was so spicy that I couldn't eat more than a few morsals. It had overcooked boiled tasteless potatoes, over fried dead beans and lots and lots of uncooked green peas. The salan served along was okay.

Wasted 350 rs because@ of these hopeless people and technical mistake from Zomato. Slept hungry. BEWARE!!! Most of the good reviews here are for the original Hyderabad Biryaani House and not for this restaurant."), ('Rated 3.5', 'RATED
  This restaurant is located on the arekere signal. They have expertise in biriyani and kababs.

The ambiance is ok not too great as its a average eating joint. Service is also ok.

One should must try thier ghee rice with butter chicken. And do not miss the prawns Manchurian.
Thier biriyani is lil spicy by taste so if you prefer less spicy please tell them well in advance.

This is a good restaurant for a pocket friendly lunch or dinner.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Ok Indian food...I ordered thinking its Hyderabad biriyani next to next to Wangs... the Map said so.. But this is different. Moderately OK food.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

  This place is named similar to the famous and iconic Hyderabad Biryaani House. Basically a cheap tactic to steal customers. Happened to send someone to pickup Vegetable Biryani from the Hyderabad Biryaani House but they ended up here.

The biryani was so spicy that I couldn't eat more than a few morsals. It had overcooked boiled tasteless potatoes, over fried dead beans and lots and lots of uncooked green peas. The salan served along was okay.

column90:
I decided to stop over at this new joint near home.

Menu is quite the regular stiff you expect from this genre of restaurants.

Ordered a special hyderabadi boneless chicken biriyani. You'd expect the biriyani to be hot. This was lukewarm at best. The chicken pieces were quite hard. The biriyani itself was too salty. Was spicy as expected though.

Will give this place another try in a couple of days and see if stuff does improve."")]"

column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  "How the fish can you do this"... As a seafood lover I've always wanted to have something fresh and good also not heavy on my belly and pocket.. Seer fish at 99 and mackeral at 70 .. U gotta be kidding.. none of the prices above 149... Howzz that even possible...!!! Well anyways though it's at a giveaway price doesn't mean the taste is compromised.. though the biriyani is bland the fish and curries are not.. the Tikka stands out too... But the best stuff is their bbq fishes... One for the seafood lover inside you.

FOOD : 4.5/5
PACKING AND QUANTITY : 5/5
VFM : 10/5')]

column14:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  I ordered veg biryani. It was like white rice only not even pulao. no spices no test like biryani. Only good thing was packing and quantity..'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I had ordered "Baby corn Lemon& Mushroom pepper dry". Mushroom pepper dry was yummy & spicy ?? ... Awesome ??. Baby corn lemon will go with people who will prefer less spicy'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  After lot of scrolling I finally decided to take a risk and order from this very new restaurant.
Well it turned out to be really good one. Not the best but really good in taste and quality'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Delicious food. Love the quantity and packaging. Great choices for all occasions. Love the vegetarian and non vegetarian verities. A must eat!'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Best place for a take away or ordering . . Both quality and quantity is high . . Satisfaction to the core . . Not only non veg, even the vegetarian is damn tastier . . Mixed veg curry and paneer chilli, the best on my first veg try here . . Highly recommended guys . . Give a try and definitely you will order for the second time . . Packing is great too . .'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Hey everyone.. pakka hyderabadi style biriyani and good quality packing... chicken 555 was awesome tastes yummy , best place to after midnight... delivery time was as promised'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Food at any time! Best fresh food even after midnight
And best quality packing, need not to compromise on taste best hydarabadi Biriyani and much more....
Thank you Biriyani Bhatti'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I have tasted Haderbadi Biriyani here on first day, good, spicy and tastes soooo good, (I like spicy)Best with curd and soda.....

also tasted chicken keema roll and it's cruchy *****
????")]

column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Have been there and ordered home delivery and have picked up myself...love the Mutton biryani and kebabs they prepare. Be prepared to wait on weekends due huge rush..'), ('Rated 3.5', "RATED
  Have tried this place..koramangala outlet and the bannergatta one...so we cannot expect anything fancy or nice...but the biriyanis are nice here...spicy ones...service is okay...They take 20 min o more...place was kinda full...All regular seatings...
It's in 1st floor...The stairs we gotta climb is sad (bad maintenence)
This rating is only for the food served. ?"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  This Place never fails to amuse me with its taste!!! One of the best biryani adda?
I ordered the family pack biryani combo and chicken kebabs, both were out of the world!!!
Keep up the good work team?'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Not a good experience I would say having tried this place many times I would say it's always a mixed experience. Sometimes it's impressive then it become dull next time. The place unexpectedly changes taste used to serve spicy biryanis earlier now it's standard has got down does not have that kind of biryani. With so many biryani restaurants competing in this area, this place sure dilutes down compare to nagarjuna and nandhana which have remained constantly great in terms of food and service. They need to make changes soon or else it would become an only delivery outlet.")]

column3: Vega City Mall, 3rd Floor, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column12: Chicken Grill, Garlic Bread, Mocktails, Burgers, Fries, Salads, Pudding
column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Stopped for a quick bite here and ordered the Chicken and Pineapple Sosaties. Delicious chicken skewers that had been well marinated and properly grilled. Succulent and flavourful. Would be nice to have a little salad or even lettuce to go with it.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Nice decor. Pleasant ambience. Persons assisting the foodies (customers) are super professional & helpful. The taste & quality of food is superb. The 5-types of sauces available at each of the tables are icing on the cake. Must visit.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  It is an ok place.. the half chicken was good.. but the green apple cooler and lemonade were very very sweet . Ordered chicken espetada.. it was not all that good.. the corn on the cob was bland, garlic bread was ok n the fries were good. Don't think will visit again . But need to mention the staff were really attentive and good.. so I have given one extra star for them.."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Situated in the food court in Vega City Mall, this can be your new South African inspired chicken shop. They tend to give you the spiciest flame grilled out there in the city. Minimal seating and an open kitchen make it an interesting setup for sure.

*Food*
Not many options were available in beverages other than soft drinks. A lot of options in chicken available, the recommended are :

Boneless Chicken Breast
Chicken Espatada
Pulled Chicken Burger

The main issue I find is that even the spiciest sauces don't tend to reach for water ( courtesy Indians spice power). It is a different try for sure.

foodndestinations.com"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Visited the Galito's outlet in Vegacity mall. Galito's proclaims to bring "BOLD AFRICAN FLAVOUR" to our city. Those who've visited Nando's can instantly relate to this place.

The food, the menu, the decor - they all reminded me of Nando's. I will however say that the service here is much better. Galito's' famed flame grilled chicken is "the bee's knees". The peri-peri sauce comes in 5 variants - Mild, Garlic, Hot, Lemon & Herb and Premium Reserve.

The grilled chicken breast in the peri-peri chicken burger could've been tenderized better. The chicken and veggie rice though was flavourful and wholesome.

The fiery pineapple mocktail was sublime. Just the right mix of sweet and heat. The mombo mint though was a little too thick in consistency.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Awesome place for a grub in vega city. They are comparatively cheaper then Nandos who serve similar food but the quality is at par!!! Also they have options like meals for 2, 4 and 6 wherein 1 can select drink, starter and main course. The only problem was we can order a mix of veg and non veg in these options, I hope the management would look into that'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  When in a mall it's very common that you just go into the food court and not notice the restaurants around(atleast that's what most of the people I know do?) ya but this place looked interesting and I happened to go there with a friend of mine. Trust me it was a good decision we made!!! The chicken here is to die for... The food is really good.. the only thing I found bad was the bun they used. It was a bit soggy they can use better ones.
My review for the place
Food 4.5/5
Ambience 3.5/5
Service 4/5
Cost for 2 800-1000"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Meal for 2 deal is amazing. Quantity is generous! Chicken strips rice bowl with Mayo is the winner. Soups are so creamy and sumptuous. Overall it was a great deal as for the quantity and the quality the money was very reasonable. Coming back for soup and rice bowls.Cheers!'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Loved the taste of each of the food served here in unique manner...Presentation is so good and taste of the chicken is so nice. A must visit for all chicken lovers. Service is quick and price is affordable.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Felt the place is a hybrid between a fast food restaurant & fine dining .The grill specially the starter were good 4/5 . The meat specially was soft & juicy . However the burger & wrap would be 3/5 . The service between the team was well coordinated.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Galito?s is a relatively new chain of restaurants in Bangalore that is known for its South African flame grilled meats.
The chicken Espetada is a must try. Chunks of well marinated chicken thighs served piping hot and fresh out of the flame on skewers with onions and crunchy peppers.
The cheesy toast and the grilled chicken liver, to my surprise were tasty and had sharp distinct flavours that is pleasing to the Indian palette.
Make sure you save room for dessert because you just have to dig into their Malva pudding served with ice cream and warm caramel sauce. Their baked yoghurt with blueberry compote is another dessert I would recommend.
You can definitely tell that every effort is made to serve you the best quality of chicken that is well marinated for 24 hours and served to you fresh off the flame grill.
The staff were prompt and well informed and their service was courteous.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Perhaps the first of its kind in Bangalore... African cuisine with sauce selection for dishes. We were attend by Vishwa, We went with their recommendations. Beautiful lightning with African sauces on tables and some decent, Music was slightly loud but it was great.

We tried the following:

Lemon & Herb Satay
Galito's Special: Chicken and Prawns Combotada
Flame grilled: Boneless Chicken Breast
Galito's Special : Paneer Espatada
Grilled Vegetables
Cheesy toast
Fries
Garlic bread
Malva pudding with ice cream and some mocktails such as Mint cooler

Prompt service with quick service. Their recommendations were top class. Tender chicken was used for Satay and Flame Grilled while a regular use for combodata; prawns were huge with different flavor, definitely on the spicy side as we preferred something hot.

Overall a Great experience, Must visit for African flavor."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  This pleasant little place is located in Vega City. Out of all the restaurants in the food court, the smell of the food that draws you right to it is Galito's. Even if you're not interested in visiting the mall, a trip just to taste the food in Galito's is totally worth it.
Having tried both veg and non veg items on the menu, it is safe to say that the food is absolutely spectacular! These African flavours are lip-smacking especially when you add their signature sauces Lemon-Pepper, Garlic, Mild, Peri Peri, and Hot. There's no need to mention any favorite dishes because everything tastes wonderful!
The service is fast and the value for money is pretty good. So go try it out and don't forget to take a bottle of sauce back home with you :D"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Felt the place is a hybrid between a fast food restaurant & fine dining .The grill specially the starter were good 4/5 . The meat specially was soft & juicy . However the burger & wrap would be 3/5 . The service between the team was well coordinated.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

  My perfect Sunday brunch couldn't get any better, just the ambience of this fiery African cuisine restaurant takes you by heart and when I talk about African,hell yeah! Every spice imported and home made sauces makes them completely natural yet unique.The menu was so huge and it just got better and better with every serving, I'm a fan of this place and I have no reasons why it shouldn't be a perfect fit for any gloomy day for any of you
So here was the menu that I personally recommend you to not miss
Chicken Espeteda- Perfectly tender and diced chicken on grill
Borie rolls- Authentic African version of hot dogs
Chicken and pineapple sosaties- Hate pineapple? Think over and you will love this awesome preparation
Malva pudding - Melting caramel to blend in with cold Vanilla,oh gosh it's mouth watering ?
I really thank the Chef and entire staff management to make this such a wonderful experience to end my weekend"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  We have been there at yesterday diwali night. Place was almost full. Ordered fresh lemonade, watermelon juice, quarter chicken with 1 sides alomg with Chicken Satay.

Service was very quick and total place was very clean with open kitchen sytle. Loved the ambiance. A ???????? from me.

facebook.com'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  We went there last weekend to get a treat from our friend?
We heard about Galito's but never visited so this was our first visit.
First visit became so yummmmmmm n tastyyyyyy???
Specially their sauces with different flavors ??

We ordered so many things so don't remember exactly all names but almost we ordered each snacks of chicken n one prawns as well in which a set of prawns n chicken were hanging with the stand and the taste of this one is the best.

Please try to have this at least whenever you plan to visit their... Really recommendable ??

One thing which we liked most is the taste of food as they prepare with your choice of flavors whether it should be less spicy or more.

We ordered some drinks as well with flavors of mint, mango and green apple. So just one suggestion, please use real fruits instead of using some flavors.."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Without a doubt a must try place for chicken and sauce lovers. Located along side Bannerghatta road in Vega City Mall these guys have a limited number of food items but bang hard on taste.
All their main course items are prepared based on the type of sauce given by you at the time of order.
We tried only two food items and they both were bang on.
For starters we had chick-inse which is nothing but a piece of bread with tons of chicken, cheese and taste just amazing.
And grilled chicken with mild sauce was made just right and juicy.
Their ice tea was a bit off and something that can be improved.
But overall a great experience and a place I will definitely visit again to try out rest of the food items.
A highly recommended place.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  My perfect Sunday brunch couldn't get any better, just the ambience of this fiery African cuisine restaurant takes you by heart and when I talk about African,hell yeah! Every spice imported and home made sauces makes them completely natural yet unique.The menu was so huge and it just got better and better with every serving, I'm a fan of this place and I have no reasons why it shouldn't be a perfect fit for any gloomy day for any of you

column276: ""RATED\n  The new kid on the block to challenge Nando's with African food... Located at Vega city mall
column277: this is easy to locate...\n\nWe ordered Chick-E-Naise
column279: Grilled Chicken and Malva Pudding... The service was really swift... Chick-E-Naise is basically Chicken garlic Bread... This was really cheesy... Just loved it... The chicken salad was normal salad with grilled chicken on top of it... GRILLED CHICKEN was the main item in the menu which was highly recommended... 2 pieces of chicken leg pieces... Soft
column280: tender and juicy... This is easily my favorite here... And the dish of the menu for me is Malva Pudding... It's apricot pudding topped with caramel sauce... Simply awesome... The pudding was really soft and was not too sweet
column281: which was great...\n\nWould love to visit this place more to try out more items from the menu..."")
column283: ""RATED\n  I saw the hype on Zomato which led me to this place. The ambience is perfectly made which gives you a feel of a standalone restaurant event though it is located in a Mall.\nThe staff were polite to offer us the table of our choice. As the concept was very much similar to Nandos
column284: it didn't take much time for us to place the order.\n\nWe ordered for Chicken Espetada
column285:
1/2 Grilled Chicken with Peri Peri Fries and Coleslaw. The Espetada was the most recommended among all but i felt a complete lack in taste on the chicken. The grilled chicken was well balanced with the spice and texture. The Sides were pretty good to say which would definitely balance the taste if the heat is getting to you.

We were offered a Chocolate Brownie with Ice Cream as a complimentary dish. The dessert was good with brownie being very well made.

column309: 'RATED\n  We had fame grilled half chicken
column310:
o Porto rice with mushrooms and boneless chicken Breast . Everything was tasty . However the rice which we choose as mildly spicy was terribly spicy . So be aware . This restaurant is just like Nando?s as an concept with similar type of accompaniments . Good place to have dinner after a movie . Definitely good for chicken lovers . Veg choices are very limited.

Food :4/5
Service:4/5
Ambience:3/5
Overall: 3.5/5')
column312: 'RATED\n  If you are a foodie and love to try new stuff
column313: this ones a must go! The taste pallets of African cuisines generally is something else!\nNow coming to Galito?s
column314: I would recommend it with my eyes shut!\nWe went there for lunch post a movie. The interiors are very welcoming. We decided to eat the ?hanging kebabs? Equally good. nice subtle flavors...definitely yes for a revisit! Keep up the amazing work team!')

column3: 16th Main, BTM, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Good food , good pricing, what else can u ask for, the chicken lollipop is really good, combine that with Prawn fried rice and u have a winning combination, noodles can be better, however the starters are really tasty and equally spicy, however would recommend u guys to eat like four to five times a month not more, u mite end up getting bored..the place is small but pretty good..'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Had ordered veg steamed momos bcoz It is craming across restaurant listing. Packaging was well packed with chutney.

Taste- 5/5
Service- 4/5
Packing -5/5'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Was craving momos and came across this restaurant listing. Ordered veg steamed momos, they were packed well with mayo and chutney.
Taste - 5/5
Packaging - 5/5'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  A very small place in BTM for authentic Chinese food at pocket friendly prices...when in doubt and in BTM jus go here...if there's no place to sit..jus parcel the food ?"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Ordered from this place for dinner. The delivery was on time and packaging was decent. We ordered chicken lollipop (chicken was a bit fragile since there wasnt much meat on sticks but it was good) and chicken triple schezwan rice (good). Also the prices r quite reasonable. Overall:
Food - 4/5
Delivery - 4/5
Packaging - 3/5
Vfm - 4/5'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  CK Mega Food is a typical IndoChinese street styled outlet. Located close to Udupi Garden in BTM. The place is divided across 2 shops- one being the kitchen and the other for customers to sit.

The menu has a variety of soups, rice, noodles and so on. Have been or ordered from this place more than 10times. Love their Chilli Garlic Noodles, probably one of the best. The place gets a little smoky due to the cooking process at high heat. The Butter Garlic noodles are decent too minus the chilies. We also tried their Veg Fried Rice, Gobi Manchurian and Manchow Soup.

The only issue being that the food quality and taste are not consistent.

rohitdassani.com')]

column3: 3rd Floor, Royal Meenakshi Mall, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column12: Mango Lassi, Dhokla, Khichda, Kesaria Lassi, Rajdhani Thali, Rabri, Buttermilk
column14:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Busy restaurant with decent marwadi food, the food was just average but the desserts were really good. Service is fast as expected. Butter milk was little stale I believe.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Been here for dinner on Sunday.

Food : 4/5 - As always the food served in rajdhani was delicious and good in quantity. If you want to eat like a king come here.

Ambiance: 3/5 - compared with other rajdhani outlets the ambience was not that good. The seating space though was good.

Service: 4/5 - good service overall.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  The rating is only for food and service because the ambience is very plain Jane and I think that applies to this chain.
Rajasthani food was mostly authentic and tasty. Service was quick as well.
You can surely visit especially if you are hungry,and that's when it is just vfm."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  We went for full family dinner ?. Nice place with simple and cosy environment . Thali has lots of variety and most of the items were tasty.
Food - 4/5
Ambience - 4/5
Service - 4/5'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A royal western Indian vegetarian Thali, especially on days other than Tuesday. It usually becomes a bit heavy for me, the taste is something to look out for! Have been there multiple times and was never disappointed!'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  It is not that great!

if you want to try this place , i would suggest to visit on Tuesdays as you will get around 50% discount. But it will be crowded on Tuesdays and you may have to wait for 15 to 20  minutes.

They serve rajasthani thali. it includes buttermilk/jaljeera, dal baati churma, tikki/dhokala, 3 curries, dal, sweets,rice/khichadi .

Everyday menu will be different( curries, sweets will be different. Other things will be almost same).

it is always better to check the menu before visiting this place.


I have tried home delivery option as well. I ordered methi thepala which was too salty and hard.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Rajdhani Thali is a very famous and renowned chain that opened a few years ago. They've definitely stayed up to the mark and have not let their quality of food or service down. I've been to multiple branches and this time, as its a family favourite, we decided to order from here.
We had the royal thali and also, a rajasthani paratha with gatte ke sabji and boondhi raita. Food was delicious, great packing and amazing quality! However a little too spicy for our liking. The thali had phulkas, a farsan, 2 subzis, 1 dal, jeera rice, a papad and a dessert. Definitely ordering again!"), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Heard a lot about rajdhani but never got a chance to try before
Was in meenakshi mall and came across this branch thought of trying out
But experience was quite disappointing
I appreciate the varieties they provide but nothing was tasty not sure if it was because we went there at late night before closing time
But it didn't meet our expectation expectation!
The only thing I liked in the Thali was daal Baati
Rest all the items were tasteless"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Typical rajhdhani dishes served in traditional utensils. The varities of food is good. The taste is good. The dalbhati churma, jelebi, malpua, dhoka etc all were yummy. You can eat as much as you want. Really nice place...')]

column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Their shawarma is the best. Havent really tried any other dishes of theirs yet. Quantity is pretty less compared to the prices. An average place.'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  It?s a small place in btm.. very average food and hospitality.. we had spring rolls, dragon rolls and so called sangria which tasted really bad.. you can avoid the place if you are in btm.'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  They mismatched the veg and nonveg items.this kind of behavior is not acceptable.on contacting zomato they said apologies and they hope to serve better next time.
Food review:paneer was sour,the flat noodle wasnt upto mark.chicken was okay.watons sucked big time.
Highly dissapointed from this restaurant.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Was surfing for a working lunch and something within my budget and something Chinese

Found this on the Zomato app for order in only
Yummy fried rice with generous amount of chicken Manchurian and a caramel shake to wash it down

The quantity large
Quality good
Packing very neat
Total paisa vasooli'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Ordered through online, placed order for Chicken Fried rice and Noodles. Packaging was OK with cutleries
Bit disappointed with the fried rice as bit tasteless with less salt. Having half boiled omelet on top of the food separately didn't go well with the overall taste as traditionally had fried rice mixed with rice.

Coming to noodles overall the taste is good could have been better with the scrambled eggs rather than small half boiled omelette. Could have had bit lesser oil"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Ordered chili rice with chicken and got a complimentary salad! The service is good, food is great for the price. The quantity is also quite filling! Totally recommended. Also, they have BOGO offers when you order online.')]
