column14:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Satisfied with the awesome taste, good quality and quantity, but when they deliver it's better if they check the packed the food properly or not.."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  One dish that I can eat a lot of times without ever getting bored by it has to be biryani.
I have tried biryani in bangalore in so many places and my recent find was biryani miya.
I stay in JP Nagar and usually I go to kormangala or indiranagar but that day I really wasn't interested to travel.
The food came on time.
It was hot and I thoroughly enjoyed the taste."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I am a big Biriyani lover, i can even eat biriyani in all three course of meal.

On opening the lid, the aroma that wafted out was stupendous. The biryani itself had quite a nice colour combination and the taste was marvelous...Highly recommended to all!'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Deceitful and disappointing.
(Delivery only review)
Almost all other reviews here are deceitful/fake/paid, look at their dine-lines and all of them have mysteriously reviewed same places with ratings only 4 and above. Hope Zomato takes note of this.

Pros:
1. The quality of ingredients is above average.
2. Biryani accompaniments are noteworthy and tasty.

Cons:
1. The Zomato images to the actually biryani are worlds apart! Please refer to my uploads.
2. The high price no where justifies a 4 cp tray packaging, which usualy is for executive service only.
Biryanis as this price point are supposed to be more worthy than quick meals.
3. It is absolutely not hyderabadi or any other know styles of biryani, tastes more close to masala/fried rice.
4. Quantity wasn't sufficient either.

Overall, other than fresh veggies in raita and taste of salan/gravy served with biryani, everything else is avoidable and disappointing."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This is not a let down place at all.I am so glad that JP Nagar is getting so many new places!I love it...Delivery was a little delayed but the food made up for it.
Biryani is soul food and I thoroughly enjoyed my food...
Recommended!!!')]

column12: Egg Chilli, Chilli Babycorn, Chicken Curry, Sweet Lassi, Palak Paneer, Chaach, Butter Chicken
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  One of my favourite place to have North Indian cuisine. The ambience is Dhaba inspired and the staff are very warm and welcoming.

We ordered Tandoori Kebab for starter and it was lip smacking. If you are someone who can handle spice then I would suggest you to try the ? Chicken Anagara? gravy. The Lassi complements all the dishes on the menu.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  The best best punjabi food I had in a while. Their food is so rich. I went twice in just a span of three days. Really love their Lassi & Hariyali kebab was spicy and heavenly..
One Suggestion is - the staff seem to be eager to finish off each table quickly which makes the customers either feel rushed or watched/conscious.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A proper Punjabi dhaba. If you like spicy food, then you can try out the angara chicken. Taste of food is great. Staff are courteous. And prices are also reasonable. North Indian people would love the place.'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  I understand it's a place intended to give you a dhaba feel, but cockroaches running around on floor and water jugs - is a strict No-No for me!I visited this place twice - twice only because it has good ratings here, but you will not believe it, I had to deal with cockroaches both the times - 2nd time on the water jug! It's utterly disgusting and unhygienic! Also, the food wasn't great - we ordered one of the starters from "Today's special" menu but the masala on the chicken was rawThe missi roti was as hard as rubber-papad and wasn't edible and the manager educated us about missi roti and even refused to replace it
Comeon, we havent come here to eat missi roti for the first time!Egg dishes were decent, Lassi was great but given my other negative experiences, may not visit this place again

Food - 3/5Ambience - 1/5Price - 1/5'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Its a really muat try place if you care fpr the flavours in food. Obviously this place is a little costly but when you have the food you wont bother about he price as it is so flavourful and the quantity is also good.
I would surely suggest you to atleast try it out for once.
And make sure you have lassi and gulab jamun here because according to me thats the best you can have here and nowhere else.'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  One of the worst dinners that I had

Ordered paneer butter masala and butter nan for dinner from Zomato after seeing there good ratings and it was a disaster.

Paneer butter masala was bland and had no taste. Nan were stretchy and not edible. There prices are at par with some fine dine restaurant in Bangalore. Please save your money and time and Order/ eat out from somewhere else.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Went to Chulha chauki da dhaba for lunch with colleagues. Finding a place was not difficult. We ordered baby corn chilli, Dal tadka, Dal makhni, paneer lababdar , garlic butter naan and butter naan. The food was really nice and the lassi was too creamy. Loved the place and will definitely love to visit again'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  One of the best places for those who crave for punjabi food. The ambience of the place is wonderful ! The food is really flavoursome. The lassi is great! The biryani and all the starters are amazing ! Worth the money too! Must visit place!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Sunday night and this place is crowded choc-a-bloc !! Got a place after cool 40 minutes of waiting !! Ordered gobi Manchurian, tandoori chicken, diwani handi , chicken lagori and malai kofta. The service was decent although cant say the same for all the food items. Lets list them out one by one
- The malai kofta was too sweet
- the Lahori chicken was just outright chewy
- the kulcha was chewy aa well
- the chass was good and spicy
- the tandoori chicken was grilled well'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Restaurant with a touch of Dhaba!!
General conception of Dhaba is that , they are generally located on a Highway.
But this dhaba is located in the heart of the city .

The dhaba is very small and can accomodate around 40-50 people, but the Food is awesome.(just awesome)
Since i am a Vegetarian i can comment only on Veg Food, and the Veg Food is toooo good.

I have also heard my friends saying that the Non Veg food too is very good.

Must try is the Sweet Lassi which is one of the best lassi i have had till now.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Good authentic food though not exact Punjabi taste but almost like it. We ordered lemon chicken in starters, ghee fulka, chicken tikka masala and lassi. The quantity and quality of the food provided is good. The service was prompt not much waiting time. The seating arrangement will give a dhabba feeling. Lanterns at the top, jhoot chairs and tables.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Chaula Chowki dhaba is another of those pocket-friendly Punjabi Dhabas. With a relatively simple decor, the place offers a highway Dhaba feel.

The food is decent, but is still far from the authentic 'Punjabi' taste.

Even though the prices are reasonable, the place still seems costly for the kind of food offered.

On a postive side, the service is exceptionally good and fast!"), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Ordered from this place on a weekend afternoon. The delivery was on time. Packaging was ok. We ordered Chicken tikka masala (good but a little too much garlic), Butter naan (ok), Daal tadka (not that great, the tadka didn't have any taste. It almost tasted like plain Daal), Gulab jamun (ok, a little hard on the inside and too sugary). The prices are ok when compared to quality. Overall:
Food - 3/5
Delivery - 4/5
Packaging - 3/5
Vfm - 3/5"), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  It's typical Punjabi restaurant!!!!?

One should not miss this restaurant one who want to taste different types of recipe in Chicken and roti with their sides!! ?

Seating someone feel uncomfortable but Ambience is very good with the delicious food!! ?

We ordered Chicken Manchurian, Chicken tikka and Lassi with main course each and every food have their own taste which we felt good to have!! ?

Due to dim light unable to click pics and I forgot to click by flash!! ?

#Mustvisit?"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Good place to have Punjabi food in a city like Bangalore. Though I have tried better options but this place gives you satisfaction in the end. Their kullad lassi is a must try. On weekends there is long waiting so be prepared.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Though the place has been around for many years never gave it thought until the last weekend when we were here for dinner. Cozy interiors, great food and good service. Definitely a gem in this locality. We ordered mostly veg food and I would have to admit the food is quite yummy. Best part is that they serve phulkas and without any fuss. I am going to visit again to tryout the menu.
Recommended for great North Indian fare'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  About Place:

The Place serves both Veg and Non-Veg Food, the ambiance is similar to dhaba (as the name suggests). But well maintained, service is fast. Expect place to be Crowded and there is no table reservation system.

About Food:

Food was tasty, and pocket friendly ordered Tandoori Rotis, Butter Paneer Masala, Dal Tadka, Masala Papad and few more items.

And Lassi is a must have, at this place.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED

column3: 6 Ground Floor, RR Commercial Complex, AkshayNagar, DLF New Town, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Ghee Podi Dosa and Irani Chai make for a perfect evening snack, while the upma pesarattu and Podi idli are sufficient for a meal!
Overall great food and a friendly, polite host. Must visit if in this side of town!:)'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Ordered for the first time from Hotel Brundavan yesterday for dinner. Schezwan Noodles was tasty, very much like home made. Roti was good and surprised to see palak dal as a side dish. Brundavan special dosa was very nice and heavy too, loved the ginger chutney and coconut chutney. Sambhar was not that fresh, so jus ignored it and disposed too. Along with all these items i ordered Paneer Chilly as a starter which was quite a disappointed one. Paneer pieces were so hard and wasn't fresh. I really couldn't enjoy starter as it could have been better. Overall, i will rate order as 3 out of 5. It was nice on the whole.")]

column3: 4, MICO Layout, 2nd Stage, Arekere, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  I honestly didn't like the food one bit.
The pulav was very basic. It lacked taste.
The rice was also a little dry. The meat pieces in the pulav were drier.
The kebab was good though. It was tasty and juicy.
The service is good. They actually listen to you.
Overall, average food and an okish experience."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  An absolute feast at this price, Mutton biryani and Guntur chicken for rs 180
The serving of mutton could be more generous but still yeah it was properly cooked and very delicious,the rice tasted like heaven
The Guntur chicken was really spicy and ofcourse delicious'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  The review is based on home delivery hence only on the food

The pulav was amazing and tastes very different from all the biryanis/pulavs that I have tried. The prawns fry was way better than expected although its a little specier than normal

Prices are definitely reasonable')]

column3: 128/54/10, Ground Floor, Opposite IIM - B, above A2B Dasarapalya, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column12: English Breakfast, Sandwiches
column14:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  We ordered for Egg Masala Omlette Combo, Taste is ok but not up to the mark, Bread quantity is very less ( 1 Small Slice of Bread ) they have to improve interms of Quantity & Taste.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Good to go place for healthy breakfast options. Its really economic and the ambience is good. Only thing strange about the place which i find is they dont keep water on table. You have to always keep asking for it.
English breakfast and the sandwiches are a good option here. I wont prefer you to buy any drinks here because i dont think thats worth it. And the dessert option are also good but you have to be carefull of what you choose only go for some pastries and nothing else from that.
According to me this place is only a good option for breakfast or some snacks.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Decent cafe at Bannerghatta main road, Bangaluru. Good for quick breakfast. Opens at 8am which is a good point. I tried strawberry smoothie, chicken club sandwich and mixed sauce chicken pasta here. Pasta was very spicy but well made. Disappointed very much with the so called chicken club sandwich and a little disappointed with the strawberry Berry smoothie. The chicken sandwich was very desi.. They should not name it club sandwich. The strawberry smoothie was okay but again it was not exactly like a smoothie. It was more od strawberry ice-cream blended and hurrah we have a strawberry shake ???? I was disappointed so didn't so forgot to click the club sandwich. Then I realised I look so pretty and here you beautiful pictures of me eating breakfast. #MinistryofGourmet #gurgaonfoodie #breakfastdone #shiulichakravorty #reviewoftheday #foodiesofinstagram

shiulichakravorty.com"), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Best place for breakfast. You will love the English breakfast but don't dare to drink cold coffee, it's disgusting. Sandwiches are good to try."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Nice ambience great service and nice milkshakes
And a hot well presented coffee
Recommended
Not crowded as expected as per the rating
Competetive Pricing'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This newly opened Restro - Cafe is an amazing hangout place. This was formerly Cafe Fattoush. The place has a good variety of English breakfast. I tried the Spicy Chicken Burger. The food can be 3.5 /5. Ambience can be 4. Do catch up at this place.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Amazing food ?...... loved their freakshakes ? and burger ? ........, will certainly visit again...pizzas and pastas ? are also good ...... staff is friendly and they also do home ? delivery ?')]

  This vibrant place is located to the left whilst commuting to BTM signal crossroads just after Jayadeva Flyover. Since I commute this stretch of the road rather quite frequently, I cannot help but have a pitstop at Magix's Parattha Roll. Quick service and affordable pricing make this place a favourite amongst youngsters, singles and couples who wish to give a miss to cooking at home yet don't want to burn a hole in their pocket once in a while. Most of Magix's rolls are an instant hit and people tend to become regular customers. Grilled Chicken, Rolls, Chicken Alfahamh, Kebabs are a must try here. Starters, Chinese and Biryanis are quite popular too. When you want a quick bite on the fly, be sure to stop by Magix's. You are sure to fall in love with their food.

  Two weeks back, we ordered Home-Delivery & we were quite satisfied with their food. This was the first time that we tried anything apart from their rolls. Their Chicken Rolls are excellent.

We were 5 people so we ordered 2 Starters & 4 Chicken Biryanis. Both, Chilly Chicken Dry & Tandoori Chicken Kabab were were tasty. Biryanis were good but kind of homely when compared to Nagarjuna/ Nandhini/Meghana. Biryani Rice used was good.; accompaniments of Biryani (curry & raita) were good too. One could enjoy the tasty curry with plain rice too, it indeed was very yummy. Chicken pieces in Biryani were small in size so at one point it felt like some more rice could have been better. 3 portions were good enough but the 4th one was welcomed, too :)

Overall, a must try if u do not like overly-spicy Chicken Biryani.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I have been having paratha rolls here since 12 years. My favorite is the double egg chicken roll. It has a juicy taste to it. Extremely soft parathas make it better. Must try.'), ('Rated 3.5', 'RATED
  A decent small joint to have rolls kabab n chinese under 1 roof at comparatively reasonble price. Had noodles n paneer manchurian, both were equally good and spicy. The softness of paneer had left me really amazed, will definitely visit next time to try something different.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED

column33:
""RATED
  The worst of all.
Staff -1/5
Food 1/5
I don't know why they use same gravy for all their food
No matters what u order it will taste like same
Even chicken n paneer gravy also same
Last day I was there and paneer gravy has too much salt in it.
I ask for replacement but staff gave me same with more salt added
When I went to manager and tell him the story..
He order his staff something in local language... And third time when I got my paneer anyone can see that water was added to that paneer even the water was not mixed properly.
If I had a negative rating option I would have given that one but unfortunately it isn't ..."")

column214: oh yeah - I'll surely be back for more

column336:
'RATED
  Magix is our saviour when our cook decides to take a day off. It is located on the main road just between BTM Water Tank Bus stop and Jayadeva Flyover. They have non-ac seating area. I still remember they used to be just a normal take away counter and its great to see them doing good.
The prices are absolutely amazing. 10 Pc chilli/manchurian chicken dishes are just Rs.110/-
Gravy items like Butter Chicken is Rs.120/- (Small diced pieces and very tasty)
Full Tandoori for Rs.240 :):) And I must say the tandoori chicken is quite good and juicy.
Never tried vegetarian there. Chinese noodles can be avoided.

Ambience 2.5/5
Cost 4.5/5
Quality 3.5/5
Quantity 3.5/5

OVERALL 3.5/5')

column393: ""RATED\n  Been eating here since my college days and since they were a roadside stall. Years later they still have one of the best rolls! Delicious and generous quantity compared to other places. Their Biryani is average but their kebabs are good. Self-service place. Clean and quick service. If you're in BTM and looking for a quick roll this is the place to go to. Even after opening the restaurant
column394: they still have maintained the taste and quality. Highly recommended!"")]"

column3: 24, Shop 1, Ground Floor, 3rd Cross, 18th Main Road, 2nd Stage, BTM, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Good Ambience, pretty little place in BTM.. Pocket friendly pricing but great taste.

Sandwiches are awesome

- Chicken Club Sandwich - It was filling,yummy and made with fresh ingredients.
- Egg Club Sandwich - Really good tasting, make you want to order more.
- Bread Omelette- One 9f the best bread omelettes you will ever have.
The secret of their sandwiches ate their house special freshly made cream cheese. Really tasty food.

Only thing i wasn't so fond of - Cheese Tea, turned out it's not my cup of tea(pun intended). Its kind of an acquired taste.

They also serve fresh and cold pressed juices and cold coffees and milkshakes.

Must try once for their sandwiches.")]

  Keeping the name the Biryani in menu and using basmati rice and plenty of garam masala does not make a 3rd grade rice item, the Biryani. I have tasted all kinds of biryani,Bangladeshi to Hydrabadi,Awadhi biryani to Donne biryani and Afghaan double layer biryani to Ambur biryani. Biryani is an exotic dish where no spices can be seen however blend of all spices can be felt in mouth, no spices must be felt over other. The one I eat that is nothing but super hot 3rd grade south Indian rice with stinky lamb that?s given the name of mutton. I thing restaurant must go through some kind of test and earn license to earn the right to prepare this kind of exotic dishes.I didn?t have anything less than 1 grade,this actually below 0.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

column14:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  There was a time, when this place was only a stone's throw away and we were probably the most frequent customers. When they just started operations, their Biryani portions were huge and they served chicken biryani with a large sized chicken raan - excellent but inconvenient to share. 

We were big fans of the biryanis (both mutton and chicken) and the salan and even bigger fans of the chicken 65. The kebabs were a good bet as well. Even to this day, there's days when we brave Silkboard traffic just because the taste buds cannot be satiated with any of the alternatives. I do hope they maintain their standards and keep the taste true."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I had been craving for some good Andhra Biryani and luckily came across this place called Birinz in BTM over last weekend. In case you haven?t had a typical Andhra Biryani before, I highly recommend you to try it out. Birinz is a very simple restaurant with basic seating that serves mouth-watering food. Their menu had Chinese and Andhra assortment of grubs and we enjoyed every single food that we ordered. ...
Read full post on nibblesdiary.wordpress.com'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Paneer biryani and butter chicken biryani. @birinzblr was previously knows as bawarchi and serves varieties of biryani having both veg and non veg options. It's served in 2 portions I.e. personal and regular, so that the portion of food is not wasted.
You can either order or just visit the place to enjoy the biryani. ??"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I ordered a paneer biryani from there and it was good. The quantity of rice was enough for a person. They also gave raita and onion with it. I liked it!!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  People ditch, but Biryani never ditches........
ell, this stands true for "Birinz", a recently opened paradise for Biryani lovers in BMT, Bangalore. 
Guys if you're travelling to Bangalore anytime soon, this is surely your one stop for lunch/dinner. 
I've tried the "Reddy's Chicken Biryani"& "Butter Chicken Biryani"which are lip smacking & unique in their taste with generous amounts of flavour to it. 
Their "Rayalseema Chicken Dry"was a stunner dish!!    A chicken dish with just the right proportions of flavor.....
All the biryani lovers pick up pace, and get ready to tickle your taste buds......
A must try restaurant with humble service.......'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Birinz as the name suggests is a place for biriyani.. they serve different varieties of biriyani. The starters here are decent too. The best of the lot I tried was the butter chicken biriyani and the chicken dum biriyani. I loved their gin powder rice too.
For vegetarians they have good options too. I loved the mushroom chilli garlic, paneer sholay. Golden baby corn was okay.
Ambience is okay. Service is quick.

cupcakesontravel.blogspot.com')]

column3: Doddakamanahalli Main Road, Kalena Agrahara, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Just got two shawarmas delivered. In last ten years together I haven't had that much of onion, what I had just now. 49 rupees for a shawarma sounds like a steal deal, and you hope that no food joint wants a bad name. But this one does. Chicken was there, one table spoon each in two rolls. WHY SO MUCH OF ONION?"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  We ordered whole meat shawarma, classic shawarma and chicken tikka. Both the shawarmas were one of the best I have had till date. The only thing missing was pickle and green chilly we normally get with it at other joints.

Chicken tikka were perfectly cooked, juicy, tasty. Accompanied with yummy chatni. Just that I found it very salty. I would like to give it a benefit of doubt and hope next time you guys will take care of the salt content.

Would definitely order again.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Great friendly place for shawarma, owner is very polite, small n neat place definitely recommended, must try sharwarma and tandoori chicken.')]

column3: #12, 12th Cross BDG Residency, Puttenahalli
column12: Samosa, Chicken Chettinad, Murgh Makhani
column13: Street Food, Fast Food, Rolls, Desserts
column14:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  This delivery only food outlet has an interesting take on our beloved evening snack, samosa!
You think of samosa and the second thing that comes to your mind (after the delicious taste) is the unhealthy oil!! Samosa Singh certainly addresses this issue as their samosas seem to absorb less oil and they look hygienic.

Now coming to the taste. I have tried many flavors. Masala corn, kadai paneer, paneer tikka and veggie spice. I must say they were all pretty decent. Nothing extraordinary but palatable. The stuffing though was very less and that was a let down!

I absolutely loved their dessert samosas. Full marks for the creativity and taste. I tried chocosa zesty orange and chocosa crunchy peanut. Zesty orange is my favourite.

Overall a decent place to satiate your evening hunger pangs.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  So I tried out the paneer tikka samosa from this outlet.. First of all finding this place is difficult as there is no board and only a small sign announcing their name.. The filling was tasty but definitely not tikka.. The reason i have given only 3 stars is because it was more like a stuffed kachori than samosa.. Flaky n thick crusted..
Should try out the other outlets too..'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Samosa Singh is King, order veg samosa platter and samosa desserts, nicely branded and packed, samosas are super tasty. Real value for money.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Try this place for their unique samosas..I have tried their masala corn, murgh makhani, chicken chettinad and chocossa caramel samosa..?

The filling is tasty but I felt that the size of the samosa was comparatively small.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  I?d have rated these guys 4 stars but for their choco samosas. They were just reshaped perk.
Now, coming to the real deal, I totally adored their chettinaadu chicken samosas. Just the right balance between potato and chicken, a crunchy shell and excellent packaging makes this a good deal. Imma try all their other items, and perhaps you should too.')]

column3: Shop 11& 12, First Floor, 3618/1, Dodda Kammanahalli, Main Road, Besides Campus Student Communities Building, Bangalore

column14: [('Rated 4.0', 'RATED\n \nNice eat out place for Punjabi Pure veg food, I tried Amritsari Chole Kulche and it was awesome. It was pocket friendly as well. I would definitely revisit this place.')]

column3: Kitchens@, No. 19, 35/4, 24th Main, JP Nagar 7th Phase, Puttenahalli, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  Had visited zomato kitchens this weekend. Ordered a hyderabadi chicken biryani and chicken 65. Their idea of a biryani is to cook it a while back and dump oil into it to make it appear fresh.Strangely there were 3 bits of stale chiken on it as a crowning glory.It is definitely the worst experience that I have had with zomato so far.'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  This is my first review for any restaurant I ordered till date.worst experience that I ordered a Hyderabadi chicken full curry and I literally got 2 small piece of chicken with gravy.
As soon as I saw the parcel I thought it was dal curry, when I tasted it I'm not at all wrong. I didn't felt like I'm eating chicken at all.
I'm surprised that we can even make chicken curry like this?
Better I could have ordered daal curry and saved some money.
Management pls change the quantity,taste, packing to an minimum standard level.
Worst experience ever."), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  I have ordered hyderabad egg biriyani today and I can say that this is the worst food I had.. I would never suggest this restaurant again to anyone..'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  I purchased chicken 65 andhra it was very sour and lot of coconut, and dint like it and prawns masala don't try this I thought it's a dry and I was surprised to receive a curry I was very upset roti and biryani is good last time I tried it, but very upset with my today's order."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  good food.. loved prawn roast.. one star less for promotional messages and late delivery'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  I ordered Andhra 65 and Nellore Chicken Biryani
Absolutely the worst of the worst biryani's I've tasted in Bangalore. For being a great dedicated lover of Andhra food is was completely Disappointed"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Being honest this is the best Briyani hub in bangalore i order through zomato delivery i got my delivery in 23 minutes and kababs are to die for.i ordered one tikka hyderabadi briyani and Andhra chicken 65.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Very happy to seen Nagas in JP Nagar awesome biryani they have and Andhra starter are really good I had in Park square mall in Itpl enjoyed lots')]

column3: 6185/ 15/1, SOS, Doddakamanahalli, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column12: Biryani
column14:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Very innovative of them to serve Biryani in matkas. The quantity is massive but the quality is disappointing. They use generous portions of spices but it overpowers the biryani. I cannot taste anything more. The matka I could keep so thanks for that!
Overall, average food and a good experience.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  After having the food thought to share my experience, the food was really awesome, very reasonable price, sufficient quantity, well packed. Definitely try again.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Ordered chicken dum biryani.Like the concept of Biryani in Matka.Thanks for the matka.Really loved it.About the food,biryani was good but not great.Spices were dominating and it was hard for me to feel the taste.There were two decent sized perfectly cooked chicken pieces.Hope they work on masala flavor which dominates and suppresses the taste of the biryani.Quantity is excellent.If you like spicy masaledar biryani or hyderabadi kind biryani ,Matka is your place.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Food is really good. The preparation and presentation were both up to the mark. A must go in this area .
Biryani was the best. Service is also nice.')]

column3: 950, 16th Main Road, 2nd Stage, BTM, Bangalore
column12: Lassi, Murgh Lababdar, Makke Ki Roti, Chaap, Butter Paneer, Butter Chicken, Patiala Paneer
column14:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  A cool Dhaba style ambience. We opted for some special dishes so the price is a bit higher. apart from that food quality was good , quantity is also good.. We have chicken nun parathas, some special dishes lassi.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Awesome and unique ambience in the heart of Btm. Loved the chicken lababdar. The ambience gives u a feeling of real pujabi dhaba in Bangalore.'), ('Rated 2.0', "RATED
  One of the new reasturants in BTM, ambience is pretty simple , food is like any other Punjabi reasturants, veg dishes are between good and very good, non veg dishes can be better, price wise it's ok, staff is ok.. nothing much to write home about, typical Punjabi reasturant....there are no special dishes that u will certainly come back for ..."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Went there for the second time last night, and it wasn't a bad experience but what I did not like at this place was the poor behavior of the staff.
Tried their Paneer Khazana and lassi and chapatis.
Food was decent, but the outlet should be a little cleaner and hygienic.
Plates were dirty too.

pleased my taste buds? - yes.
burnt a hole my pocket? - not really.
had a punjabi vibe? - yes.
was the staff courteous? - could've been better."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Punjabi Swag is a North Indian dhaba style place that offers very good Punjabi food items. The ambience is truly of a dhaba and also the music played there is very lively. I have tried a number of items but their Butter Chicken definitely stands out. It is awesome and a must-try item. Masala Papas, Garlic Naan, and Cuole Kulche are also tasty. Service is slow and needs to be improved. They keep the restaurant open till late in the night so it's a good choice for the late night cravings."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Today I visited panjabi swag. Place was so amazing, full of panjabi flavours, spices. And that aroma of ingredients was mind blowing. Hat's off to chef because he knows how to put spices perfectly aand how to balance dish. That creaminess, spiciness of chaap was outstanding. Sarso ka saag was perfectly balanced and full of flavours and when you will take a bite of sarso ka saag with makke ki rooti you will feel like you are in panjab. And I had best dalmakhni of my life. And about my favourite part dessert, Without dessert there is nothing in life and that gajar ka halwa was literally too good. Nice ambiance you will feel like you are in panjab. Great hospitality!!! At last if food will put a smile on your face that food deserves more than 10 rating. Thank you panjabi swag you guys made my day!!!!"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Found a great outlet to have some great North Indian Punjabi style food. Menu is short and concise but they have done a great job in making food delicious. Sarson ka saag and makke ki roti made my day along with paneer tikka as a starter. Staff was great, friendly and service was really fast.'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  I ordered Malai Chaap and some Paneer dish from this restaurant few days ago. It was ok in taste. So we thought to try the Chaap again with Chicken Tikka as this is a punjabi again.
Then after ordering from here via Swiggy, my concept of trying every Punjabi Restaurant in Bangalore, got changed.
I ordered Achaari Chaap and Chicken Tikka today. The achaari chaap was boiled and mixed with Achaar masala(from the achaar we found in Supermarket) and Chicken Tikka was not cooked well.
@Restaurant: If you want to check how to cook Chaap, then go to Gurgaon/Noida. You will definitely learn how to make Tandoori chaap/Malai Chaap/Masala Chaap/Hariyali Chaap/Achaari Chaap. Also visit Delhi in between to learn Chicken Tikka.
For Chicken Tikka, You can also visit Khan Saheb outlet in Jayanagar.
So its an advice: If you will cook better, then we will share your positive reviews otherwise will definitely share your bad reviews.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Ordered from this place on a week day afternoon. The delivery was prompt and packaging was ok. We ordered Chicken tikka masala (good), garlic naan (fine), and aloo pyaaz paratha (not good. Also there wasn't any pickle or chutney accompanying it). Prices are decent compared to the quality. Overall:
Food - 3/5
Delivery - 4/5
Packaging - 3/5
Vfm - 4/5"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Good Place to try Punjabi food in BTM ,Friendly staff very good service , food quantity is very good , i was surprised with the quantity of Paneer they give in the paneer dishes .
One to the good places in BTM to have pocket friendly dinner.
They also have soya chaap which you can try which i found okay as i earlier had in Baba Chatkora which was very good .

Try Paneer Dishes. (They had a special paneer also iguess the anme was Paneer Tada which is ot on menu , you can ask about this .It was very good)'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  A small restaurant with brilliant starters but mains are a let-down. Lassi is sufficiently thick to qualify it as an authentic Punjabi restaurant. No cream floating on the lassi though.

To get to this place, turn left (if arriving from silk board) when you reach Udupi Signal. Walk/drive past Akshay Grand and you'll reach a crossroad. Punjabi Swag is just after the crossroad. It is diagonally opposite the corner liquor store.

Seating consists of wicker chairs and low tables. It means you will scream in agony after a few minutes if you have a big bum (I have). Your only hope are the two normal tables located at the back.

Attentive staff."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  This is... By far... the best restaurant that I?ve been to ( in terms of the taste of food) in Bangalore.
It?s not a big restaurant and has a limited seating, but the kind of food they serve here is out of this world.
I?d give 11/10 to the food here.
The staff is also polite and courteous.
The food served here is authentic punjabi.
Everyone in Bangalore should try their butter chicken.
The chef also recommended their bestselling appetiser, Dhanno Chicken, to us which was again worth the money.
I?ve not had everything in the menu but I can assure that everything that you?d order here would be Value for Money.
Their ambience gives it a feel of a highway side Punjabi Dhaba. They play the best ever punjabi songs.
Must visit.
Can?t wait to visit again and explore their menu.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I love punjabi restaurants. Mostly because of their ambiance. Good music, friends and the perfect dinner is all you need. Don?t forge to try chicken patiala. It?s no on the menu but you can order separately'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Small place
great food
Must visit for those who love punjabi food
We ordered biryani and butter chicken
It was amazing
Do visit this place for wonderful punjabi food'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

  Here review related to veg / paneer / mashroom biryani.... Don't prefer here for biryani , these people not have proper skills in preparing biryani....... Biryani lovers don't try here... U guys definitely hate it.... the gravy they provide with biryani is no where fit for biryani"), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  It use to be good but now a days they are no making good food. i tried paneer recently it was awfully bad. please concentrate on your dishes...'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Found this place by accident.
Absolutely love the energy of the place and it's owner!
The ambience is fun and very Punjabi.
And you muuuuust try the malai chaap! It's amazing!
Love eating here!"), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Found this place by accident. Truly gives one the feel of punjab with their punjabi music and dhaba type of ambience. We ordered
1) Butter chicken- A must try dish loaded with butter. The staff is kind enough to let us know before ordering that it will be bit sweeter. We didn't mind that and we did not regret this decision. The yummiest butter chicken I tried lately.
2) Chicken Rara: this is semi gravy and not dry like it was mentioned. This was bit tangy and spicy with onion tomato base. Loved this too. However we wanted it to be more tangy hence added lemon juice to it ?
3) Tandoori Butter Roti: This was freshly made with quite generous amount of butter.
4) Lassi: Obviously.. How could we leave this place without punjabi lassi? Lassi was quite good but it proved to be too heavy for us.
Worth visiting this place. Dishes are slightly expensive. Not too light on the pocket. Seating is very limited. Staff is courteous and quick"), ('Rated 2.0', "RATED

  Here review related to veg / paneer / mashroom biryani.... Don't prefer here for biryani , these people not have proper skills in preparing biryani....... Biryani lovers don't try here... U guys definitely hate it.... the gravy they provide with biryani is no where fit for biryani"), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  It use to be good but now a days they are no making good food. i tried paneer recently it was awfully bad. please concentrate on your dishes...'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Found this place by accident.
Absolutely love the energy of the place and it's owner!
The ambience is fun and very Punjabi.
And you muuuuust try the malai chaap! It's amazing!
Love eating here!"), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Found this place by accident. Truly gives one the feel of punjab with their punjabi music and dhaba type of ambience. We ordered
1) Butter chicken- A must try dish loaded with butter. The staff is kind enough to let us know before ordering that it will be bit sweeter. We didn't mind that and we did not regret this decision. The yummiest butter chicken I tried lately.
2) Chicken Rara: this is semi gravy and not dry like it was mentioned. This was bit tangy and spicy with onion tomato base. Loved this too. However we wanted it to be more tangy hence added lemon juice to it ?
3) Tandoori Butter Roti: This was freshly made with quite generous amount of butter.
4) Lassi: Obviously.. How could we leave this place without punjabi lassi? Lassi was quite good but it proved to be too heavy for us.
Worth visiting this place. Dishes are slightly expensive. Not too light on the pocket. Seating is very limited. Staff is courteous and quick"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Went here for lunch and guys I must say the place is really cool. You will feel as if you are in North part of India, because of Punjabi songs, pictures, quotes. Food too tasted good and service was quick too.
Happy that they also have online delivery.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Ordered non-veg combo from here one fine afternoon from my office..it comprised of boneless biriyani, raitha, a gravy and salad..biriyani was soooo yum and the gravy was spicy..overall, I was satisfied with the meal..?')]

column3: Royal Meenakshi Mall, Third Floor, Hulimavu, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column12: Tacos, Fries, Nachos, Burrito
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  My all time favourite eatery.... yummmmmm is just not the word. I love the tacos, quesadilla, rice bowl...all of it ...IN VEG !
this time I was totally in love with the ambience too... it was us a too kool...please never miss an opportunity to experience the food and place at this location in specific. Kudos to the interiors!'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Ordered Burrito, Taco, Fries and a soda beverage. For some reason did not enjoy the Burrito or the Taco and also felt that, food at TacoBell - Gopalan Mall tastes way better than the food served here.'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  The food used to be so good here, now it's totally gone down. On our most recent visit, everything we ordered tasted stale, old stock and just inedible. Highly disappointed"), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  It's more of a restaurant than a self service joint. While you order on the counter, you get a token number and food is served by a server on your table.

Ambiance has more elegance to it than other branches, clean and spacious. Overall, lovely.

Coming to food, we've tried many, from Tacos (Naked chicken, Potaco, Paneer Tikka), Burritos (spicy sriracha and others), Quesadilla, loaded nachos and mexican fries. Food is fresh and delicious.

Service is good too. Staff is polite and professional.

Overall, a delightful experience. Keep up the good work!"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This place serves delicious tacos and super delicious nachos. We mostly order nachos from this place and it never disappoints. Great place to hangout ?'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Their Naked Chicken Tacos are amazing! Period. The Cheesy Nachos are not so cheesy but taste just fine. I would prefer their French Fries over any other fast food joints one any day. The ambiance is quite nice and the service is quick. They somehow always make sure that your glass is never empty. Love visiting this place over and over again.')]

  This is a very small outlet run by Muslims that serves authentic ambur style biriyani. There is a very small area to sit and eat so better to opt for takeaway. I also love their kababs (40 rs only for half plate) with around 5 small pieces but spicy and tasty. I go here AT LEAST once a week as I live nearby.')]

column14: [('Rated 5.0', 'RATED\n  This place literally brings the mom cooking to the plate and I just loved the food absolutely homely and in less oil, the place served delicious home sabzis, Dals and desserts too. Specifically would recommend their baingan bharta which is their speciality and is one of the best I have managed to find in Bangalore. It has correct spices and is complimented by the hot piping homely phulkas they serve along with it. Cheers!')]

column14:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Ordered in for a working lunch from here via the Zomato app
Found them on the under 99 section for meals
Got excited but sadly not happy
The quantity good packing good but taste no no
I have eaten Bengali food elsewhere hence do know the difference from good Bong food and not so great Bong food
The Bengali fish thali had
Fish curry with a piece of fish was tasteless
Dal watery and tasteless again and very bland
Fried onions
Lots of rice and
A tomoto chutney gone totally wrong
Please do look into your Tate issues'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Updated: The owner called and apologized and even after refusing because of the late night. He came to give the correct order.

Great customer service!

*******************

AVOID.

Bad food.
Bad quantity.
Bad packaging.

And absolutely shameful Bengali food. Anyway, cheers! Never again

So Zomato wants me to write 140 characters, but I don't feel like wasting my time on this.")]

column12: Vada, Coffee, Masala Dosa, Gulab Jamun, Roti, Idli, Tomato Soup
column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This is located just opposite Bangalore Central mall, JP Nagar. This is totally vegetarian restaurant. The restaurant is spread on to two stored building. The ground floor section has no seating area, but the place is always very crowded than uper stored. The upper stored area has comfortable seating area with much high price. The food was good and they had very fast service. Must try their gobi Manchurian, masala dosa, veg noodles. And South Indian cuisine is incomplete without filter coffee. '), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Normal!

I?ve been here a couple of times. I?ve only tried their evening snacks. I?ve had Gobi Manchurian and Masala Puri. Gobi Manchurian was good, but the Masala puri was just passable.'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Very bad experience here! Staff here are extremely rude and made us wait for 45 minutes and didn't give us the table. The ambience wasn't great too and tables and cutlery were extremely dirty."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  This place is just opposite to Central mall in Jayanagar, Bangalore. They have self service facilities at ground floor. If you want to properly sit and dine in then first floor is for this purpose. They have amazing food whether it is south Indian or north Indian. Place has quite decent ambience. Polite staff. Badam halwa is a must try.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  opp to bangalore central mall jp nagar.this is a treat to all foodies out there. always crowded (for a good reason) this place offers the most cost to taste ratio. absolute satisfaction of decent meal. ambience is decent, purely for family (dates are not recommended) . delicious food , theres self service on ground floor nd service hall first floor. you get what you are shown in the menu. the food is adequate in quantity and served with a smile. underrated restaurant. if u go to the mall for some shopping or movies it is worth more to visit upahara darshini than to visit the food court. give this restaurant a chance and u will start to admire it.')]

column3: 127, 16/1, Venkateswappa Layout, Kembathalli, Near Canara Bank ATM, Gottigere Post, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Original and authentic bengali food restaurant . All the items had the aroma of typical Bengali spices . Paneer in white gravy can be the signature dish, although all the items were utterly delicious. Highly recommended .'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Authentic Bengali cuisines. Worth a try. Have been a frequent customer to this home kitchen. If you are expecting foods which are rich and full of masalas and oil, then you can look somewhere else as, the food prepared here is healthy and devoid of unnecessary spice and riches. Proper home made stuff.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  The wife got my hunger pangs running by reminding me of some of our favorite dishes .ordered through zomato and was delivered promptly at my place.
For people of eastern India u can blindly go ahead with this.
We had ordered chicken kosha,fish curry,alu posto,tomato chutney,cabbage fry and cabbage with fish head.
Every dish reminded me of eating at home and the beautiful cuisine which is core to eastern India.
I now can get home cooked food without having to travel from my home .'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Authentic Bengali food.Service is excellent.Behaviour of the owner is also appreciable.I am a regular customer here to take order.If you are fond of Bengali food must try.
Chicken Biriyani taste is also good no doubt.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Yesterday night I and my roommate were very hungry and were looking for some good food. I opened the Zomato app and after having a glance at Chandrima?s Kitchen?s menu card, ordered 2 Egg thali meals. The taste of the food was absolutely fantastic. Had a fantastic evening with the food. 5 out of 5 for everyting. A suggestion to add the authentic Bengali sweet Rasogulla in the meals. It will make the food complete ???'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I tried chanar dalna and dhokar dalna and I should say the food tastes really good. The food is delivered by resturant on time. The food was freshly cooked and packed nicely. I will love to order again. Must try for people who like authentic Bengali food.'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  If this is what Bengali food tastes like then you should change your profession. I ordered a chicken thali for lunch let me start with the chicken curry it was 4 pieces of boiled chicken pieces floating in a watery curry and the curry tasted and smelled like raw ginger garlic paste. There was no taste in the chicken pieces not even salt. The Dal was equally watery like tasteless yellow water. The so called Bhaja which was aalu bhaja was not fried enough and again was more like boiled. The only good thing was the tomato chutney which was very very less in quantity. Since I belong to that region of India I am well aware of authentic Bengali food and this was far far from it. Really disappointed and waste of money.'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  I ordered chilli chicken for home delivery and i got a call from restaurant instantly and i told them to make it dry with more onions. But to my surprise being a Bengali establishment i received a runny chilli chicken and taste was not at all good. Chicken pieces were small.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  One of the best Bengali Cuisine I have tasted here in Bangalore. Being a bong and a foodie it's a delight to be able to taste the wide variety of bengali dishes that are there on the menu. I'd surely recommend that you order and try out the delicacies. Doesn't matter if you are a bengali or not just go ahead and order, just don't miss out on the opportunity to treat your taste buds."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Chicken taste is good.. But porota was not properly fried.. Should be completely fried..'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  EXCELLENT SERVICE AND FOOD . ALSO THE FOOD IS DELIVERED IN TIME. ALL THE ITEMS ARE VERY TASTY AND NOT THAT MUCH SPICY. THE TASTE OF MOONG DAL WITH COCONUT AND PEAS WAS FANTASTIC'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Home like food out here in the outskirts of bangalore especially for a student like me is bliss...Would recommend very much if you are a foodie and bong'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Loved the food .'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED

Better stay away from this type of restaurant otherws you will end up with bad experience n worst food.'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  We had ordered 2 khidchi and 1 mutton dak bungalow. T9 be honest the worst food that I have ever eaten. They do not even know how to cook Bengali cuisine. The mutton dak bungalow was half cooked... the meat was so very hard... who cooks mutton dak bungalow with curry leaves and pepper balls? I can cook better than this. column14:

Taste 3.5/5'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Recently visited this place for lunch

less oily and spicy
pocket friendly rates
courteous staff
Add more items in the menu
good luck'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED

column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Very Tasty food. Just loved the way they prepared it. it was authentic Chinese. momos fried rice just perfect. dragon chicken was delicious.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Good food that scores high on quantity and taste. Try their combos, which are worth the money. Had ordered the chicken combo and it came perfectly packaged. So, they managed to fit in (but in good way) two varieties of chicken including tasty drums of heaven in semi-gravy form, two hot momos, and sauce. Read most of the reviews of this place and I agree with them. It is value for money although I would not recommend having often from this place as (with most places serving Chinese fare) they tend to go a little overboard with the unhealthy ingredients.
As for me, would like to visit this place sometime soon.

Taste: 3.5/5
Value for money: 4/5
Delivery: 3/5
Packaging: 4/5'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Felt like eating Chinese today and found this new restaurant in BTM while searching on Zomato.
Though I doubted to order ,it did not upset me .
We ordered the Veg Noodles combo and Peking Paneer.
I must say that this was a great deal at decent price. The quantity of food is more than enough for one person. Momos in the combo were huge and tasty. Baby corn was slight saltier than normal for me so could not eat all. Peking Veg was mouth watering .Paneer (in Peking paneer ) was fresh and soft . I would recommend this place for sure and try these things if you are looking for noodles/momo/Manchurian all in one :).
The packaging was nice , it was provided with chilly sauce and red sauce.
Overall a pleasant experience .

Nitesh C')]

  The ambience in the private cabins is really cozy and makes for great times. The food (especially the Guntur Chicken, which warranted a repeat!!!) was sensational. The pizza (we tried the chicken Alfredo) is thin crust and cheeseilicious. Zomato gold redemption was a breeze and the service by the friendly Mr. Bipul Sarkar was top notch.
I?m surprised with the quality of outlets in my humble nook of Bengaluru. May BLRbox live long and prosper.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  The place is actually really cool.. The concept of converting a box into something so innovative!

Very laid-back place, good music.. we went there just to grab some drinks. The device definitely needs to improve, there were just a few customers and it was difficult to get the attention of the staff. The alcohol is decently priced, no doubts. I had the kamikaze bomb which was priced at 220 on the menu, but I was charged 300. I do not understand why the menu was showing the accurate prices and why I was not informed that the prices were incorrect.

I had a portion of the dimsum shumai. It was an okay dish!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  Hey writing feedback after long time.. ? Bangalore box name sounds interesting even their looks too.. Super spacious made up of shipping containers looks classic.. I went their for my hubby's birthday.. As it was near to our place we opted that.

This is a great place one should visit. Until next time cheers."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  I think it's an above average place.

The good thing is the place is really big with dining on multiple floors, but music is not loud.
Staff is good."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Good pub to hang out. Its not a party place but ambiance is really good and music is not loud.
We had few shots and bbq chicken wings, brownie and fish in banana leaf. Food was really amazing. And, the service was amazing. Rajat went out of his way to make us feel comfortable. Kudos to him?'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Builds hope and surely drowns it all.
The ambience and name speaks volumes of how they hoped the restaurant to be ; but good food needs good chef. Ordered butter garlic prawns and mushroom teriyaki . Both were below average ( streetfood tastes better). Dint have the guts to go for the main course , so headed off to A2b ?.
The 2* is for the interior(remnants of a ship I guess) and a few courteous waiters.
Let. down.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  The restaurant is really nice. Ambience is really good. They have a concept of box cabins for sitting. They also have rooftop place which is good if you want to drink.
The food is really good. Their burgers are awesome. Their signature dish is Chocolate Spring roll. It is crispy outside and chocolatey inside.
Seperate chocolate sauce is given which you can put on top of these rolls.
Overall very good experience. Can recommend for Familly as well as young crowd.
They serve hot drinks.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Bangalore box is very near to my place. So me and my friend decided to visit this place on a weekday. This place is located near Vijaya Bank Layout.
This place is spread across three floors. Rustic ambience with recycled decor. You can find missiles, metal containers and they do have small cabin setup on 1st floor. In short, dining in a shipping container.
We ordered mushroom teriyaki and chicken roulette. Mushroom teriyaki was way too sweet. We were bit disappointed but chicken roulette came as a saviour. Apparently they didn't have Bira strong so we had to settle for Kingfisher and Tuborg. Will visit again!!"), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  The place looks eye catchy from the outside with a fancy outlook,However the ambience isn?t that great inside. It has 4 floors and we chose to sit in the last floor. The place kind of has a rustic theme but isn?t that very expressive

We ordered Guntur chicken, chicken wings and a couple of other starters. All seemed good. I particularly liked the Chicken Biriyani here. Pricing is a bit expensive compared to other places around this area.')]

  We have been there coincidentally, while searching for a please for quick snack while back from bannerghatta temple, we found this place @Gottigiri.
Simply love the verierty of fod they serve. There snacks are amazing and all they prepare is fresh, great ambience and coperative staff.

-  great ambience
- coperative staff
- reasanable costing
- great location
- kids and family friendly
- best place for Gujarati shacks
- breakfast destination
- From Samosa to Katchori to Dhokla to Fafra -- everything you will find here.

#mustTry #breakfastDestination #longMorningDrive #gujjuStyle #friendsAdda'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Visited this place today for breakfast.
Being a Gujarati myself, I am very particular about the Gujarati cuisine. But still as it is very rare to find one in Bangalore I had to try this new restaurant.
The food they serve is authentic Gujarati food! Every sweet is made in desi ghee, faffda jalebi was amazing and also the Vada pav had was very like from Gujarat with an great touch of red garlic chutney!
Overall the experience was very good and it actually serves authentic Gujarati food and actually will meet the expectations of every gujju in Bangalore atleast.
#Musttry')]

column12: Cheesy Pizza
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I order from here quite often. Initially it was not my favourite but now they have changed the base and I like it. This time I ordered their chicken keema and suasage pizza and it was mind blowing, The overall flavours ,cheese quantity and base was amazing.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Gone are the days where the only option for home delivery pizzas were pizza hut and dominos. With players like ovenstory giving tough competition to them, they are sure to lose a lot of business in near future. It's been a year and I have constantly been ordering pizzas from Ovenstory because
A. They are delicious
B. They are delivered hot and on time
C. They have a good menu
D. They are pocket friendly

This time I tried the Spanish Delight and loved this one too!! I have two more to try on their menu and soon will be ordering those as well ?"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

column3: 5th Cross Road, Dollar Layout, 3rd Phase, JP Nagar, Bangalore
column12: Pasta, Sandwiches
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  A small and a warm cafÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82ÃÂ© with lots of friendly vibes. Located near the delmia circle in JP Nagar is this newly opened Cafe with lots of potential. Yes, this is also pet friendly with a small section just for them!

You can get whole lot of interesting books here to read or probably bring your own book of choice and enjoy with your food.

Coming to the food, it was really good and they are always up for suggestions and feedback if it's not upto the mark.

Some of my favorites were the nostalgia drink which is a unique combination of complan, hot chocolate and cocoa. Then the square shaped pizza's which were cheesy and very affordable as well. The pasta and sandwiches were also really good which was really soothing.
All the bread is made in-house which is really soft and tasty.

I'm giving an extra star just for the amazing service and hospitality given by the owners here. Definitely a must visit for people residing nearby JP Nagar area."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Nice place which a pet friendly nook inside the cafe ... there is no place for the dogs to play or walk around ... we ordered for burger which was unique but tasted ok and burji pav ... may or may not visit the cafe again ... they also have books if you wanna read ...'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Had a really great time at Slate Cafe, new outlet in JP Nagar. Aesthetic and very comforting ambience, The food was delicious and the staff was very hospitable, had a very positive experience in a long time, also it is pet friendly. Until next time, cheers! :)')]

column3: 2, Akshay Nagar, Near DLF New Town, Begur Main Road, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  A decent and economic place. Sattu kachori and puri are a go to option in breakfast here.
If you are looking for meals for lunch or dinner. This place has it all type of meals for your hunger.
They have some good parathas here. The stuffing in parathas are good in quantity. And really tasty.

Litti chokha here is decent enough and really flavourfull.

I wont suggest you to order starters here as they are not so great here you can try it somwwhere else. But for other suggested options above this place is good'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  It's best for quick snacking.. breakfast and dinner. Basically I go there for paratha. And on the road and can easily be noticed.
Small place n quite hygiene.")]

column14:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Decent ambience, good drinks but very slow service and the non veg menu is a bit on expensive side and again slow service. Can be improved, plus the menu should be more.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  I must say this is one unique place! The place looks very different from the restaurants you've been to! Nothing to extraordinary but simple and feels so homely and greenery all around you. It's on the highest floor but makes you feel so close to the earth. A beautiful concept. And that's the ambience and I am absolutely sure you will love the food here as well

We ordered a lot of dishes and the most loved one was the Nigerian suya! The pizza is good too and please do not miss out on the sizzlers I am sure nothing on the menu is going to disappoint you. Maybe pricing is a little higher but definitely worth it."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Absolutely recommended place to come for family lunch and dinners (especially dinners). The place is beautifully done with lots of space in between tables. The interiors are quite suave. Food is really good with quality portion size. To top it all they give some really cute saplings for free :)'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Well.. Have been there twice expecting it would be better from the first. Nah. Not worth your money. They have their own style but not accomodating enough for all types of food lovers. Names are fancier than the taste.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  This cafe like restaurant is very artistic. I will talk about the ambiance first as I always do. :)
The look of the restaurant is very attractive. Use of pop colours gives it a fresh feel. This restaurant is a rooftop place, and having greenery arround you makes it wonderful.
Art is a base of this cafe, so the great food!

We had pasta and prawns cracker (prawns bhajji)
And as I mentioned it was GREAT!
We found pricing a little high but you can always ignore it for the great experience designed by the friendly and soft spoken staff!

#chavadi'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  The 3 stars are only for the service and the beautiful ambience. Was extremely disappointed with the food. Don't know what went wrong, but Chavadi needs to step up with their starters big time. Didn't have the main course so the review isn't based on that. Cocktails are good though."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  So I have this friend whose friend is a foodie. He recommends a place on the rooftop and I am like yeah yeah yeah.
We take the address and drive down and when I reach there, I am confused. This does not look like a restaurant. This is an apartment. I was like, oh shit - did I get fooled? I still take the elevator and go to the roof and woah... a restaurant...on the rooftop. We order food like paneer Tikka and peanut masala and pizza and sizzlers and babycorn and egg bhurji, and we can't stop.
Now the friend of friend is a friend. Thanks bro!!"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Love the ambience but not the food. Good music. Parking place is there. Fish finger is good. I love the picture wall. As a sweet gsture once they gifted us a flower plant which we appreciate,!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I had heard about this place often however never got a chance to visit the restaurant. Its a pretty restaurant, cozy, romantic & comfortable. Family, friends or couples - it is meant for all.
We had a couple of long island ice tea & Spiced Guava Martini for drinks, Chicken grilled on charcoal & , french fries for starters & Thai Grilled Fish served with Thai Green curry & rice. Home made Coconut flavor ice-cream for dessert.
All the items were good but what I loved the most was the grilled chicken. It was yummy.
You can read books, or take your laptop & use it as a workspace too. Really cool place to visit. I shall visit again.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

  First coming to the ambience, that's absolutely amazing since it's on the rooftop and you get such an amazing view of the city. ?? By the time it's evening, the soft lighting and music makes the place even more fun to be at, especially with a bunch of friends. Also, I wouldn't want to forget the interiors, they put out the pictures of people who visits them at the entrance and I found that cool. Then coming to food, Pizza, pastas and chicken starters are amazing that goes perfect with a bottle of chilled beer. Management of the place is great and you'll get a top class service. A lovely place to visit in Bannerghatta. ??"), ('Rated 4.5', "RATED

  Ambience was awesome , it?s a rooftop restaurant. Bit costly but food was good. We loved starters and couple of Italian dishes like creamy mushroom pasta and pizza.Pizza was pathetic.rest everything was ok.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  This review comes over 6 weeks since my visit, so I'm going to miss out on a whole lot of details. But from what I recall

Bizarre location
Appealing spread
Great taste
Well priced
Above average ambience

The music, if I'm not mistaken swung from the remixes of 80s English to Boy bands of 90s. But the smoked sweet potato, sizzlers and cauliflower soup kept my mind off it. I must say that Chavadi has one of the most interesting spread and i actually wanted to try each one of them.

But, had a great time, tummy filled and satisfied having tried some new stuff, something I always look forward to."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED

  Exploring new places with a group of New friends is one of my favorite activities...This time I explored Chavadi,an open air restaurant with multi-layered set-up, giving a lush green view to enhance the ambience. As soon as I entered there I was amazed by the concept of the restaurant which is spread greenery... simple sitting arrangements with green plants all over the place, giving a fresh soothing relief to your eyes....mood uplifting soft music was going with the ambience perfectly....They have quite a good offerings of food & beverages...I enjoyed my glass of Jager bomb & jalapeno martini... wood fire veg loaded pizza and lagan ki boti was really mouth watering. I liked Moroccan lamb tagine with saffron rice in mains....they have a unique dessert called matka cappuccino coffee which is worth tasting...I have to appreciate the good job done by their chefs & mixologist... I would really like to chill out often here...kudos to team Chavadi....'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED

I liked Moroccan lamb tagine with saffron rice in mains....they have a unique dessert called matka cappuccino coffee which is worth tasting...I have to appreciate the good job done by their chefs & mixologist... I would really like to chill out often here...kudos to team Chavadi....'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED

column3: 45, Kasthuri Nivasa, 2nd Floor, 19th Main, 2nd Stage, BTM, Bangalore
column12: Appam, Chicken Biryani, Kuluki Sarbat, Panneer Butter Masala, Meen Pollichathu, Vellarikka Pattanam, Sea Food
column14:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  One among those places that could be categorized as more quality and less quantity. Not satisfied with the price and the quantity that was provided. However the dishes were pretty good. Ordered pothu fry & vazattiyathu and would recommend the same'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Amazing place for authentic Kerala food. Loved their kappa udachathu and pothu vazhattyathu. Absolutely lipsmacking and must tries. Malabar chicken biryani was also really good.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Its been long since I wrote something about restaurant. For past 2 days, I am using this restaurant for take away. Quality of the food is worth every penny. Quantity is also up to the mark. You can feel the real taste of Kerala. They took time to give the food but it was worth the wait.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Two years back, I've posted a review for Cucumber Town. However, unfortunately, after a while they closed the restaurant. Now, the good news is that they are back with a Home-delivery and take-away model. I'm extremely glad to welcome them back as they are the best Kerala cuisine in Bangalore! The food taste and quality is excellent. Try their beef/chicken and mutton items, appam/idiyappam/aripathiri, irachipputtu, seafood and biriyanis.

Only worry is that now we're unable to get the amazing sarbaths and mocktails they served. I hope they will start that too in the future. As I shared earlier, their main highlight is their care for maintaining top-notch taste, without compromising the quality (they don't add any artificial colors or enhancers).

Best of luck guys, you always deserve a 5 star. :-)")]

column3: 389, Cave Temple Road, Doddamma Layout, Pai Layout, Hulimavu, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Street food is one of the best things in Bangalore and to experience that,you should just forget things like hygiene and cleanliness. Of course that doesn't mean street food are always unhygienic but there are few people in this world who give excuse of hygiene when we offer them street food.

Don't bother to ask and remember 99 varieties coz basically you cant remember and its just unusual mix of flavors that covers 99 in number. It's the same usual kind of menu you find there unlike any other 99 varieties of dosa food carts..

Ordered masala dosa. It was too good.

Try once:)"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

column14:

The food is simply awesome and and I have ordered the lassi here that is also something too much for one person to finish. But they took kinda more time to prepare the food. But I think that is acceptable when you know that a great food is coming on its way.

Ambiance-4

  I will give a 3 star rating. It has good ambiance, but the food is just ok. Didn't like the taste of food here. I've been to a lot of good Punjabi restaurants, felt the taste can be far better is what I feel."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  The food is excellent. Specially the biryani was good.
The ambience is good. But the starter we ordered was a bit less . Nevermind the main course made up for it. A must visit in this part of Bangalore'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Food / Drink - Punjabi.. (balle balle, may I say!).. Truly North Indian restaurant in Bengaluru. Curries are spicy and flavourful. Could be better though. Breads are yummy. Lassi is good, wish it was a little less sweet. Overall, decent place for North Indian food.

Price - Priced according to competition. Nothing exciting in terms of value quotient. But.. not exorbitant either.

Service - Decent. Responsive staff. Food takes a bit of time to arrive though. Plan accordingly. Not much wait time on weekends. Funny story.. I had to get my bill corrected thrice..!

Ambience - Good. Tables are well laid out. Quirky posters on the wall. Dummy bullet to make you feel like Punjabi.. Would that get you to do balle balle.. I don?t know, you tell me!

Location - On the ORR.. close to Bannerghatta Road.

Parking - Street. Not sure of on-site parking.

Speciality - Punjabi food. Lassi.

Must try? - Nah! Better Punjabi restaurants available.

Pro tip - Check the bill presented to you!'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Decent ambience & food (tasty , medium spicy & oily ) . when you are on punjabi cuisine you don?t count calories - just enjoy the food . The time taken to serve could have been better .'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Was a regular at their meenakshi mall store a few years back before they closed that one down. Was very disappointed with their food today. Had a prawn starter which was basically a dry curry and not the tawa prawn we expected. But the mutton Rogan Josh ( or its equivalent name here ) was VERY disappointing. Seems like they have changed the cooks along with the store and have bad food at very high prices ( the mall prices were reasonable ) . Not going back .')]

column3: 1st Floor, 173, Bannerghatta Road, Bilekahalli, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  This restaurant has given me a headache on my first order itself. I ordered hyderabadi chicken dum biryani (something worth of Rs. 200+ as of the menu) but with some Zomato offer, got it for Rs.99. Upon delivery, I found that the quantity of the biryani is so so less that even a child would go hungry with that. Upon complain, they said that they give the same quantity to every customer. It made me sure that they are just thugging the people with these online orders because certainly a Rs. 200+ biryani container doesn't look that small. They just kept me hungry the entire night.
People please don't fall prey for this restaurant. I would have rated it a 0 star."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

column3: 55, 5th Floor, Goenka Chambers, 19th Main Road, Jeewan Griha Colony, Phase 2, JP Nagar, Bangalore
column12: Pork Chops, Craft Beer, Chicken Biryani, Chowmein, Drunken Chicken Wings, Cocktails, Mocktails
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  It?s on roof top, nice food and worth paying as well. Over all if it?s nearby to anybody then it would usual place to go, for people who stay far may be one time go'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Heard a lot about this mini brewsky, finally got chance to visit this place and try it. Definitely it?s mini reflection of Byg Brewsky in terms of ambience. Food was equally good as the other outlets. Loved the grilled fish with mashed potatoes. The service was good, as it was very less crowded so we received good hospitality.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  A great roof top brewery with a view. I had visited it multiple times but this review is for my visit from last week. This visit was after 3 long years but nothing changed. It has the same vibes reciprocating across everything. Great ambience, service, food and beverages. I can't ask for more. It was a Saturday night and seeing people bustling with energy pumps you up. Ordered LIIT, the same old monk, chicken nachos, chicken wings platter & noodles. Taste was as good as it gets and generous quantity with competitive prices stole the show. Keep it up!!! One incident worth mentioning is I forgot to pick up my card after payment and started leaving. I was near the staircase and the waiter who was serving us came running and gave back my card. Thank you so much. I forgot to enquire his name but kudos to him for this gesture. Cheers!!!"), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Ambience is fantastic. One of the better breweries I have visited. Nice beer but not the best I have tasted. Red ale was mediocre. American blonde was better. The chicken wings we ordered were average. One should visit this place for it's ambience."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  One of the best brewery in town, loved the ambiance and the food too is pretty decent. A bit difficult to get place especially during the weekends, so recommend you guys to book it prior. Overall a thumbs up!!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  The place is amazing. The whole place is three floors and the top most floor probably has the best view. The ambience is too good. Food quality is top notch and tastes good. We tried Baby Potatoes Achari i.e. Baked potatoes dipped in lemon pickle. I must admit it was the best side dish to have.
The only problem with this pub, SERVICE. Yes, the service is too damn slow. You ask for a Papad and the waiter would have lost his count would say he will get it but post 30mins he would still say the same. Forget food, one serve of water was served after 15 mins after constant reminder.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Great place for beer lovers. Fun, lively place soread over 3 floors. Their stout is the best beer they brew. The red ale and hefewezein and Belgian whit are great too. The cocktails however we're a little disappointing. The Drunken Passion (whiskey based) cocktail was an overly sweet cocktail. Mojito was pretty good. Food was great. The Greek salad was so good I couldn't help order another one. The omlette was yummy topped with fried garlic. Chicken biryani was good flavours but slightly on the drier side. Cheese balls were yummy paired with salsa ? ambiance is fun vibes with great music. Staff friendly, helpful and attentive. Definitely going back for more.
Edit: found my cocktail here. Long Beach ice tea is the best I have had so far. Perfectly balanced , managed to down 3 of them quite fast ?"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Have never explored this area...went to this place on 24 Dec and it was really packed..we sat on the terrace area and liked the chilled ambience...tried a variety of things and drinks..liked the peshawari chicken tikka and the LIIT....service is also good despite heavy rush..just found the table size pretty small for 4 people..we had to really adjust... recommended if u are in the area...'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  **One of the nice place to hangout with friends**

We decided to celebrate one of our friend's bday here,its on roof top. The ambience is good with some nice lighting arrangements. The chilled breeze was blowing and our tastebuds were waiting for tasty food and it was a treat for them.

The quality and taste of food is very good here. We ordered for Paneer platter,Wings platter, Cheese balls,Mushroom Tikka,Chicken chopsy, Fish masala fry,Chicken and Veg biriyani and ended Walnet brownie with ice cream.

Apart of fish masala, everything was good. Platter is comparatively budget friendly here, you get 4-5 varieties for around 400 bugs which is cheaper when compared with individual items. Brownie and ice cream was top notch. Cheese balls were very tasty.

Service:4/5

One of the popular dishes, it was simple, crunchy and tasty.

All time favourite classic fries with extra cheesy effect , it was great.

tender.
