  Nice place . Good ambience. However service can be better and also the food. But somehow managed well. Please work on the taste of the food. It was really basic.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Heard a lot about restaurant, on a weekend been there with a friend. It is a rooftop restaurant with nice ambience. The music is not very loud. Their food was good. We ordered Cheese Garlic Bread and Paneer Papadi as a starter.
Paneer Papadi is their unique dish. It was crispy outside and soft inside. Recommend to the people who like Papad.
We ordered mix veg curry and some naan. Curry was good.
In d end we ordered Apple Scramble which was really good. They serve it with Vanilla ice cream.
Overall the experience was good.
Can suggest to people who like draught beer.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I like this place especially the roof top. Beers are good and food is tasty. We have been here 3 times and everytime the food we ordered was good with no complaints at all. I am a big fan of belgium beer so in most of my visits i ordered for wheat beer and it was really good with nice aroma and taste.

The family restautant which is downstairs does not live up to the expectation. Not sure if the chefs for both are different but I didnt like the food which was served here.

Children are not allowed in the roof top so plan accordingly if you have kids and try to get a place upstairs.
Alert: Being a good brewery in this vicinity, this place (upstaris) is jam packed on weekends so book before you go whereas on the other hand you can get a table easily in the family reataurant downstairs even on weekends.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED

column3: 3474, Maruti Dental College Road, Dodakamanhalli, Opposite Valmark Ananda Apartment, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column12: Paratha, Chole Bhature, Lassi, Thali, Paneer Parantha
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Went for breakfast on a Saturday morning. They serve amazing parathas. We tried the Sattu, Matar, Paneer and Paneer Cheese parathas along with Chole Bhature. Parathas are served with curd, mint & coriander chutney and a cube of Amul butter. Not much of a place where you look for ambience, but as far as the food is concerned, it will sure have me visit again for more.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  The food is extremely tasty. In short it reminds me of home away from home. Chule Bhature and paneer parathas are to die for!
Would keep coming back to this place for more!'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Perfect stop for Delecious paranthas, chole bhathure , chawal combos .. pocket friendly plus tasty . 5 star to this place ! Paneer parantha being my personnal favourite.')]

column3: 8, First Floor, Arekere Gate, Opposite Rose Garden Apartment, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column12: Masala Prawn, Mutton Kosha, Thali, Mutton Curry, Luchi, Fish Cutlet, Bengali Pulao
column14: [('Rated 2.0', 'RATED\n  Had ordered a fish kabiraji from them. It was pretty bad, to say it politely. Even the sauce, kasundi, was very mild, and seemed quite stale. Overall it was not a very nice experience, and definitely not worth the price.')]

column3: 170, 16th Main, 2nd Stage, BTM, Bangalore
column12: Buttermilk, Jal-jeera, Churma, Palak Kofta, Lassi, Gulab Jamun, Dahi Bhindi
column14:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  One of the most decent place in BTM, very nice food with very effective cost. Yep but I would say it's not up to the mark for ambience but overall its perfact pack for delicacy."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Great veg food. Have been visiting this place for 7 years now. The taste has been always great. The ambiance is nice n rural. good variety of veg dishes. Ppl with both veg n non-veg tastes Shud try this place.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

Must try: Dal Bhati, Mushroom Masala, Rasmalai"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Ordered a plate of gulab jamun and rasgulla each for home delivery. Nice packed, quick delivered. Delectable! Must try for sugar rush. Absolute value for money.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  This is a small restaurant that prides itself on authentic tasting food from rajasthan and flavours of northern india
The only place I have visited so far that has real pudina (mint) chutney

The dishes are all mouth watering and well priced for the sitting environment, albiet the portion sizes could be increased.

Taste- 4
Ambience-3
Service-3

Overall, can give a go when the hunger kicks in for true to flavour food in low budget'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  It is the best place where u can find best veg dishes, and all of them are delicious. Looks like mini Rajasthan. Must try if u love North Indian food.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Veg only-Simple North Indian/Rajasthani place which serves excellent food. This is not a place to talk about ambiance, it is simple but like setup. Place is clean with friendly waiters.
I am kinda regular to this place when I hangout with veggie friends, I don?t like their starters be it anything. But the main course is simply great.
Love their rotis, parathas. They serve them popping hot.
All other curries are good too. They will be super busy and You may have to wait a bit for your turn during weekends.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Pure vegetarian rajasthani cuisines with a rustic decor. The only place where I have got jaggery instead of sweet fennel at the cashier. Wide range of Thalis you should go n try. Sumptuous and pocket friendly at the same time.')]

column3: 45/46, Ajantha Avenue, 1st Floor, Puttenahalli Main Road, 7th Phase, JP Nagar, Bangalore
column13: Continental, Sandwich, Burger, Italian, Salad, Pizza
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  It was a saturday afternoon and I was looking for a pet friendly place to grab some grub when I stumbled upon this interesting lil joint in 7th phase Jp Nagar. When my pups and I walked in, I felt transported to another world.

The place was so welcoming and calm. We were greeted cheerfully by a young gentleman who then showed us to our seat. When I placed the order I had no idea what lay in store for us.

Each dish took a little time but was perfectly cooked and tastefully flavoured. The staff were very courteous and non intrusive. That was the longest and most enjoyable lunch I have had in a while.

Definitely going back soon.')]

column3: 63, Ground Floor, Royal Meenakshi Mall, Hulimavu, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore

column3: Yelanahalli Main Road, Akshaya Nagar, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column14:

  Horrible Food
I ordered for masala dosa and masala dosa was like a piece of shit
Order for dhai wada they did not have stock so sent me wada sambar
I ordered for iddli they did not have stock they sent me puri
The complete order was so pathetic only my waste bin was lucky to taste it

My experiance was like
I ordered for chicken and they have served me beef as only beef was left with them in their kitchen. HORRIBLE is not the word to difine t hia outlet and experience...'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Food was deliver cold when I called up restaurant he refused to listen. Zomato support is another pain in....
Good for nothing
I would advise and suggest don't expect help from zomato and if possible switch to another app like Swiggy Food Panda and so on, even though they are from same bed but Zomato never if you want to waste your time energy and money along with nightmare from their so called support team then please enjoy thr taste

Couldn't njoy coz of food temp not happy I do not recommend"), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED

column3: 3rd Floor, Food Court, Vega City Mall, Srinivas Industrial Estate, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column12: Waffles
column14:
[('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  The waffles are a bit dry and they look good but aren't as delicious in taste. I asked for a second serving of chocolate sauce, which they were happy to provide, but that too did not help.
Try with some other toppings and you might have a better luck."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Wonderful place. Had Strawberry Hong Kong and Smoothies with my wife. It was delicious. I'm willing to try Chocolate and Oreo flavours once I visit again. Kudos!"), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  We went to the stall at Vega City Mall. The Oreo shake was good, the cappuccino was okayish. They can improve on the taste, I feel. It can get better with Service as well!'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  This place is located in Vega City Mall and serves such amazing waffles that you can't hv them just once.

The waffles are so tasty and yummy that you go into a different dimension altogether.

The pricing is very reasonable.

The staff was very courteous."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  One of the best wafel houses in Bangalore, an world wide wafle chain now in Bangalore, a wide variety of savouries and coolers to pick from, a completely unique menu , and lip smacking taste , the wafel sandwich was really crisp and on point,
The nutella nuts too is highly recommended, i loved it's softness and taste, one of the best restaurants on the Vega City food court . A must visit place for the best wafles in town."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  A wide variety of delicious waffles are served here . Chocolate OMG is my favourite. Best waffles in town. They gives choice of waffles with ice cream scoops of any flavour, also sandwich waffle is worth tasting here for all salty tongues')]

column3: 309, Sai Nandana Presidency, 5th Main, 11th Cross, Near Rajashri Grandhim Hospitals, Vijaya Bank Layout, Bilekahalli, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column12: Pothichoru, Roast Chicken, Fish Fry
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  I have tried only the Pothichoru from Deeja, I have to admit this is the best and most authentic pothichoru I've had in Bangalore so far. Truly delicious, it carries all the character and love a typical mom made pothichoru has. With a portion of perfectly cooked fish fry, egg omelette and generous serving of chutney, thoran and curd, truly value for money too.

Thank you!

A request: Introduce curry side like pulisseri, erisseri, kootucurry etc, atleast one, as add-on options in your menu.")]

column3: 24th Main, 2nd Cross, 2nd Phase, JP Nagar, Bangalore
column12: Waffles, Burgers, Masala Fries, Crunchy Veg Burger, Tiramisu, Chocolate Pancakes, Oreo Shake
column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  We had chips & sprinklers mini pan cakes !! It was fresh n very delicious !! Had visited this place couple of times since it?s just a walking distance from my home . Worth the money n your time . Pocket friendly prices with ultimate taste . Must visit n recommend to all .'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  As soon as you enter you get a great cozy vibe!!
Chocolate ecstasy made my day... well nutty banana wasn't bad either soft creamy pancakes well it's totally in the second time visit list!!! Lovely place and amazing waffles with decent music and good company. What else you need to call it perfect!?"), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Hufff ... The sweety creamy soft pancakes... ?
It's a plan before a month to visit in here ... We had already planned what to order ... Directly went in and ordered as planned ... The bubble wrap waffle is too god and then comes this citrus zing .. the ice cream compensates the sweetness of orange syrap... But my good suggestion is please order any savoury dish with any of the pancakes or waffles... Every thing is intact in service, ambiance, music all good."), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  The pancakes were way too thick, clawingly sweet without any freshness or tartness. Considering pancakes are their speciality, they should do a much better job.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  An amazing place with good ambience and courteous staff the prices are decent and food is worth the money.Tried the cheesy fries,Tiramisu waffle,Marble chocolate French pancake and choco bongo mini pancake,Mushroom and cheese sandwich and cheesy pops all of them taste amazing I would definitely recommend this place.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I m a pancake and waffle lover whether it?s for breakfast or dessert!!
Found this great place at Jp nagar 2nd phase called @pancuzzi and lived their menu service and the taste
I will visit their for sure. Again
I recommend this place for yummy desserts and most amazing pancakes especially Dutch'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  It is a very small, average sort of place, and I am still quite confused about the rating. Apparently if you rate them on Zomato you get a free ice-cream scoop, and that I suppose explains the 4.2. The coffee was not good at all, and the waffles were sub par. The fries were decent. The service is quick and polite.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Pretty good place for breakfast. We ordered nutty banana pancakes and mushroom cheese sandwich. Pancakes were fluffy and the goodness of banana and caramel sauce with it was bang on! Sandwich was so yum. Mushroom tasted so good with cheese and green chutney. Ambience and wall art is just awesome here.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Dessert is probably the most important stage of the meal, since it will be the last thing your guests remember before they pass out all over the table. This outlet @pancuzzi is doing pretty well.
We had tiramisu bubble waffle, seasonal fruits mini pancakes, nutty banana and mushroom sandwich.
My personal favourite is tiramisu waffle.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Highly Recommended for Breakfast Food lovers.

The Cereal Killah with the fluffiest French Pancakes, assorted Fruit Bowl and Cereal is a great meal at any time of the day.

The Choco Bongo Mini pancakes were delightful little treats,

Waffles with Berry sauce, strawberries and scoop of blackcurrent ice cream(The Berry Delight) can never go wrong.

For us the highlight was The Meaty Delight which is a savoury pancake with mushrooms, sausages and a fried egg on top. It was the best savoury pancake we've had in a while.

Variety of Shakes available with all the Sweet and Savoury goodness.
We recommend the The Dirty Shake."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  A small happy place! I tried masala omelette, coffee and mini pancakes.. I liked all of them. We also ordered potato wedges, they were disappointing! Overall, it's a cosy self service place with happy servers.

P.S.: Like the way it looks.! Try the eggs


pubandgrubsite.wordpress.com")]

column3: 14, Patel Medicals, 7th Main, 2nd Stage, BTM, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Amazing food have ordered dragon chillie prawns and egg fried rice the flavour the taste and on top of that the customer service was spot on. You won't get a better place to order at late night.. HIGHLY RECOMMENDED"), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  Dragon chilli prawns n veg fried rice. Totally wasted so much money and time. it costed me rs393. but rather the food looks like for rs150. not worth'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Amazing food. Late night on time services. Really glad for that. Had ordered Thai red curry with herb rice and must say it was absolutely delicious. Loved the crafted menu. Cheers guys. Keep up the good work.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  1st time user, I have ordered Gopi Manchurian and BBQ chicken . I was really impressed with the food ingredients, it was freshly cook, and flavor. They even provide chopsticks as well . Delivery was timely and the best part was the owner himself came n delivered himself at around 1, he was very friendly and nice ..Overall the food was really yum...'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  What can i say? Finally an authentic Thai and Chinese cuisine.....everything was perfect, fantastic and amazing food!! Form Thai my choice will be Thukpa and Chinese Devils Chicken')]

column3: 1743, Raghavendra Plaza , 2nd Phase, (Near Diwakars Hospital), JP Nagar, Bangalore
column12: Momos, Chilli Mushroom, Chop Suey, Sweet Corn Soup, Clear Soup, Hakka Noodles, Honey Chilli Potatoes
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Dish: American chopsuey
Place: Zhangs, JP Nagar

Follow me on Instagram @vk_gopal #viveksfoodquest

Lost count of the number of times I have visited this place. Located at JP Nagar, this Chinese restaurant offers amazing dishes. Clean place with courteous staff. From #noodles to #chopsuey , everything is ??.
Must try:
i. Triple Schezwan Rice- Chicken/Veg
ii. Chopsuey
#viveksfoodquest'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  A good place to have Chinese cuisine in the locality. It's a very old outlet in jp nagar. Ambience is good. Place is well maintained with all interiors and lighting.
They have kept a Chinese zodiac on the table, you can go through it by the time food arrives.

Ordered egg fried rice and prawn Manchurian. Food was okay. Egg fried rice was bit salty and Manchurian was very spicy. Else taste was good.
Should improve food quality.

Staffs were courteous and service was fast."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Nice place and a nice restaurant of descent ambience. The service is descent. The Wanton Soup was really a good start and this joint serves good Chopsuey (American).'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Ever since this place opened in BTM in the 2000's , I have been a fan of this place. One of the best Chinese outlets in Bangalore. Foods such as manchow soup, chicken fried wantons, schezwan chicken, koietheo noodles are top notch."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Zhangs....its attract me from the name....so I Went there with excitement....it didn't failed me...
Ambience:
That the most part I want to share...it's awesome...we feel that we are in some area of Beijing...the ceiling lamp and the portrait hanging on the wall....
Food:
Chinese food always goes well to me...
Must try...tom yum soup...chicken Manchurian...if you like sea food try their fish pepper dry and chili prawn ...its yummy...they have salad and soft beverages also...
Service:
All the staff are dress well and polite and nice to talk to them..thank u for their service...
Overall I had a great time recommend for everyone"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Very famous and old restaurant from this area. They are running from last 20 years. They have only one outlet. The decor is of typically a chinese restaurant. We ordered a Veg Manchaw Soup which is the best chinese soup i ever had. Then we ordered a Paneer as starter which also was very nice.
The quantity of strarter is sufficient for 2.
Main course we ordered triple seezwan with gravy.
This was the perfect chinese lunch.
Highly rerecommended for chinese food.
One of the best restaurant in Bangalore for chinese.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Wanted to try this Chinese restaurant noodles here is really good we ordered for chilli garlic noodles and mixed noodles(with prawns and chicken) both were really good. We also ordered for mushroom chilly which was just average. Service was really fast and staffs were polite ?
Food3/5
Ambience3.5/5
Service 4/5?'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  We ordered chicken wonton clear soup, drums of heaven , chilli paneer , garlic chilli noodles and triple schezwan veg rice . All dishes tastes delicious .
Ambience : 4.5
Service : 5
Food : 4.5
Drums of heaven chicken : 5 stars')]

column3: 294, 7th Main, 7th Cross, BTM 2nd Stage, BTM, Bangalore
column12: Chaat, Chole Bhature, Raj Kachori, Thali, Rasmalai, Paratha, Pav Bhaji
column13: Mithai, North Indian, Street Food, Chinese
column14:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Good place to try out some North Indian chats and snacks. If u love street food then you have to try out from their spread of snacks. Also they serve combos like chole kulcha and Puri sabji. Overall my experience was good. Also if u want to try tandoori chai..yeAh u heard it right.. tandoori chai. Den u might want to visit this place .'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Had visited this place twice. Today I had Dahi Bhalla. The taste was very nice. Few days back, had North Indian meals here. Food was good. We had Phulka thali and Special Phulka thali. Price difference was 50 rs. The Raita was *replaced* by Panner gravy and one extra Phulka in the special thali. I think, they have the same menu, everyday. Overall, the food is good.'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Went there today as I was having craving for Delhi chaat and the overall experience was okay-ish. The ambience is nice, its a self service place, seating is comfortable.

We ordered aloo tikki chaat, papdi Chaat, choke bhature and rajma chawal. I liked only choke bhature, else everything was average.

The chaat were very bland, which certainly is not a feature of authentic Delhi chaat, we had to add table salt in it to make it worth eating. I was disappointed with aloo tikki the most. They need to change their preparations and recipe a bit to be relevant in the competitive market.

Would not visit again.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Ordered from this place on a weekday. This is essentially a sweet shop. The packaging was decent and delivery was on time. We ordered chole bhature (chole was a little oily but good. I liked the salad that came with it) and a box of motichoor ladoos (ladoos were really good but some were broken. Not too be fussy about things but ladoos should not be broken). The prices seem fine when compared to quality. Overall:
Food - 3.5/5
Delivery - 4/5
Vfm - 3.5/5'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  *This review is solely for the Tandoori Chai served*

Tried the very famous Tandoori Chai which was doing it's round around India & was excited because this place was the first ever in Bangalore!

It's a small stall set up right in front of Shagun Sweets, obviously for everyone to try it out. The bill is taken from Shagun sweets & then the chai is prepared outside.

It's 20/- in total and honestly, I was so bummed! I can do better masala chai at home. It tasted so bland and I regretted it at the first sip. It's all just a hype to have fancy tea served all desi.

*IGNORE this place for chai."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  As I wanted to try their tandoori chai from so long so I rushed to their outlet. The chai stall is available outside the shop and the person makes it right in front of you. Although the process of making was gud but the flavor of tandoor was not so strong to call it a tandoori chai. Overall it's a good store."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I ordered golgappa from this place once. It was really good. Packaging was very good. Dahi and chutney was given separately and papri was given in a box. A must try item.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  When something new like tandoori chai drops in your city, you gotta try It!
This chai is available outside shagun sweets and it's there almost the whole day.
The chai person makes it right in front of you and it's a fascinating process.
For people who like little less sweet and strong tea, this is a must try.
You can sit inside the restaurant and enjoy your tea with some snacks."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  If you want to drink 'Tandoor Chai' then this the place for you in BTM 2nd Stage. One cup will cost Rupees 20 and worth it. The taste of ginger, cardamom, cinnamon & kulhad (heated in tandoor) makes this tea the best. Overall the shop is good for sweets and quick bites. Give it a chance!"), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  We rushed to this very restaurant because of this newly opened tandoori chae stall.The tandoori tea will give you the flavor of tandoor but it can't be replaced by the regular kulhad tea.Not that great though one can try it.we had Singapore noodles and papdi Chaat...They we're quick in delivery and the quantity was also pretty good.Noodles we're quite basic but the Chaat was tasty."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I visit this place specially during festivals?
Sweets are very good here. They maintain quality that?s the best part about this place ?
Chat items are very good but I feel it?s bit costly for this place and quantity is very less.
For sweets this place worth it but am not sure for other items as I find it bit costly.
Service is very good here. People are cordial
Overall best place for sweets ?'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Very good place to have breakfast in BTM. You will get lot of options for breakfast especially North Indian food.
Ordered
Dhokla was very tasty and it was fresh and soft.
Chole bhature was very delicious but little bit oily and forget about fitness ,just try it.
Other best items are paneer parantha ,Raj kachori.
They are serving Tandoori chai but it was not so good.
I will recommend this place.
Ambience was not so good but it was very clean and hygienic .')]

column3: 25, 6th main, Mico Layout, BTM layout 2nd Stage, BTM, Bangalore
column12: Fish, Rasmalai, Doi Katla, Aalo Bhaja, Bhetki Paturi, Chicken Kasha, Aloo Posto
column14:
[('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Ordered chicken fried rice, chilly chicken and fish fry. Horrible food. When you are charging money, please provide quality. Fish fry doesn't look like a fish fry. 120 bucks for 1 and it doesn't even even good? Every thing is hot with chilly and that does not make food tastier. Not happy with the quality and quantity."), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  I visited the place 3-4 times.. never had any good experience at all.. ordered food many times .. being a bong i did not have much choice to order from some other restaurant.. but everytime they dissapointed me..being a bengali restaurant Guga baba provides luchi which is made of aata instead of maida.. roti was horrible... quality is so poor and order chicken curry as well which does not have much taste only full of onions.. very poor food quality...'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Well never been there but Ordered 3-4times via Swiggy/Uber Eats from this place which is mostly fish curries and chicken items. Taste is pretty good what I felt like proper Bengali dishes. Love their Aloo Posto, Doi Katla and Bhetki Paturi which is a must try. Chicken Kosha and Mutton Kosha were nicely cooked but was oily. Once ordered Pulao which was not that great. So u Bengali folks staying near BTM in Bangalore u can definitely try this....as we crave for Bengali dishes like always...?'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Visited this place many times and had mixed experiences. With veg meal you will get rice, dal, two types of vegetables, alu bhaja and chatni and they changes the vegetables on daily basis. Since it?s a Bengali cuisine, you will get different types of fish items but the fish quality is average. Chicken and mutton dishes are okayish. In the dessert mostly you will get misti doi, rosogolla and gulab jamun.')]

column3: 18, 24th Main Road, Near Sobha Tulip Apartment, 5th Phase, JP Nagar, Bangalore
column12: Noodles, Mocktails, Honey Chilli Potatoes, Veg Ball Manchurian, Kung Pao Chicken, Momos, Pepper Chicken
column14:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  A decent place to have good Chinese food. Ordered their big plate combo which gave a fair idea about their dishes. Chicken momo had a generous stuffing of chicken. Pepper chicken was okayish. Schezwan hakka noodles was more Indian than Chinese. The chicken mushroom gravy was well made. It perfectly complimented the schezwan noodles. Apart from these their speciality, the tangy orange chicken is my favourite here and a must try.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Very clean and tidy place. Great to chill with friends, casually. A place that serves this type of standard Chindian menu at these prices, doesn't normally look like this. Full marks for that! Food itself is your average Chindian fare, but with excellent value for money, if you consider the quality of the venue and portion sizes. Been here 4-5 times and tried a variety of dishes. The Fried rice section and the Chicken appetisers section is what we end up ordering the most."), ('Rated 2.0', "RATED
  I'd heard really great things about Oogway and decided to get dinner from the place. 4 of us went there with hopes of great food, but everything was quite the opposite.

Everything was bland! Everything lacked salt. Nothing was flavorful.
We got 2 combos in which we got Chilli paneer, mushroom broccoli Namprik, Asian greens, veg Manchurian, schezuan fried rice, plain hakka noodles, wantons and spring rolls.

The only impressive ones were the wantons, but not by themselves. The sauce made them taste good.

The food though, although super affordable, I'd like to get my money's worth.

This was a wasteful experience."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Great food, good service, clean place.
This is a good place for friendly get together or a night out with the family.
I went there for their buffet, which offered unlimited main course and side. And you can have drink or dessert for additional 35 bucks.
The price is very reasonable and the food is fresh off the wok.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Really good soups and starters... I love the chicken manchow soup and their babycorn and paneer starters among others. We have always got the food home delivered and the service is pretty fast. Ordered the chicken hakka noodles once, didnt like it though, found them to be overcooked and bland.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Food is fresh and tasty.
Very spacious and clean restaurant
Oogway signature's and Honey Daarsaan with ice cream are must try
Staffs are friendly and helpful"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Decent and affordable restaurant for South East asian cuisine.

We tried noodle soup, chilly panneer, dragon mushrooms, schezwan noodles, Thai fried rice and desserts.

Noodle soup was just salt water plus boiled Vegetables. Soup was a big let down. Apart from that everything else tasted good! Chilly panneer won the evening!'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Tried their chicken manchow soup, the chicken was hardly there! Packaging is good and the price is affordable. They should be generous with chicken! People deserve good amount of chicken ?')]

column14:

  Visited this place after a long time and found that the look and the feel has changed. Friendly staff and decent food. The only problem is the service; for at times they really test your patience.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  We came early morning at 8 on spot for breakfast.
The beans were dry and not so nice. I love mushrooms and I was it wasn?t so dry and a tad bit of seasoning would have done some good. The scrambled eggs were soft and lightly fluffy. I don?t like white bread though. I didn?t realize this before ordering and I don?t know if they do give that option. If they don?t , it would great if they would keep it. I typically never order white bread on the side.
The food was only okay. The service pretty good.
And I love that they used paper straws. The world needs more paper straws , less plastic.'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED

  Bucket list checked!!!!!!?
Wanted to go there long time. So went for brunch on Sunday.. Amazing place. If u are egg lover it definitely a place for u..
Ambience - spacious, industrial look.. Colorful background.
Parking - that is bit problematic over there. As they don't have any parking space, though there is empty ground where we need to pay 30rs to local people to keep the car.
Food - now comes the best part.. Food is to die for.. I very big egg lover, i can have them 3time a day so it was heavy for me. Please do try classic French toast is really lip-smacking. Masala bun was good to. We wanted to ordered everything on the menu but u kw thats possible so we were over with 4 dishes.
Will definitely go again for next set...??????"), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Been here with family to try all in all egg dishes after a long time. I heard they the management has been changes. Taste was not good, it lacked any one of the flavour. Wake up team egg factory wake up.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

Also recommend you to have the Panner Chilli
Staff - 4/5
Ambiance - 4/5
Food - 4/5'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Never knew what Oyako was or what it meant. Thanks for letting me know what it is. Ordered Masala Egg Bhurji which was hot and spicy. Their Tex Mex Migas was great and quite filling. You can definitely try that if you don?t like something much spicy and different. And yes to end it all up a perfect Classic French Toast. No complaints here. It was just perfect. The ambiance is okayish and the place I seem is not busy most of the time so your order won?t be taking much long. This place is very much pocket friendly as well.')]

  You know, sometimes these small, pocket friendly restaurants serve you the best food. I have been to chow san more than 15 times now.
The quantity, quality and the taste is commendable, just as how we Indians like the Chinese food to be. I've tried almost all the chicken starters. The best of what I like here is the lifu chicken, namprik chicken and for the spicy bit, hotpot chicken. Oh! How can I forget the soups. Manchow soup, though one of the most common soups that I order almost in all Chinese restaurants, I love this one the best.
Triple Szechuan rice with sauce can't be ignored too.
Although, their service can be improved.
Overall, be sure to satisfy your taste buds at a very pocket friendly price. :)"), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED

column3: 11/2, Arakera Main Road, Arakera Gate, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  One of the best mangalorean sea food in the area.. Tried Pomfret masala fry, Nang (Sole fish) tawa fry, marwai (shell fish) sukka & fish curry... I can certify for authenticity...'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  One place which I visit every time I crave for actual sea food... They make the yummiest prawn ghee roast and neer dosa. It's budget friendly and the restaurant is open until 11 PM. The staff is also very sweet and kind. A must visit for all the coastal people craving for dome actual sea food"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Good food! Non-spicy, sufficient quantity and reasonable price. Decent seating available. Convenient location, near Arekere main road, off Bannerghatta road.'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  worst food ever...no taste and food was very cold.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Been to this restaurant twice and had a good experience here. We ordered fish meals, bondas sukka (squid sukka) and chicken ghee roast.
Ambience is good. Good spacious tables and the menu is very reasonable price.
Bondas sukka was tasty. We loved fish meals. It's an authentic coastal food. Fish meals costs 130 rupees, And we get 1 full mackerel fish cut into 2 piece. Half in curry and half fried. 2 neer dosa, 1 cup clams sukka and veg curry. Chicken ghee roast was also great

There a other restaurant serving coastal foods around. But this one serves authentic coastal food. Will visit again"), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  Roties were burnt, vegetables were not cleaned properly, granular stones on every bite.'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED

column3: 941/1, Shop 4, Hulimavu Main Road, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Situated near Hulimavi hate, this has become our lunch spot as it's very close to college. Most of their food is good. It should be among the most pocket friendly places around here. Good food, service might get delayed during lunch hours as it gets very crowded.

Kerala porota is a must try here. Their veg n non-veg curries are all good. Chicken Hyderabadi Biryani is also a good option here. I like their chicken shawarma as well. Overall a good, pocket friendly restaurant.

I wouldn't recommend their malabari chicken biryani because is basically chicken mixed in ghee rice. Their Chinese menu is just decent. Also the Chinese main course I have tried, the chicken was very hard. Their juices tasted very good the first time I tried but later on it became too watery.")]

column3: 2nd Cross, Kothnoor Village Main Road, Natraja Layout, 7th Phase, JP Nagar, Bangalore
column12: Noodles, Corn Momo, Manchurian, Momo Platter, Veg Momos, Potato Momos, Tandoori Momos
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  This place is a pure joy. Lovely food. It was home delivery and it was quick. Totally recommended. The Momos are nice and also the baos. Good food by good people.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A small place , not so easy to spot. Momos were good but too small as compared to the price. And their mustard oil was lil uncooked. However they do have a vast variety of momos of all kinds.'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  The new menu of chicken isn't great.

The seasoned potato momos have been removed. Bring it back! . They were awesome! It's removed in the new menu."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This place I visited back when it was pure veg and was opposite to Black Pearl, Koramangala. I had no clue when it did get shift.

A must place for all music lovers as they play reaallllllyyy reaalllyyy beautiful and amazing soundtracks. 

Coming to food : I have tried mixed momo platter which was authentic and too good for my taste buds. Also tried a fried rice which I customized and was damn filling.

Price: Moderate.

Wifi- super strong at early stage and they reduces drastically.

Service : Really appreciate the way the owner himself interacts and makes sure you are comfortable.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  No more a pure vegetarian place. They are selling non-veg also now. Days.

Noodles are always not available. 3star rating based on their previous taste for fried rice.

A big disappointment with start of non-veg.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Yummy momos? best place ? to try momos I had ordered spinach corn fried momos, soya Momo's fried,paneer tikka Momo's all of them where yumyy?.
.
.
.
.
.
.

column14:

  Located in a nice quiet place. Good ambience and place is kept neat and tidy. Its more like a restobar. Had Shyam Savera a type of kofta which was a delight to eat. Recommended to visit here once.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I have been visited this place more than 15 times and every time this place is managed to impress me. Every non-veg items are mouth watering. Veg Doha is so delicious. Crunchy palak Paneer ..u must try.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  It has a multi story seating arrangement and offers quite huge space with family area separated and bars separate. The quality of food is explicit and tasteful especially the non vegetarian items.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  When you feel like going out but within your neighbourhood to avoid traffic . Good options for Mangalore non vegetarian options . The staff is courteous.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Well to be true it's near my home so, no mood to cook let's go simply Indian. I just love the place. They have ample parking space. it's 3storied building they have roof top as well which I prefer the most.?
Service wise they are pretty decent. Quality and quantity of food is good. People around there are polite and decent. If u have someone coming home and u need to take them somewhere simple Indian is a quick fix.
With live Match and light music definitely will do the work"), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  A good place to have a dine out with friends and family. Nice rooftop environment also. The restaurant have proper sitting arrangements with good interiors. The food is quite good in taste no complaints in that.. Service is little slow. I think there is less number of people on work so attending all the tables is difficult for them also. Hope they can get more waiters so that service become faster. Overall a good experience.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Best part about simply indian is you get an option to choose between the rooftop or the fine dine. Variety of options to choose from. If you are there, don't forget to try the Chicken Ghee roast.. Good service. Slightly expensive.."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I went with my three friends and we enjoyed the food like anything..

The Interior of the place makes u feel more good and what better way to enjoy Punjabi food when you have Punjabi ambiance like dhaba!!

Food was extremely delicious, order too many to remember the names..

Gonna be visiting this place again nd again..'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Typical Punjabi restaurant. Had my favorite Pulao and rajma. It was delicious and would love to go back there again. P.S. The ambience is also Punjabi with pictures and dolls'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  After reading reviews from here we went to this place. We were craving for North Indian food. It was not as we expected! ?
Ambience is good. Hospitality is good.
Rotis are great! Normal vegetable sabjis are good but paneer gravies are very sweet ?
Starters are okay.
Finally food is over priced! For the price which we paid we would have eat in some other North Indian restaurants twice!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Whenever I crave good punjabi khana, I head to this place. They server authentic Punjabi food. Every dish is slathered with butter for the extra richness. If you are in bannerghatta road and looking for good food, you know where to go'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Just Wow ... Visited with my Friends for a Casul Dinner on Last Week. Though we went there on a Week Day but the Place was almost Packed. I am regular to their Bellandur Outlet. The best part is their Consistency. There are so many Choices in their menu. Perfect Ambiance. Quick and Friendly Service. As usual the Hospitality at it's Best. I must say that they are the Best Punjabi Restaurant in the Town. If you really wanna try an Authentic Punjabi Food then you must Visit this Place. Highly recommend! Will surely Visit this Outlet soon. Cheers!

Ambiance : 5/5
Food : 5/5
Service : 5/5
Value for Money : 5/5"), ('Rated 2.0', "RATED
  It was just average. Wished it was more fresher food specially in case of non vegetarian food. We had a thali and i dont think its as per the ratings and reviews here. Overrated restaurant. I have better food at my own home so won't be visiting."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Have been going there for the past 5 years and it has not disappointed me :). Been there with friends, family and its food as well as ambience have been really good. Kudos to the staff as well. Food has been really great. Especially pickled onions-absolutely love them.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  This place is a hidden gem.
And I really hope it continues to stay awesome.
I ordered dal makahanni and biriyani. Both were excellent and huge in size. They arrived in time, hot and fresh. I would definitely eat here again.
Service:- 5/5
Value for money:- 4.5/5
Food:- 4.5/5'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Had a good experience.
Food was good. Service was nice. Hygienic and well maintained place..
My family likes this place, my friends like this place as well.
Staff are polite too...
The food is so delicious, one of the best north Indian food I have had in Bangalore.Keep up the good work.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Planning for a Sunday Lunch?
Punjabi Times is what we prefer and recommend ....

Overall the perfect venue to spend Sunday afternoon.
Love to revisit.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  Excellent experience.
This place serves amazing food quality and quantity and taste wise!Every time without fail my experience has been such a good one.I always have a good time, actually the staff here makes the experience worth while, they are efficient with work and also they are polite .Its a good place to come with friends or family or colleagues, I usually come here with my colleagues as we work near by.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Went here for a buffet in weekdays and could not take the pictures because had left the phone at home and that is the only regret. The buffet was magnificent with items ranging from dal makhani, paneer tikka starters, potato wedges to an amazing main course with authentic Punjabi flavours and is truly a delight to a north Indian food fan! The ambience is classy as expected and the service was also courteous unexpectedly which generally is absent in restaurants serving such delicious food. The paneer pasanda and makhani in the main course were truly delicious and on top of it the dessert in form of gulab jamuns made the day just perfect. The place vibrates positive energy and is a must visit for anyone who wants to try out some authentic Punjabi food. The price is a bit on a higher end but the buffet is worth it compared to competitors so cheers!!'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED

This place serves amazing food quality and quantity and taste wise!Every time without fail my experience has been such a good one.I always have a good time, actually the staff here makes the experience worth while, they are efficient with work and also they are polite .Its a good place to come with friends or family or colleagues, I usually come here with my colleagues as we work near by.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Went here for a buffet in weekdays and could not take the pictures because had left the phone at home and that is the only regret. The buffet was magnificent with items ranging from dal makhani, paneer tikka starters, potato wedges to an amazing main course with authentic Punjabi flavours and is truly a delight to a north Indian food fan! The ambience is classy as expected and the service was also courteous unexpectedly which generally is absent in restaurants serving such delicious food. The paneer pasanda and makhani in the main course were truly delicious and on top of it the dessert in form of gulab jamuns made the day just perfect. The place vibrates positive energy and is a must visit for anyone who wants to try out some authentic Punjabi food. The price is a bit on a higher end but the buffet is worth it compared to competitors so cheers!!'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  The food is excellent and very authentic! The ambience is amazing.
A place worth coming with your family or friends or colleagues.
The staff treated us very nicely, service wasn't delayed either..
Wonderful experience altogether.
Thoroughly enjoyed it."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Went on a usual dinner as was craving for punjabi food
Nice ambience has a lot of punjabi tough to it with nice punjabi music going on
The food is very spicy so we couldn?t enjoy much of it as we?re drinking lot of water throughout
We ordered paneer starters and paneer tikka masala with roti and misi roti
Rotis were good and soft to eat
An average place'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  The contrast of all the popular reviews I've been seeing, the place was empty in the evening.
It's a small outlet, food is okish. The quantity is good though.

We ordered Murg Galauti Kebab, big chunks of chicken with distinct flavour.

Some phulkas along with Murg Bhatinda - a punjabi style curry with onion based gravy. I was told that this was one of the spiciest curries on the menu, but it turned out to be a little too sweet, so I was kinda disappointed.

A good place for a family lunch/dinner or corporate lunch.

Food: 3.5/5
Service: 3.5/5
Price: 3.5/5
Ambience: 4/5"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Awesome experience. Lovely customer service. Delicious food.
Love to come over again....
Really professional
Really fun loving
Next time we are going to visit with my entire family..'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I had a good time at this place..
This place has a lovely Ambience and serves very good food.
I went there with one of my friend and we had a great time.
The service was good and the servers were very humble. This is a must visit place. Period.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  I visited this place after a decade! And my experience was underwhelming. We were 10 people and ordered everything from soups to appetizers to mains. Nothing stood out. Tomato shorba was like tomato extract mixed with tons of oil and Harra shorba was tasteless. Paneer chutney had thin slices of paneer that were hard. Coming to mains - dal makhani had garam masala a bit too much and paneer tikka they forgot to make tikka of the paneer before adding to the curry. May be the non veg is better. I don't know"), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  As soon as you enter the place you totally forget that you're in Bangalore. Perfect ambience for a Punjabi restaurant. Food is amazing. Amazing service and ambience. Good Punjabi folk music in the background. Prompt and fast service. Ek aur bar jaana toh Banta hai.
Food - 4/5
Service - 5/5
Ambience - 4.5/5
Price - 4/5
You rock Punjabi Times!!!
Keep it up.")]

  To begin with , I ordered only two items , rock burger and aloo Patty burger for home delivery. Though the items are few but it's worth sharing for it's quality. It was a bang on for my cravings. Had to share the half picture of rock burger to show that how juicy it was from inside. Good thing is that the burgers did not feel dry at all. Will be visiting or ordering again, undoubtedly. Good job cravy wings ?"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Another one like KFC. Its so nice to see KFC having cheaper versions at other stores???. But with ?150(50 off) I had a lot of things for lunch, fries, lollipops, even a ?20 coke. So yeah why not, do give it a try??'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Visited this place while i was around this area. Found this through Zomato and visited after seeing some good reviews and ratings. Tried the Mexican Grilled Chicken burger and Chicken Cheese Shots. Even though the taste of the patty of the burger was good, but the bun spoilt the overall taste of the burger to a certain extent. The quality of the bun needs to be improved to give a better taste to the burger. The cheese shots tasted good but had only one small & round piece of wrapped with cheese. If it was shredded chicken or smaller pieces of chicken then the overall taste would have been much better.

Overall, its a pocket friendly place with average taste that will ease your hunger without burning a hole in your pocket')]

column14:

  Just beside the main road is this restaurant, which has the look of an on-the go restaurant that is self-serviced. I will break my review into three parts.

1. Do not expect any ambience because there aint any.

2. The prices are very reasonable but yes the most worth mentioning part is that there is amply variety to choose from. So many different combinations of North Indian Vegetarian food. And they're all totally worth the price. The food is good. You can definitely eat here once a while.

3. I would suggest the management to cover the area facing the road with some type of shield either plastic or any sort of thing to prevent dust from entering the premises. I would rate your restaurant with an extra star if that could be taken care of.

Recommended.")]

  Happened to spot this new kid on the block two nights ago. Decided to give it a try. Ordered lemon chicken and chicken szechwan fried rice. The fried rice was good but the lemon chicken was not lemony enough for my taste. When i expressed my opinion to Mr.Shivu, it was considered immediately and he modified the dish for me.   A new restaurant that offers good food at affordable prices. Visited the place over the weekend to grab a scrumptious veg lunch. The interiors is clean with comfortable seating. I would have preferred a lot more veggies as well which is a bit scarce. The drinks are decent. The service is a bit laid back depending upon the flow of customers. A warmer welcome would do more good. Having said all this, the place still beats MacD or Burger King in the overall taste vs price rating.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Probably my favourite place for burgers as of now. This place is my preferred place for working with buddies, brainstorming sessions and a lot more work and fun. You can get a variety of burgers, shakes and much more here. The burgers are juicy, the fries crispy and shakes so thick that makes you want more. Only bummer being that the service takes a lil while longer than you can expect normally. Price wise, not so bad but a bit on the expensive side.

Overall a good place to hang around with friends and co workers. Good food, ambience and a decent value for money.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED

All in all I would highly recommend this place for some quick bites...!!!'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
 
Intended Rating: 4.5/5

Biggie's burger is one of my favourite burger joints. They have exquisite range of burgers both veg and non veg. The burgers are very different from the regular ones. Must visit burger joint. They also have hot dog, fries, wedges, shakes and mojito's.

? Ambiance:
This outlet is huge compared to the other outlets. It's very spacious and has indoor and outdoor seating. The decor is quite catchy and lit well.

? What I had:
? Chicken Cheese Beast: This is the best burger I have had. The chicken patty is filled with cheese inside. The cheese oozes out of the burger at just a bite.

? Veg Exotic: amazing blend of Mushroom n Paneer patty with grilled veggies and cheese.

? Cuban Classic Mojito: very fruity and refreshing. Just goes well with the hot fresh burgers.

Ambiance: 4/5
Food: 4/5
Service: 4/5
Price: 4/5"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  This was my first order from this particular outlet. Ordered their mutton biryani, peas pulao and chicken maharaja. Packaging was good and food arrived hot. Coming to the biryani, I am a great lover of their biryani, as soon as I opened the pack, a foul smell came out. column3: 544, 6th Main, 11th Cross, BTM layout, 2nd stage, BTM, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Tried this new place for pastries & Thanks to them... The cakes were pretty good & everyone in the family loved it.

Had 4 different pastries for the evening which includes

1. Red Velvet
2. Chocolate Truffle
3. Pineapple
4. Black Forest

My favorite picks would be Red Velvet & Chocolate Truffle :)

Red Velvet was pure love to have from this place. rich chocolate in the truffle gives it extra edge over the others.

Was informed that the cakes are freshly prepared one hour before the delivery , which made the cakes super soft & moist with good texture..Cake slices are cut to good portions which makes it value for money..

Appreciate the staff who made these yummy desserts.. 
Definitely recommended & will order for more occasions.')]

They recently introduced Southern spice chicken which is best.'), ('Rated 2.5', "RATED
  Ordered two burger meals from five star. One yummy veg and other hungry bird one.

Let me be quick and to the point here.
The food was delivered around 25-30 mins after we placed the order though it's not very far from our place.
Second the quantity of French fries which they gave was waayyy too less plus they were sort of peri peri ones, which I feel not everyone will like so they should not compel customers to have that option only. Also they gave one fried chicken piece which I liked.
Third, they gave ekdum chotu 15-20rs vala Pepsi.

Taste wise both the burgers were fine, though I did not like the bun that much as it was a little sticky.
Just the fact it is affordable and not that very bad in taste, I am giving them 2.5"), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED

  I happened to visit Five Star Chicken Branch in Vijaya Bank Layout, Bangalore. I ordered Peri Peri chicken for take away. When I opened the chicken it?s like piece of Charcoal. The color is black. It?s a completely different from the picture they display in the store. It?s not all tempting to eat. After taking the first bite ..I realized this worst piece of chicken I had in my life. It?s was over fried and ultra-salted in taste. This is not Peri Peri chicken I had in Nandoo?s. It?s not the best chicken in world. It?s the worst chicken on Earth. I threw the whole piece in dustbin. I will never ever order from Five Star Chicken.')]

column3: A11, Opposite Ranka Apartments, Bilekahalli, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Bhavani chats is a great place for a evening snack. Chats, juice and sweets are available at very reasonable price. Dont go by the look of the place.. taste and hygiene is what matters and there is both at this place. Everything will be prepared in front of your eyes. Cheese vada pav, samosa, chum chum sweet are a must try. Enjoy!'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  There are a few places where you get good chaats.. This is one of them..
It is not that clean... But ya chaats are good.. Especially pani puri, tikki chaat.
Jalebis are good... Hot n crispy Jalebis... Moong dal pakodas are nice...
They do serve parathas like paneer, aloo, Gobi which are average.. Even milkshakes n fruit juices are OK..
On weekends this place is crowded in the evening..
For breakfast which starts by 730, you get parathas, poha n puri sabji which is also good..'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Very decent place for chats and parathas in this locality.

Should tell the guy who makes the chat your preference, otherwise good luck ;) 

May be on a next visit, should try out their items in the breakfast menu, which are their specialties')]

column3: 3/1, VAV Avenue, Eshwara Layout, RBI Layout Main Road, JP Nagar 7th Phase, JP Nagar, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  The biggest disappointment is name ..Tandoori Chai, I expected they will put kullhad in tandoor and when it is red hot they will pour tea and serve it in another mitti ka kullhad..for this experience I went there and completely shocked and disappointed!!

They served normal tea in chini mitti kullhad, tea was ok and french fries were ok but major disappointment because of expectation.Please change the name of shop or serve real tandoor chaim.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  I decided to eat from this place with my fingers crossed as there are not many reviews about this place. The shawarma I ate here was the best shawarma I've ever eaten. Must try the shawarma in this place."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  ordered shawarma and chicken burger. i must say its amazing. packing was good. never tasted shawarma lyk this before. the best part is there is no extra packing charges for any of the product. loved it... must try...'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Best shawarma I had ever tasted in Bangalore.. It's really very good... Best among all the rest of the restaurant. The quantity is amazing must try..."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Just ordered shawarma. First I thought it?s a new restaurant but again ordered by finger crossed. I must say it?s amazing and mouth watering shawarma. Yummmmmmy.')]

column14:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  This place is located next to Oracle office. The ambience is good n nice. Coming to taste and price it's decent enough pocket friendly.

Tried the veg pizza it saw yummy, well cooked n the size was worth the price."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  We had a Paneer pesto sizzler, a hot chocolate and a cafe latte. The hot chocolate and cafe latte were tooo sweet! We asked them to fix it, they said that they have a vending machine. They also tried to fix it by adding more milk but it ended up being sweeter. ?? On the bright side, the sizzler was amazing!! Would certainly visit again for the sizzler here ?')]

column3: Hose 17, 19 cross, 7th main 2nd Stage, BTM, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  If you want delicious 'ghar ka khaana' in BTM, then this is the place to visit! People here are friendly and service is fast. There slogan is 'Good food is good mood'. And they sure follow it. Cheers!"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Very tasty food in budget price. Must try the paneer and chicken dishes along with delicious Parathas and Veg Starters.

Highly recommended !!!!!')]

column3: 7, Doddakammanahalli Main Road, Central Excise Layout, Phase 2, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column12: Burgers, Sandwiches, Pizza, French Fries, Cheesecake
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Reasonably priced and tasty food. Perfect for a snack or two. I especially love the cutlets from this place. We had ordered chicken cutlet this time and by mistake they sent us veg ones. But they were kind enough to send us chicken ones later, late in the night. So good service by zomato and the restaurant. You know how to keep your costumers happy.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Lemme first look at this cheese cake again ?? i was loving it .. the taste was really cheesy cheese .. it was a blueberry one .. and i also tried chicken kabab hot dog ( If i am Not wrong with the name ) .. it was so filling .. the ambience was quite pleasant ?'), ('Rated 3.5', 'RATED
  Nice ambience and a lot of good food on their menu like sandwiches, pizzas, chicken roll and burgers.They serve pastries and milkshakes too. Overall a good cozy place to drop by with family or friends for your evening snacks.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  One of my favourite place for hangout. Second floor is really very cozy.... Delicious food and great smoothies. Cake is really tasty..... Especially the rainbow cake...')]

column3: 1304, 1st Floor, 9th Cross, 20th Main, 2nd Phase, JP Nagar, Bangalore
column12: Burgers, Egg Salad, Pasta, Pancakes, Lasagne, Pizza, Lime Soda
column13: Cafe, Asian, Burger, Continental, Italian, Salad
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Newly opened in JP Nagar 2nd phase, this small place serves you amazing Continental food dishes. Amazing options to choose from. I wanted to check this place out and went there for lunch. Their menu is crisp and to the point. Neat and tidy place, with decent seating and ambience. From starters to their Mexican and Italian dishes, everything was freshly made.
1. For starters, had paneer fingers where the paneer was fresh and melted in my mouth.
2. Garlic Mayo dressing Salad: tasted good but was too salty. Told this to their staff and they got it changed.
3. Mexican Veg flat bread: try this, and you will love it. All vegetables added, freshly baked with wheat base.
4. Main course: Fish curry with rice and chicken lasagne: my friends loved this.

Try out this place, and I am sure that you will start frequenting here often.

For more such updates follow me on Instagram @vk_gopal
#viveksfoodquest'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Bland, just too bland. Everything was extremely bland. I don't recommend this place to anyone. Service was fast, but food was disappointing. We asked the manager, he said ' This is Italian, so its supposed to be bland'??‍??"), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Sorry that I'm rating it 3 it's only because of them ... Took such a long time to serve the food ... I hate being waited to get served ..
But coming to the food ... I can rate 5/5 stars .. the burger patty was crisp n fresh ... Since we asked to make it spicy they made it
I usually do not prefer milk shakes .. but I tasted brownie shake.. it was light n yummyyyy
Even the chicken wings was rightly spiced and tasted very with slight of sweetness and herbs on it.
And the Alfredo pasta was also good but could have been added with right amount of salt n spices in it
In total I like the whole ambiance the only problem is you have to wait if u have ample amount of time."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  This place is placed on main road at first floor jp nagar..
Ambience: it?s simple and plain with some quotes on the wall with simple seating arrangement
Food: their menu is good with healthy substitutes
We ordered brownie shake and burger with cream cheese paneer wrap
The salad was ok ok but the fried were yummy
The wrap was heavy
The burger was good the tiki was made from kidney beans
Rates are reasonable too'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Had food here for first time . Quite healthy n delicious. They have variety of options in wheat instead of maida stuff. We had veg here n I loved it !! Would recommend all to visit this place !!'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Had been here twice for weekend breakfast!!! Enjoyed both the visits. All Eggetarians must visit this place. We thoroughly enjoyed the dishes. The hospitality is so good as food served. The presentation is neat and the taste is consistent. We enjoyed the Omlettes and pancakes... our Favourite is Mushroom Spinach Cheese Omlette with baked potatoes , which goes with watermelon juice. The Manager is down to earth and does not hurry the customer to order next... he patiently explains each dish... My breakfast joint on weekends is already chosen.... ? Ajay Babu
Price:4/5
Food Presentation:5/5
Quality:5/5
Quantity:5/5
Ambiance:5/5
Service:5/5
Hospitality:5/5
Taste:5/5'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This place is situated at JP Nagar 2nd Phase. This place serves continental food with a bit of Thai dishes. Ambience of the place is very good. The food is also good had there chicken soup and watermelon salad is a must try dishes. Staff is very friendly and the service was also very quick. Come here with a group of friends you will enjoy this place. Price is also reasonable
Food- 4/5
Service-4/5
Ambience-4/5'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Decided on this place based on Zomato rating & this set an high expectation. The options available based on menu card is really amazing with dishes across the globe . The Italian option we took had an over dose of cheese in all of them . (Seemed like an cheesy affair, with it over riding the taste of all other ingredients ) . For once did not agree that yeh cheese mast hey ?. Service was ok .'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  If you are searching for a place that serve a variety of omelettes and have a good taste in English breakfast then look no further.
Crafted plate located in JP Nagar 2nd phase gives u a number of reasons to visit.
1) Tasty, stomach filling breakfast from eggs to pancakes to waffles
2) reasonable price for the quality of food they provide
3) good coffee
4) Very welcoming and polite owner

Over all a great place with good vibes and would highly recommend this for people in and around jp Nagar.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Good service.Decent food.I only hope their claim of no artifical flavor colour n MSG is true.There was no nachos as per zomato suggestion but whatever i ate was 7/10.need to visit again to trymore stuff'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Went there for a dinner, not very busy being a weekday.
Good ambiance, very well thought out menu combined with multiple cuisines. We ordered chicken leek soup - good, veg Thai curry - great.
Chicken steak - good,
Only letdown was desert - Apricot delight.
Service was lil slow but ok. Staff were very friendly and helpful.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

Looking forward to trying more from the menu.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  Cp burger was good , fresh lime soda was great

Ambience was fair enough. Parking space was der.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Stumbled upon this place while looking for a place to have lunch . Having the fetish to try out new restaurants I found this place on zomato . Easily locatable in main road of JP nagar . They have some unique and different variety of soup and menu . Very courteous owner who would walk down to your table and explain the menu and suggest their signature dishes to try out.
We ordered pumpkin ginger soup which was a bang on . Very yummy very tasty . Then we ordered jalapeno potato cheese balls with tomato aioli which was equally good .
They have flat bread pizza which looked very delicious .we ordered paneer flat bread which was perfectly baked . All in all it was amazing experience .would definitely visit again .')]

column3: Sir M Visveswaraya Road, Kutappa Garden, Mulki Sundar Ram Shetty Nagar, Bilekahalli, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column12: Sea Food, Neer Dosa
column14:
[('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  All right!

I had been here on a weekday just to have a fish fry as I was craving for fish that day. I chose this place as it was a mangalore cuisine. I asked for bangude tawa fry. The taste was just satisfactory, nothing impressive. I don?t know how their other menu items would taste. Rating is just for for the fish fry.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I wanted to try out this place since a long time.. So one night we decided to order in.. The delivery was done in time and the food was delicious..! We ordered rava fry fish, neer dose and chicken gassi.. Will definitely visit this place to try out more manglorean style dishes. An added bonus for this restaurant is its pricing.. It is extremely reasonable for coastal cuisine!')]

column3: 30, First Floor, 2nd Main, Santrupthi Nagar, Opposite Axis Bank, Kothanur Dinne Main Road, 7th Phase, Bangalore, JP Nagar, Bangalore
column12: Sea Food, Anjal Masala Fry, Fish Curry, Thali, Neer Dosa
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  As it's located to near my house, I was planning to visit this place from long time and happen to visit last weekend. Located on the main road, it's ambience is nice.
It has authentic sea food, esp Mangalorean special fishes.

We tried Chicken Ghee roast with Neer dosa- wherein Chicken was tender and spicy. Dosa was so soft and tasty. Loved the Bangda Tawa fry- which was less masala and cooked well.

Ladyfish masala fry was semi gravy and was good in taste. Also Anjal (Seer) Kebab was nice.
Lastly we ordered Ginger Juice, had more of ginger flavor.

Service was appreciable. This is a nice restaurant if your looking for authentic Mangalore style with a pocket friendly price."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  This particular Restaurant is located just walkable distance from our house. Was wanting to visit this from a very long time. Finally, got to visit for today's dinner.
It's a sea food heaven for sea food lovers. Loved the ambience too. Its a mangalore style cuisine.
We had ordered for chicken ghee roast. It was very authentic. It was filled with flavours. The chicken was very tender and tasty.
Next we ordered for bangda fish fry, we could taste the actual taste of the fish, so delicious. It was made with very minimal amount of masala. This gave the fish a very distinct taste. Then we ordered for neer dosa, it thick and filling unlike other places where it would be very thin.
Then anjal fish kabab was the best. The fish was very fresh and cooked to perfection. It was boneless. It tasted much more better than the usual chicken kabab."), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Was very curious about a seafood place in JP Nagar. Well you know what they say about curiosity and the cat. Long story short, the seafood was extremely stale and rubbery. The seer fish and butter garlic prawns were fork resistant and i gave up after 5 minutes. The only good thing was the lime soda and we made a quick exit after gulping it down. If anyone is interested in the feedback, please please make sure you serve fresh seafood.')]

  On a nice Saturday off, I was in no mood to cook.

Looking at pocket friendly rates, this gobbler ordered palak paneer, chapatti and chicken kebab.

Firstly, the order taker could not differentiate between roti, chapatti and phulka. He was too confused while telling me what is available. Naan was not available. So, I asked him to get chapatti or phulka or roti.

Palak paneer was a disaster! I was highly disappointed. I could not even eat more than half of my chapatti with it. It was too sweet! Have you heard of sweet palak paneer ever? Also, it was too oily. The sabji did not seem too hygienic either.

Chicken kebab was not that appetising. It stink but if stale chicken. It was nothing like kebab. They were some cut pieces with bones tossed in red masala and fried.

A very disappointing experience.'), ('Rated 3.5', "RATED
  It was my first experience and I was not disappointed.

The kebabs were lip smackingly delicious.

Will taste the rest and share further.

As of now I rate is as 3.5. But it's highly recommend for people who return late from work.

It's pocket friendly and delicious.

Cheers!!!"), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED

Firstly, the order taker could not differentiate between roti, chapatti and phulka. He was too confused while telling me what is available. Naan was not available. So, I asked him to get chapatti or phulka or roti.

Palak paneer was a disaster! I was highly disappointed. I could not even eat more than half of my chapatti with it. It was too sweet! Have you heard of sweet palak paneer ever? Also, it was too oily. The sabji did not seem too hygienic either.

Chicken kebab was not that appetising. It stink but if stale chicken. It was nothing like kebab. They were some cut pieces with bones tossed in red masala and fried.

A very disappointing experience.'), ('Rated 3.5', "RATED
  It was my first experience and I was not disappointed.

The kebabs were lip smackingly delicious.

Will taste the rest and share further.

As of now I rate is as 3.5. But it's highly recommend for people who return late from work.

It's pocket friendly and delicious.

Cheers!!!"), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED

column3: 449, 9th Cross, 2nd Phase, JP Nagar, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  If you're craving for some crispy chats... Here it is... Mr. Meetharam serves delicious chats at there outlet... Much like the conventional touch of taste... Loved these masala and dahi puri here... A must visit chat shop to full fill your snack needs..."), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  Food taste was average and it was very cold. Looked like some left over food of morning breakfast was being served in the evening. My first and last experience with them.'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  probably beacuse it was delivered late and packing was torn and got wet from the rain'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  It was extremely oily and was uneatable..it can make someone sick...waste of money'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  their pav Bhaji is filling and always delivered with garnish!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Had few varieties of chats that are not available at most of chat shops in the nearby location. Clean and neat place to have chats with parking space'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  the aloo chaat,even when ordered at home was crisp and warm and well garnished.loved it'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  low salt'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  the food was warm and delicious and reached within the delivery time
recommendation: Pav Bhaji and Ras Malai'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Tried some chats, none of the chat was good. Will never visit the place again. Have not tried any sweet dishes there, I don't think they are very good."), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  spoilt and smelling gravy'), ('Rated 1.5', "RATED
  If you want to taste all items in this shop, take masala Puri. He added everything every masalas in his shop to that. Worst I have ever tasted. Don't be surprised if you find Chile in it. Go for sandwich if don't want to spoil your tummy...?"), ('Rated 1.5', "RATED
  Went to this place as I was hungry and was on the way. The person at the counter took money for two plates but gave the token for only one. And the person serving pani puri was totally disinterested and what he served was Pathetic. Never gonna drop by this place even if I'm starving."), ('Rated 1.5', "RATED
  Tried a couple of food items here all tasted average, especially vada pav tasted super bad. Not sure about the sweets I haven't tried but I don't think they will be great"), ('Rated 2.5', 'RATED
  Not so good not so bad.. Ordered pav bhaaji, raj bhog and lassi.. Ok ok types service .. Ok ok types food.. Was so hungry so had to go there..'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  I did visit this place a couple of times for an evening bite.. A huge variety of chats and have tried most of them.. I could not find one item which is special and tasted average.. I haven't tried their sweets though.."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Suddenly bumped into this place amidst of late evening hunger. We tried kachori, pani puri and pav bhaji. We didn't really like the pav bhaji. It didn't have the right tastes and not the butter that is one essential thing on bhaji.
Pani puri was decent nothing to boast about. But yes the kachoris were really good. Hot crisp fresh and with the right fillings. Exactly how I like it."), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  The quality of sweets is very poor and they charge a very very high price for sweets. And also also it very unhygienic. The staff are also very unprofessional'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  I am not a big fan of roadside eateries especially the ones on a noisy main road and quite close to shanties, but Mr. Meetharam just caught my eye when I was passing by the the 9th cross road. It was the only place open at 9:45 PM, even though the closing time mentioned was 9:30 PM. It is a place famous for the parathas and chaats. I ordered the Pav Bhaji, but wouldn't recommend it. It was tasteless. The parathas were served with curd, pickles and an accompaniment made of dhal and spices which was quite interesting. 
The gol gappa is a must try and quite refreshing. The chap behind the counter was quite enterprising and offered us free samples of the mixtures and other savouries and coaxed us into buying them. :-)

A touch pricey for a small place with no seats. Especially the parathas."), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  Ordered 1 kg sweets this Sunday from here through Grofers, was delivered stale 2-3 days old sweets. Shame on Mr. Meetharam and Grofers to cheat on customers like this. Never going to order again.'), ('Rated 3.5', 'RATED
  My personal fav place for pav bhaji and jalebis..jus love them there ..
Hygienic ..medium rates ...Gud staff and nice ambience
For chat lovers like me another Gud destination in the city!!'), ('Rated 3.5', 'RATED
  Finally a chat place which is close to the original chat taste. Some more improvement is required but at least its better than the other ones in JP Nagar.'), ('Rated 3.5', "RATED
  On my way to home from office, my savior when I don't want to eat idli dosa, for gujjus they serves Dhokla, Yes DHOKLA. Many varieties in Chat, Sandwiches and Parathas were good too.")]
