column13: Chinese, Thai, Seafood, North Indian, Momos
column14:
[('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  I wanted to try out a restaurant serving Asian food and was prompted to try this as it's close to my home.

I will list out my experiences as per categories :

1. Ambience : Not good. The ground floor has a fine dining vibe and the rooftop gives off a pub vibe but the crowd is mixed in rooftop as families come in big groups. It's extremely confusing as to who the rooftop caters to as the music is played loudly, a projector displays sports games.

2. Staff : I was disappointed by the hospitality extended towards me yesterday. Not one of the staff members so much as even gave a smile and I waited 20 minutes to get my bill.

3. Food : Manchow soup was good but the crispy corn starter wasn't great as the corn wasn't crunchy. Pan fried noodles with schezwan sauce was good.

Overall, if you are looking just for decent food at a reasonable price then this place is good."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  This is a very nice place in the heart of jpnagar.Opposite to zaitoon jpnagar and having a nice big parking lot.They have an air-conditioned dining area and a roof top dining area as well.
We went there for a lunch and chose to sit in the roof top area.Roof top section is good with lots of indoor plants and all.However they don't have a seperate smoking area.So if there are lots of smokers nearby you it could be an issue for nonsmokers.
Service is very good and fast.
Coming to food,we tried Chinese/Thai food which was very good.Tried Diced chicken with green chilla paste & namprik goong for starters.Both were very much tasty.
For main course,we ordered Thai green curry with rice and Hakka noodles.Loved the Hakka noodles which was fairly spicy.Thai green curry was very much creamy and mildly sweet.One Thai curry with rice should be enough for two as it's very heavy..
The menu is well priced.Not that pricey.
I will definitely be visiting them again ..even more hungry for more..."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Loved the food here and they have good offers too. The variety in the cuisine is something to appreciate and so is the courteous service offered. They also have three different types of seating area to cater to variety of needs. Definitely recommended place to go in JP Nagar.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Fujian we located in JP Nagar but never got a chance to enter inside. From the name thought they serve only Japanese food but surprisingly they make really good coastal food too. We ordered ghee roast, mutton pepper,appam and prawns gassi.. Every dish had quality and quantity.. Will be again going to this place.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Another restaurant on main streets of J P nagar . Wide range of options for non-payment vegetarians since they have coastal, coorg , north indian and Chinese varities.
We being vegetarian thought of trying Chinese this time .
In starters we ordered crispy corn chilli pepper which was a bang on.
We ordered butter garlic noodles and schezwan fried rice and it had perfect blend of spice and Chinese flavor . Not to mention the quantity which is good . Ambiance vice they have an indoor seating and a rooftop .
Rooftop dining is recommended and is beautiful .
If you are around JP nagar definitely must try .'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  This is one of my fav in the city.always been! Their Nasi goreng is one of the best I've eaten so far. We are a group of friends who love to go to this place because of the service, ambience and especially their food! You should try their Chilli lamb as well as their roast lamp..they were succulent and addictively lip smacking delicious!
They have a good spread for vegetarians as well to the veg's delight. There is value of money in this place and everytime I've been there I've made memories to treasure."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A good place for seafood lovers. The ambience is very basic, can definitely be improved. The staff are polite and their service very quick. Apart from the seafood items, the lamb stew with appams are delicious.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Food tasted decent-3.5/5, service was decent 3.5/5,variety -4/5, what i didnt like was the table spread was dirty, the sofa wet n dirty( food from previous diner), hair everywhere on the table including on the sauce cups.thankfully i didnt see hair ?in? my food.they need to improve the cleanliness.The ambience too was nice.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Been to this place for a friend?s Birthday party ?
A quite place with a good melody to hang up along for a decent dining... Ambience was something very much dealing with greenery i.e. pots all around the wall.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Fujian surprises the customers with rare combination of Chinese , Thai and Mangalore Style!!!. ??
The starters and curries were delicious, will definitely give this place another chance just for the great range in their menu..
The ambiance is of typical colonial cafÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82ÃÂ©. The place is open from one side making it ideal for romantic dinners.?'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  A fine place for a buffet lunch, visited this place on a birthday occasion, the food is good and the service good. All in all a good place to visit, preferably lunch.
Why 3? Read comments. :) (Made the edit because the world lacks gratitude)
Until next time, cheers!')]

column14:
[('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  I ordered from this place yesterday. The eggs, beans, mashed potatoes served with toast and butter were yum. The sausages were slightly undercooked. Since this is a newly opened outlet, maybe it's too soon to put out a verdict."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Ordered the typical english bfast. 3 slices of toasted bread, lil mushroom, 2 sausages, eggs 2nos and butter. Tastewise it was ok. Highly overpriced at 155 per portion.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Was a little reluctant before trying, but went with it as I didn?t have many choices early in the morning.

I ordered The Great English Breakfast with sunny side up. Though the taste was okay, serving size seems really really small. Bacon tasted little uncooked, sausages were tasty and mushrooms were okayish. I could literally count the number of mushrooms on my finger tips and that gives an idea of serving size.

  This is the best place for lunch,and also budget friendly. Especially North Indian food is fabulous here.

  Should be one's last resort.  Had north Indian meals with Paneer Butter Masala, the amount of oil I could extract out of it would give anyone a heartache.

The only reason I gave 2 stars was their south Indian snacks viz Dosa and Idli/Vada are pretty decent, minus the chutney/sambhar which have a bland taste."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This is a reliable and very pocket friendly place for home delivery for breakfast.. column14:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Decided to visit this place because it was fairly new. This is much better than subway in the taste section. The subs are delicious and the service is fast. Doesn't burn a hole in the wallet."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Ordered from the Bombay Sandwich company and was very please with the packaging and quality of the sandwich! Ordered kukkad sandwich, although I could not taste tandoori spices as mentioned in the description in zomato, it tasted really good. Very filling with the right amount of chicken and fresh veggies. Looking forward to trying out other varieties on their menu.

Second order: Spicy chicken sandwich. Not really spicy, it's just mildly spicy. Bread was quite hard, other that that same like previous order. I really appreciate their excellent quality of the veggies.")]

column3: 21, 1st Floor, Next to Oracle, Kalyani Magnum Technum Park, 7th Phase, JP Nagar, Bangalore
column12: Egg Biryani, Tandoori Chicken, Chicken Biryani, Paneer Tikka, Mutton Biryani, Noodles, Dal Tadka
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  A restaurant nearby the Kalyani and Oracle tech parks in JP nagar. Have ordered numerous times via online orders but visited th place for the first time this friday. Its was completely full. Never had a complain with the food before also and it was the same this time. The biryani, Kandari kabab, crispy corn, butter chicken everything was just good. Service can always improve.

4.5 stars for this place.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  This restaurant is located on top of a pizzeria and right next to Oracle.

I had the Tomato Soup which was good. It was creamy and the bread crumbs we're crispy.

For starters I had the Kandari Kebab which was very soft and succulent and tasted amazing.

I also had the Chicken 65 which was good.

For my main course I had the Garlic Roti which had a lot of garlic and butter with Chicken Tikka Lababdar Curry. The curry had some dairy in it and it mad the curry taste brilliant.

I also had the Mutton Dumb Biryani. It tasted good with a good taste of spices but I feel that it should have had more flavor. The pieces of mutton were tender though.

Overall, great food and a great experience."), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Sent stale chicken, never order chilli chicken from them. Made me feel sick after having it. Worst experience ever, won?t recommend this place to people.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Hello foodies
Here management is so responsive though stewards r bit carless only.... still these stewards have their own reasons for their mistakes.... But still I feel they r lack in their presence of mind while doing their job... apart from this
The authentic paneer dum biryani any one can enjoy thoroughly here... The gravy ( not sure whether its mirchi ka salan but its awesome.... the thickness of gravy add on taste 2 it ).... management gestures and responsiveness make u feel comfort so that u feel to visit / order once again'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  It was for a quick snack.. forgot to mention that I like the wood firred pizza spicy. #bland. #quicksnack. I felt it?s overpriced but for the place....... we have too.

Saturday evening so the place was empty.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Its a absolute favorite for office goers around Kalyani Magnum and that is evident from the queue during lunch hours. The chilly prawn is one of my favorite items from their menu. The tandoori chicken, malai kebabs, and other north indian mughlai items are great too. Whats even better is that the service is super quick and its very reasonably priced. Great for home delivery too!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I went there 2-3 times for office lunch as it is just beside from my office. It?s good is tasty. They have chinese, tandoor and Mughlai dishes. Items are good with good quantity. It?s not too costly. Ambience and staffs are all good. Recommended.')]

column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  First time we visited ROCK STONE ordered for Doctor Nuts and Fruit Extravaganza they both taste awesome Doctor Nuts are fully loaded with almonds and cashews quantity and quality are really worth full'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Writing this review after multiple visits. This is our go to place if we want to chill & catch up
The ice creams are pretty good. Ambience & seating is nice. They even offer ice cream cakes. The staff is quite nice, friendly & courteous. Try their seasonal fruits ice creams. Pretty good.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This is a nice place for dessert lover in BTM. I have been to this place for a midnight dessert cramp. Even my friends ordered my birthday spacial ice cream-cake also from here and I just loved the taste of it. But price is a bit more compared to the quantity, I think that can be improved.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Must for Ice Cream Lovers !!!

Rock Stone Ice Cream Factory is a small outlet in BTM Laout.
Got to know about it from a friend and visited it .

The experience was totally different and the ice creams were really fantastic.

The ice creams are prepared on a ice table(frozen table) in front of your eyes and the process of preparing itself amuses you.
You can even get your ice creams customized with the fruits/candies you want.

MUST visit for all ice cream lovers.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Ordered ice cream from here midnight and it was delivered on time. Taste of ice cream was too good. I am in love with ice cream from this place.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Nice ice cream parlor at BTM, I have tried few icecream flavours and shakes here were very good, my recommendation is bubble gum one is very nostalgic, I have several visits this place is kind of self service, staff don't have guest recognise ability yet. best part is when experts make you choice in front of you, quite existing not everyone can do."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  A better than average ice cream parlor in BTM. To reach, get down at Udupi Signal and walk towards BTM lake. Take the first right.

Entered on a whim and nearly balked at the high prices of mixed ice creams. No wonder the shop was empty other than me being the only customer.

Ordered single scoop butterscotch. It came in a little bigger than your average scoop size and quite good. The concoction was creamy and hit all the right flavour spots. Chewiness, a must in butterscotch ice Cream, was however nearly absent.

Surprisingly, they had no water stand. This is surprising as almost all ice cream parlours now have a drinking water outlet. Youve to buy a bottle to quench your thirst.

Will I visit again? Doubtful.')]

column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Good stumptous Parantha, tasty food you should try. Good collections of Parantha available with yummy side dishes .... feel like Delhi in Bangalore'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Nice crisp paratha and in reasonable price also ..nice place to have some interesting parathas at this place and they have more varieties in many ways as they have given different name for every stuffing of paratha so u will love to enjoy your meal here'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Have lost the count of times I've been here.. A small outlet on the roadside, this place doesn't have parking or anything.. Yet it is always having a line of people waiting for their order.. They have only 3 tables in their seating area but that doesn't affect business as most of it is take away or delivery.. With a variety of parathas to try from, funny paratha names and smiling hosts, its a pleasure to eat from here.. My favorites are the paneer ones as wen u break a small bit, the stuffed paneer just flows out... Oooo.. Yumm! U must try!"), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Ordered from here thinking they will serve the best authentic parathas but only ingredient they know is Salt i guess. The food was so salty that i could not even eat it felt like puking. I think curd also was not fresh. Nothing was good about it. Worst parathas ever. A total mood spoiler.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  We ordered vegetable manchurian which had baby corn, potato, capsicum and gobi. It was average, a bit oily. Coming to parathas, everything we ordered were great. 50-50, chilli milli, Raja Rani everything tasted well and it was quiet filling as well. It was served with fresh curd, mint chutney. Packing was neat and parathas were hot! Definitely coming again..')]

The verdict, I enjoyed the meal! Thanks to foodie February that I found this place!')]

column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Small and cozy Karnataka Coastal Restaurant. Quick service, Top dishes are chicken ghee roast, Chicken sukka, Kori Rotti, Fish fry. Reasonably priced and offers decent quantity. Their both Indian and Tandoor dishes are good too..! Like a hidden gem in the area. However, Though they have AC seating separate, Not a very comfortable seating. Recommended for a quick lunch or dinner.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  There is no better place in the entire area for fish and coastal cuisines. Gassi, Pulimunchi, Masala fry, Tawa fry, everything is cooked to perfection and the taste just lingers. Amazing is the only word. Must try: chicken/fish meals, kori roti, ganji chutney, neer dosa, fish tawa/masala fries, prawns ghee roast, chicken pepper dry fry, fish gassi and fish pulimunchi, kokum sarbath. Very fast service.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  As the name suggests, this restaurant caters coastal sea food pallets. I find my comfort food there. Everything tastes home cooked and quantity/quality is pretty good too. Not a fancy place to keep in mind. Whenever I feel unwell, I pay a visit there.')]

column14: [('Rated 1.0', "RATED\n  I don't even want to review this restaurant because i feel extremely cheated , but I'm writing this so that the management or whoever responsible can take action . column14:

  Visited the place twice. Once, it was their closing time and they were unhappy about not being able to feed someone hungry. They did however go out of their way to arrange for fried rice. But I guess, it was a lil odd for me to trouble anyone unnecessarily. Therefore denied the offer.

Second visit, early morning this time ?. Went for breakfast. Ordered a benne plain and a tea.

Thin crust and perfectly roasted with the tint of the perfect roast - golden brown! And a nice strong cup of piping hot tea.

Parking - Available
Price - worth the money
Ambiance - higher-end darshini, seating option available.

4 because I need to try other stuff before giving it a full five!"), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED

column144: ""RATED\n  My wife and I stayed in JP Nagar for a year during our MBA
column146: we needed a place that had cheap but tasty food.\nThe veg section has a couple of my wife's favorites
column147: and because they customize food for regulars
column148: it is very tasty.\nThe paneer tikka masala
column150: Bhindi Fry and veg fried rice are notable.\n\nIn Non Veg
column154: kalmi kabab etc are very good.\n\nAs a dine in it just has a couple of tables and nothing noteworthy. Desserts are passable. All in all a good place for a college crowd
column155: or for a delivery order on a rainy day."")

'RATED
  Best place for home delivery or take away. Had excellent experience with various variety of food mostly Veg.
Veg Biryani is just too good to have.
Average 400 for two. Worth a try do call and ask for some special based on what you want Veg. or Non-Veg.
Quick order is what we look for and enjoy it. Crispy veg was just ok. Veg. Jalpuri was also below average.')

  Food is good. 4/5
Package. 3/5

In Zomato, delivery will be closed all the times. So you can avail in Uber eats.

No chapati combo ( only chapati/rotti and sides)

I tried their Chicken comfo offer and it was pretty good..

  First of all, the food is really good. I've had Chicken Burger, Chiken rolls and Veg Burger at different times and they are really yummy for the price. Its location is lil inside. But not too tough to find out. Since it's right next to my work place we go regularly.

The place is lil small, and the Ambiance is good for the price. If they have charged more definetly the review would be different.   Good ambience and environment mostly containing a young crowd. Only drawback is the constant honking of cars since restuarant is located right opposite to Vega City Mall. Fries Basket n Cheese balls are very nice and time pass items.
Must visit place at least once.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED

  Went here on a weekday for lunch. A few tables very filled on top with some occasion so we chose to sit down. We were the only ones seated downstairs.

Food : We were very hungry so we ordered everything together. For starters we had Tandoori Peri Peri Chicken, surprisingly it was not what we expected but much better than that. It was nicely quoted with the peri peri sauce from outside which had an amazing flavour and we loved it.

  Located right opposite Vega city, it has ample parking space and looks spectacular during the evenings when their fancy lights are turned on.

They serve wine cocktails and beer.

  Have been wanting to visit this place since a long time. Finally decided to go there for lunch. The ambiance is pretty good. But then since Bangalore rains drop by anytime, it's difficult to sit in this place. It's rooftop or the ground floor seating doesn't have much covering from the rains. There are very few tables indoor seating.

Coming to the food, had ordered for barbeque chicken pizza. It was a huge disappointment. The crust was neither thin nor thick. It wasn't baked well.
The cheese was hard and the toppings weren't great either. Couldn't even finish the pizza.
This is the first time ever I couldn't eat pizza.
Didn't really feel like ordering anything more after having that pizza.
Had ordered for cranberry coracle. It had more of litchi crush than cranberry. It was okay.

Didn't really like the experience. Surely not worth the ratings or the price."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  I've passed this joint several times on my way home and finally decided to pay it a visit. The decor is interesting but the place was not very clean; it looks so much better from the outside at night than it did on the inside during the day. The staff are friendly but the liquor is a little overpriced (perhaps cause they serve sheesha as well)... the food is very average. I was a little disappointed with my experience but that might be because I had built it up in my mind over time. column12: Poha, Tea, Paratha
column14:
[('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Ambiance - The place is located in a narrow street surrounded by smoking joints. The ambiance is simple. Uncomfortable.
The smoke from the smoking joints made the experience very unpleasant.
Folks eating there were also mostly bachelor guys. There weren't families.

Price - Affordable

Taste - We tried the following items.

Aloo paratha was served with curd and pickle - Tasted really good
Jeera rice was served with dal - Was served a large portion of rice and it was well-made.
Gobi pepper fry - Again a large portion enough for two individuals were served. Delicious it was. Must try!

Ordering food from this place would be a great idea as the food is tasty and atmosphere unpleasant."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  the kind of place JP Nagar has been waiting for long. It is for Students, working professionals, families. you can grab a quick snack and drinks or or your you can dine in & enjoy their delicious Tandoori-punjabi items.

most importantly they now serve poha. so you don't have to rush to Shoppers Stop or BTM.

do try their Lassi & Papad Masala.")]

column3: 21/22, Saifee Apartment, 5th Cross, 22nd Main Road, Near Rizwan Mazjid, Vinayaka Nagar, 5th Phase, JP Nagar, Bangalore
column14: [('Rated 1.0', "RATED\n  Food quality and taste were very poor. I ordered roti and paneer butter masala and chicken dum biryani. The paneer butter masala tasted like raw onion and tomato with cold paneer chunks. The curry did not even blend well and were like separate uncooked ingredients. The chicken dum biryani was literally bone chunks in tomato rice. The chicken pieces were not good either. And the biryani rice was literally tasting like tomato rice. Maybe it's their style of cooking, but it is not dum method for sure. The paneer butter masala was for Rs.215 I guess and the chicken dum biryani was Rs.210, and I applied a new year promo code. This quality and taste for such a cost is completely unjustified. The restaurant should seriously consider improving the food quality."), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED\n  Bulshit , these uneducated people opens restaurant .. they have provided gravy instead of Murg Bowl Nd then once I called they are arguing.   I love the chicken strips, the zinger burger and the usual fried chicken, value for money compared to kfc and tastes better than both kfc and five star chicken.

2 for ambience
5 for food'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Took 2 hours 15 min to deliver 4 pieces of uncooked chicken... And Zomato didn't give a damn about the delay and refused to cancel the order and refund. Shows who's important to them when it comes between user and vendor. And meat and eat is basically just that... Raw Meat, not fried chicken!"), ('Rated 3.5', 'RATED
  Middle Class KFC.
Yes, believe me. They serve similar broasted chicken, it also tastes similar when hot otherwise slightly average. They also have Indian tikka style chicken and Fish & Chips too. Buckets, Popcorn chicken and fiery chicken are worth a shot.'), ('Rated 4.5', "RATED
  Since one year I have ditched KFC for Meat and Eat. I must have been here more than 5-6 times. This is place is unpretentious unlike its bigger counterparts. The taste of their burgers , chicken strips , wings , wraps are all delicious. What's better is that unlike KFC and MCDONALD'S they don't charge even a single penny in the form of tax . My personal favorite is the ME chicken burger. And of course their wings and wraps."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Nice small burger joint...the make nice burgers for a quick munch at pretty cheap price... The chicken popcorns are famous here but I somehow do not like them here... The chicken strips are good... Even the chicken fries...they serve a rice meal which is good...this place is a good place to eat when you are broke!!! :) the service is slow...and the tables are often not clean!!! This is one thing that must be checked!!!'), ('Rated 3.5', 'RATED
  I was planning to eat momos on a lazy evening as I was on my way to the shop I came across this small shop. Went through the menu it is reasonably priced. We ordered a boneless bucket chicken which was tasty, only thing which I feel it lagged was there was no spice in it. I hope that they make it a little spicy'), ('Rated 3.5', "RATED
  Decent joint and a very good alternative to KFC's overpriced offerings.
I love their crispy chicken wrap. It's even better when you ask them to serve the mayo separately cause otherwise, they are too generous with portions.

Best part is...they probably have the best tortillas in the city and they use ample amounts of lettuce."), ('Rated 3.5', 'RATED
  The place is quite small but the food is very tasty ! For a person like me who has had kfc chicken his whole life this place was really good ! The chicken is very tasty ! But the staff are very stupid ! They dontunderstand english and they take hell a lot of time to deliver !'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  It was my first encounter today and I'm really happy with the food. I had Boneless Chicken Strip's and they were good. Please season the chicken before deep frying it. Take this as positive feedback & not a criticism. Overall good food, at a reasonable price than KFC. Good job Team "Meat And Eat."'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  It was near my house in jp nagar 7th phase so i was a regular customer der. Vry small outlet bt quite frndly staff. Service is slow bt d meat is worth d wait. I jst love der burgers!'), ('Rated 3.5', "RATED
  My 1st visit wasn't satisfying as ME wraps r something I would never recommend anyone to have...but 2nd visit was quite satisfying... Chicken pieces are crunchy n juicy...french fries were good...burger was good as well...cost is okay according to quantity and taste..."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  It is near my house and so thought of visiting it once. It is a small shop with few chairs to seat. It is compact which makes it difficult for people to move. I ordered one Chicken Burger costing ?70. It took time for the guy to get the food unlike other burger places. The burger was delicious and the chicken was crisp. Overall, a nice place to have emergency food or for a one time meal.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  KFC has a serious challenge here. Meat and Eat, gives you a way better experience of chicken burgers and wings as compared to KFC or any other non veg fast food joint.
Unlike KFC, you'll find a more juicy chicken patty here.
Now as this chain is expanding its business, they are providing wraps and other things too.
We ordered Me fried chicken burger and chicken wings.
The burgers were really tasty and affordable, 75 for one.
The patty was juicy and nicely fried with a soft bun.
Chicken wings on the other hand was again nicely fried and fresh.

Looking forward to try their double grilled chicken burger."), ('Rated 3.5', 'RATED

column14: [('Rated 3.0', "RATED\n  This is great place for some quiet time off with friends or cousins as it is not very crowded. Food quality was good. Irish frappe was decent. column12: Andhra Meal, Mutton Biryani, Pepper Chicken, Veg Thali, Chicken Guntur, Raita, Chicken Kebab
column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Best place for andhra food. This place serves amazing andhra cuisine. We ordered meal, simple menu, tastes good. Only drawback is waiting time. This place is overcrowded on weekends and you have to wait outside for your chance.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Nice food with great ambience, crazy south indian food guntuk chicken was amazing everything was a bit spicy but still everything was pure south indian.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Had chicken biryani, the best part i like here is raitha ? after 2yrs tasted again Nagarjuna ??????? gonna visit again before i leave Bangalore'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  This place serves authentic Andhra cuisine and is one of the most popular chains in the city.
They serve food on banana leaves and their menu has a variety of mouthwatering dishes.
We had their famous thali. It had a variety of vegetables which were extremely delicious, sambhar, rasam, ghee rice, and a few other components. It tasted heavenly. We tried the mutton biryani which was prepared so well and was extremely flavoursome. We also had the chicken 65. You usually get small diced pieces of chicken when you order this anywhere else but they had chicken legs that were spiced very well and again, tasted super yummy.
Their service was also quick and prompt and the staff was very nice.
A must visit if you want to have some good food that will leave you satisfied.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  A typical Andhra reasturant...the same menu, the same meals... The taste is almost the same...just the pricing is more...the meals however was pretty tasty.. but that's like in all other Andhra style reasturants..."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  One of my all time favourite when it comes to andhra food.
The food here is served on banana leaf which is like cherry on the cake.The food is always served piping hot.The meals are a must to relish!'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  This rating is not enough to tell how much I love their Andhra Meals. It's one of the best in Bangalore.
Haven't tried anything much here, but I have been coming for their meals. Briyani is great as well.

? Ordered : Andhra Meals (3), Chicken Sixer Boneless (1) 12 pieces. Bill Amount 908/- (including tax). This is an unlimited meal ( includes rice, curries, ghee etc.)

?Kababs/ Chicken starters are a must try.

?There can be waiting time sometimes, weekends specially.

? Afternoon Meals served till 3.45pm.

Food - 5/5
Ambience - 3.5/5
Service - 4/5
Hygiene - 4.5/5
Staff behaviour - 4/5"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  The biryani or the plantain leaf vegetarian meal is always good on taste & hygiene. The service is good & people are courteous. If you have a guest from outside , who prefers a plantain leaf meal , this is a good option.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Was a bit disappointed after visiting there. Wanted to have biryani and they told me not have have it as they seen that its not made good. They wanted us to have meals and insisted a lot to have that. But the meals we had was of good taste but not great. Bit more crowded place.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  One of the best biriyani i have tried here..
If you are in bangalore, must visit this place..

Quite good ambience..
Service : Pretty good..
Food : Awesome..

They serve food on banana leaf..

Overall Nice experience.. ??'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  When you're in here at Bangalore...n missing Andhra style food...

Well...... Nagarjuna is the place you're looking forward to....

Best Food with quite impressive ambience...

Thali is a must have...

Though I have ordered Biryani along Tikka....

Which is too a very impressive cuisine..."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Wow !! Always crowded. And you need to wait here. Give your name and count of people with you. Your name will be called. And then you can go to your table. Please do try the Chicken Biryani over here and chicken fry. It is just awesome. Fast serving,well cleaned,good ambience.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Had been to the place on a vegetarian day where all my friends were having andhra chilli chicken.. one of the best dishes of the place.. waiting to go and have the same again.. great food as always.. but biriyani can be better than what is served.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Visited this place last Saturday for lunch as it was suggested by a friend. When we went there the place was full, we waited for 10 minutes to get our table. We were warmly welcomed by a person.
We ordered Andhra meals and Mutton curry. They serve food on banana leaf. The Andhra meal was really good, there were so many items served with rice like daal, alu ka sabji, sambhar, rasam, curd, butter milk and one sweet item. All of them were really good and it was not spicy.
The mutton curry disappointed me. It was very spicy and salt was very less.
The hospitality was really great by the staffs even in the rush hours, they were serving food very quickly and one person was there to check if we need anything.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  Visited this place last Saturday for lunch as it was suggested by a friend. When we went there the place was full, we waited for 10 minutes to get our table. We were warmly welcomed by a person.
We ordered Andhra meals and Mutton curry. They serve food on banana leaf. The Andhra meal was really good, there were so many items served with rice like daal, alu ka sabji, sambhar, rasam, curd, butter milk and one sweet item. All of them were really good and it was not spicy.
The mutton curry disappointed me. It was very spicy and salt was very less.
The hospitality was really great by the staffs even in the rush hours, they were serving food very quickly and one person was there to check if we need anything.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  My visit to laddoo is only for samosa, laddoo, jalebi and kachoris. They have many other things also. The price is not very reasonable but for the taste I am ready to pay anytime. The samosas, kachoiri are very fresh. They make these fresh everyday. I love everytime I went there or ordered online. '), ('Rated 2.0', "RATED
  So as usual on a festive day, I ordered few sweets and chaat from ladoos. Delivery was on time but the quality was really low. I ordered kaju roll, papdi chat, and khaman dhokla. The dhokla was the worst thing. Food color was added and didn't taste good at all. Please avoid these things from ordering."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  This place is a good option for sweets and snacks. Its located in busy area of BTM.The items are a bit priced more than expected. But this place is a good choice in this area. Vada pav , kachori, dahi puri ,parathas are some of my favourites here. Taste and quality is good. Ambience is ok.Its better for buy and go than sit and eat here. Not very attractive ,but does not matter considering u would visit it for snacks for shorter time.'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Let me start with good thing. Sweets are good.
Their other food items like parathas n pooris n meals arenÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92t good at all! Quality is too poor.
The guy who sits on counter is arrogant. Dunno how to greet people?
They have to improve a quality of food a lot better.
Their parathas are just simple parathas. None of the stuffed parathas would have any filling ?

I donÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92t recommend this place.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  After a lot of hits and misses finally found a place in Bangalore, which makes authentic chats without adding carrot and stuffs like that as is normal in Bangalore. Also not just chats but the pay bhaji, chhole Bhatoore,lassi and dhokla were the dishes I tried and they were awesome.
Not exactly the same taste as of any chat shop in Delhi you will get but when compared with other outlets in Bangalore it's one of the best north Indian veg restaurant.
The laddoos in BTM is a good place to start and follow it up with some genuine North Indian dishes like sum aloo which is not sweet and the Paratha, samosa etc, ending the meal with some good malai lassi."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Tried the Dahi Kachori.I must say taste was very good specially the dahi used in the item was fresh. It's little bit overpriced but the quantity is More than enough"), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Tried the dhokla of this place it was very disappointing...the dhokla was very heavy dense and had no taste kinda tasted bland...the green and sweet chutney should have been given separately but they mixed both of them together on the container')]

column3: 5, Groud Floor, Opposite Meenakshi Mall, Hulimavu, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
92, 1st Floor, DSN Plaza, 1st Main Road, 7th Phase, JP Nagar, Bangalore
column12: Mutton Biryani, Chicken Biryani
column13: South Indian, Biryani, Chinese, North Indian
column14:
[('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Raagi Mudde. Balls made of Finger Millet. This was what drew me to this place...apart from the fact that it was next door to my partners office in JPNagar :-)

Food- 3.0 . We started with Ragi Mudde with Nati Kurma ...a gravy curry containing Jungle Fowl or Nati Koli. Spicy. And filling because of the Mudde.
We then tried simple Chappati with Guntur Chicken. Another Spicy item. I liked this better than the Nati Curry. We had some spicy and piping hot Rasam to close the session.

Ambience-3.0 . Clean and decent. Not crowded. Nice paintings on the walls. Some one actually put effort into the paintings...

Service-3.5. Friendly and prompt.

Value for money- 3.0 . A meal for 2 at Rs 700/- . It's not bad...But the bottle of water at Rs.25/-!!! That's annoying.")]

column3: 22, Ground Floor, 7th Cross, 1st B Main, 2nd Stage, BTM, Bangalore
column12: Waffles, Brownie Sundae
column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Loved the place! The desserts presentation looked absolutely mouth watering. There are many varieties of waffles based desserts in the menu. This is a must go place if you are a sweet tooth and ever go to BTM.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Polite staff, more of a self service place. New n clean waffle is good n so are the toppings, tried chocolate Icecream n Choco chip. Swing seatings are an added attraction.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Located in BTM 2nd stage but at a place not too crowded..Good location, ample parking around the place..they have good options for Waffles but need to add more stuff on the menu apart from it..hardly any options for other finger food etc or even drinks..Waffles quaity is pretty decent..Pizza samosa is nice too but very small in qty..'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This is my dessert hangout place with my friends most of the time. Almost all the waffles that I have tried at this place were good. Some of them are Butter Scotch Sundae, Brownie Sundae, Choco Blast Waffle, Nutella Waffle & Iced Lemonade. My favourites are the Brownie Sundae & the Nutella Waffle. Others are good too. A good place to try out yummy waffles.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  If I ever want to eat waffles, this is the best place to visit. Nuff Said!

The usual order is Waffles with Whipped cream, Maple Syrup and Bananas. This is a classic combination and never goes wrong. The waffle is freshly made, the whipped cream is thick and doesn't slide off your waffle in the next 2 mins. The syrup is the Goldilocks kind, neither too sweet, nor too bland.....and bananas are bananas (no build up here). There is no decadence here. The waffle is just perfect.

This joint is located along with Freeze-it, who make frozen nitro ice creams. They make it quick and serve it cold. My fav is the Hazelnut Chocolate flavour that tastes amazing. Their slushes are good too.

But mainly, just go there for the waffles and you will feel like a kid sitting on one of their swing like chairs with your feet in the air :-)"), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Waffle stories is a good place when compared to most of the Waffle specialized places. They have great options of waffles and ice-creams. The only disappointment with this outlet was the waffle base. They aren't as crispy as the other outlets. Would request to work on this. 
Rest all is amazing!"), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Taste: 4/5
Ambiance: 4/5
Staff: 4/5

The waffles are really nice and taste well. The ambiance is really nice, it's white and they have swings as chairs.
It's well lit and a really comfortable place to chill with friends and family for small gatherings."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Must say it's a small place compared to the Jayanagar store. But super fast service!!! My all time favourite is the black waffle!!! It's the best of all I've had. Not a vanilla lover and guess this was the best one for me!! But it's not worth the price you pay for!!!"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Yummy waffles to stop by and munch anytime.. love red velvet and night and day waffles here. They are amazing .
Have been to this place severally times...'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I love this place because of their ambience. I love to swing and eat! Their staff are cheerful and helpful. They have got amazing waffles! My favourite dessert place!'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Crispy waffle, lovely ambience, they have swings to sit, fresh fruits and crispy waffle(decent size), worth the money.
Will definitely visit again ?')]

column14:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Late Night has become my go-to spot for comfort food. Although the quality has varied but I have enjoyed the food from the outlet every single time. Most often I would go for a serving of Chicken Chilli Garlic Fried Rice or Chicken Chilli Garlic Noodles along with a side-serving of Chicken in Hot Sauce. The North Indian section of the menu is also something one can try out. Particularly the Chicken Tikka Masala they offer.

Late Night offers food which are slightly pricey but they are full of comfort none the less.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Hands down the best late night food in the area
Gobi manchurian- absolutely love, perfectly fried with taste
Sweets- Gulab Jamun, Gajar ka halwa,Randi
All could have been better
The delivery time is too long,took almost an hour')]

column3: Royal Meenakshi Mall, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column12: Liege Waffle, Vanilla Ice Cream, Chocolate Waffles, Chocolate Drink, Crunchy Waffles, Chocolate Icecreams, Belgian Waffles
column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  They have many kinds of different waffles. Must visit here if you ever visit Meenakshi mall. You can even customize your waffles at will. However some improvement is needed for eggless waffles.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Had a chance to have their amazing waffles, perfect blend of crispy and soft. The owners are very passionate about it which makes it a lot more amazing as they prepare fresh batter everyday and invest in quality.
You have to go here if you want to have authentic waffles. Plus they also offer cool internships to college kids ;)'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Have been there so many times in breezy Bangalore weather. The taste is great and service is nice. Plus point is that the service person remembers your favourite order if you have been there few times.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Ordered waffle combo from here..one was waffle with chocolate sauce and the other was waffle with caramel sauce..?

I am not a fan of waffles but I liked whatever I ordered from here..

Waffles were crispy and hot..?'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  ORDER REGULAR!!
I would recommend a regular size if you are opting for a snack. Also, do opt for the Liege instead of Brussels if you have never tried the former.
Loads of different toppings, mix-n-match and go crazy.
In my opinion Caramel + Cashew > Belgian Hot Chocolate + Whipped Cream + Chocochips.
Loyalty Offer - Buy 10 Get 1 over a period of 3 months.')]

column3: 53/1, 3rd Main Road, Dr. Vivekananda Layout, Santrupthi Nagar, 7th Phase, JP Nagar, Bangalore
column12: Vada, Masala Dosa, Filter Coffee, Kesari Bath, Kharabath, Open Dosa
column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Dakshin cafe - daily breakfast goto place! Great taste, Great crowd anytime. 

They have a varieties of breakfast and meal options are available in the outlet which is behind called dakshin thindis. Dakshin thindis has wide variety of combos, north indian food. 

Idlis are the best here! you can have it with chutney or sambar of your choice. Love the both combination. Vada is crispy and good.
In dosas main attraction is open dosa with butter on top! which has great taste! 
Also try kharabath, Kesari bath, and Bisi bele bath here. 
Coffee is always love! ?

delivery is available through major food delivery apps. 
card accepted, no wallets or scan pay available. 

? Best breakfast place ?
? Great taste ?
? Affordable prices'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Ordered podi dosa,open masala dosa and idly vada for breakfast. The dosas very very small. They were not dosas they were mini dosas. It is too small for the amount paid. The taste was good but not great. Also the rates were increased in swiggy.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Was really hungry and craving for some good south indian food.headed to this place. Totally satiated. The puliogare out here is very tasteful. Even the rest of the dishes looked mouth watering. And it is very reasonably price. Ambience is good and friendly staff. One of the best south indian breakfast joints i have been to.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  IÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92ll rate it 4.5 without thinking. One of the best cafe that everyone should taste. The food here tastes really good and awesome. But the staff behaviour is the worst sometimes. So considering the staff behaviour I would rate it with 3.5'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  ItÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92s replica of legendary South Indian outlets of Bangalore ? With more options!
Best place in jp nagar for idly ? ditto to b2k and taaza tindi ?
I recommend idly vade, uppittu and coffee!'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  This small establishment's food is worth the wait and the food is cheap and very good. The service is fairly fast.The dosas are extremely good in this place."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Wish to describe this place in just 3 words:
Healthy
Appetizing
Delicious!
I have tried everything on their menu only after which I came to pen down my experience. Everything is a must try, but I suggest you to go with only the chutney and not the sambar, the chutney is the key which brings out the flavour in the dishes!
I just keep coming back here for more. ?'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED

column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Had this place on my bucket list for quite some time. I have been observing this place from a mediocre rating to rise to a 4+ rating. Coming to the restaurant itself honestly was not blown away by the ambience. The menu Is cleverly designed incorporating wizardry acronyms. The food is also quite tasty and well presented. The prices are economical. A good place to chill with your friends for a few hours.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Happened to drop in to this place without much of an expectation. First to notice was the pleasing ambience. This place is on the first floor, with a Harry Potter theme set up. With a menu that needs time to grasp and order, the food also was as good as the ambience. Overall, would recommend you to visit this place. Worth your time spent.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I like how the first floor is conveniently converted into the cafe. I loved the fact that this cafe has a theme and what makes it better is that it is Harry Potter themed. The names of the dishes served here are very catchy and the food here is great. Lovely place to visit with friends.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Lovely wizard ambience of Harry Potter ....loved the place . They have placards to take photos ...food is also tasty.

Ordered white slime soup , jack o runner chicken in grapes and chicken just ....yummy ....lamb and cheese in red sauce and cats ....all dishes were good , cheesy and yummy. Will go once again
...'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  A cosy place to hangout with friends and colleagues. The ambience is very thrilling along with the menu. Though the names will cause tingle to your throat but the taste will be a contentment for ones soul. We ordered for a wide variety of dishes which were all served hot and fresh within a decent wait time. Quantity of the dishes were value for money. The staffs are very courteous and will help in figuring out the dishes in details. Do spent some time in the menu and you will end up spending quality time munching some mouth watering food. The beverages are also worth mentioning.
Our menu included: Bloody Bruschetta, Flying Faith, Flit Flat, Mumble Munch, Fire from the Forest, Dragons Diary, Warlocks Wrath and Ghosts Gluttony. I'm eagerly waiting to try the other dishes soon."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This place is a house turned Cafe with witch theme which serves Italian Menu.

The wedges were good.
JalapeÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82ÃÂ±o balls were served cold but when pointed out they were baked again
Lasagna was just OK, could have been much better
Pizza with a range of vegetables were good.
The highlight of the place was the Truffle with Chocolate, which Botha the kids and adults loved (ordered for second serving)'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Well this place is located at the first floor of an independent house. It's very neatly converted into a cafe. It has a spooky feel to it and you r sure to love the theme .They accept Zomato gold but don't forget to get your ID proof.
The menu is very vast(the one on Zomato is outdated) and you won't understand most of it.
So we ordered crispy fried babycorn for starter ,a panner pizza and a cheese mushroom platter
All of it was really very good.Well I suggest you to ask the owner for the items bec the menu won't help you.
Overall the place had really good food and ambience and I'd say it's worth a visit. If u have a car then their maybe difficulty finding a parking spot during peak hours.
Food:8/10
Ambience:8.5/10
Staff:8/10"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I was really excited when I found out Bangalore has a Harry Potter themed cafe! The place is extremely unique and very well decorated, you can see that theyÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92re really trying to capture a particular theme here. If youÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92re a Harry Potter lover, this is a perfect place, even the names on the menu are extremely unique. The best part is the fact that they have BUTTER BEER!
TheyÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92ve launched a new menu and it really does taste great! The service is good as well and the owners are extremely sweet. My personal favourite items from the menu included - Treacle Tart and GoblinÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92s Pudding.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Had lots of expectations. By seeing the review. But expectations hurts..... What ever the spicy dishes they recommend was not as good as they suggested. The hyped butter beer... Was not so good as they suggested. The burgers Wer also not so recommendable... Even the service was so slow...
Green apple lemonade was far better than butter beer.
The roaster attack.. said it was spicy... But it's of no spice ..only potato wedges were good enof.
Fries which were served with burgers were also no properly salted .
Had so so mixed experience."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  A very less known wizard cafe in that vicinity . It's a complete wizard theme cafe , will definitely recommend if you are a Harry potter fan . They have quirky interiors n a photo booth with wizard hats, cloacks, wands , brooms. The option on the menu are limited . They were reintroducing there menu which had a lil more options than the previous one wen we visited . We tried the butter beer , fiery fries, triple chicken pizza, Peri peri chicken burger and gnocchi from the newly launched menu . The butter beer , fries and pizza is a must try. The Gnocchi was blande n tasteless .The service was very bad , it took us too long for us to understand what he was talking . We asked for suggestions on the food but he started with his pointless conversation which was really hard to digest . We time n again had to call the owner n talk to her . She was a sweet lady .worth a mention though."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  The ambiance over here is 3.5/5... Didn't live up to my expectations... But I guess you can go here for a one time visit and click pictures if you are potterhead and photo freak... I don't know if the food is good on any other day but the day we went all we had is chicken BBQ wings... And it was bad... I went to toilet the very night and my friend saw the face of toilet several times the next day... We regretted going so far to end up falling sick...."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I will not be boasting in saying that I have tasted the food by God of burger here..this place does actually harvest the umami of burger and serves to you the nector of gods ..try the burger and feast in awe. Thank me later in comments ??'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Located just a few steps from vega city small is this spooky little harry potter themed place.
It is a must visit if you are nearby and have some fast food cravings..

Should go for the bigger sizes cause it was delicious?

It is a little hard to find since the board leading up to the place is small and looks like a nice little house.

Good to click pictures and have a chit chat!'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED

  This place is basically a house turned to a witch/Harry Potter themed Cafe. It's a clam, silent, mundane place to hang out.

  We visited this place on a weekday afternoon, maybe that's why there was no one at all.. Even the owners were huddled inside..   Small and cozy little place with decent options and good food.To elaborate,we ordered giant burger with elixir of life with another one which i cant remember but was good(sorry!).And we ended it with caramel waffles which were just yumm! Coming to the burgers,the patty was Excellent properly seasoned,but the bread was a bit too crumbly (it was a bit difficult to eat since we had huge burgers to finish). If i have to complain,the service is a bit slow,granted there was a considerable amount of rush that day.Highly recommended if you are around.I will definitely visit this place again. Oh!and pocket pinch- 600something.(with zomato gold)'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  A tiny cafe on the main road near Jd Mara signal has it's own quirks and looks to be a place for small bunches of people to hang out!
Ordered many things here..
Potato wedges, pizza, onion rings, few mocktails etc..
Service team did a good job accommodating a big group of ours even though the furniture setup would have been difficult..
Pizza was nice and the potato wedges were I guess the best I have had in recent times!
Felt the drinks could have been better, in terms of quantity and quality!
The cucumber lemon drink was a bit better compared to other ones lik the strawberry soda drink or even the tea..
All.in all a very good place to be at and maybe I will experience something new again next time!"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  The place is beautiful and cozy and has almost everything from Harry Potter world. The staff is extremely polite and is very receptive of any suggestions and comments.

There are robes and pointed hats with which you can click pictures. The place is small but still pretty spacious. Definitely to Potterheads.

Coming to food, we ordered
Butter beer: Butter scotch shake with fizz in it. I liked the concept.

Witch fries: Spicy twisted fries which were damn tasty

Mrs. Weasley exotic pizza: They also give Tabasco pepper sauce with it. This is how Pizza should be.

Hagrids Pasta with chicken: My favourite of the lot. Right amount of everything in it. Putting oregano and chilly flakes on it made it super extra tasty. We just loved it.

I totally recommend this place to everyone. The food, ambiance as well as the service is awesome.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Visited this place which is Harry Potter themed.You can sense that in the ambience, the props and the menu.
It's like a breath of fresh air, uniquely designed and hence different from the usual cafes.Along with the good food, this place offers a chance to explore the wide range of props-magic cloak, wand, hat ,etc and have fun along.Had a 'Dwarf' burger and a 'Hell of a chocolate shake'.Burger was decent but the shake was amazing."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED

  Homely kind of place, nice to relax and spend quality time with a book/friend maybe.
Giant burger was quite nice - juicy, good flavours and sauces. Excellent fries.
Triple chicken Pizza was quite average, expected that to be more cheesy and less saucy.
Harry Potter theme is quite nice - liked that.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Finally I was able to go to this place. Being a fan of Harry Potter series this place was always in my list.
Decor reminds of HP for sure. Had butter beer and couple of ice-creams. Felt it was ok. You can check out the place for Harry Potter sake'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Cute little place. I'm glad they didn't use Harry Potter movie posters to "Potter" it up.
Enjoyed the food. Had ordered Muggle soup, Hagrid's steak, burger and Butter beer. They could do a bit more about the taste of the Butterbeer as well as the presentation of all the food and the place. It wasn't very Harry Potter like. The service was impeccable. Would be interested to see how they add to the decor.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Small but good place kind of Harry Potter theamed one and food and ambiance is great worth trying and it is even good casual meet ups and meetings')]

column3: 458, 2nd Main Road, Mico Layout, Stage 1, BTM, Bangalore
column12: Tea, Chocolate Muffin, Veg Burger, Coffee, Burgers, Donut, Cup Cake
column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Very nice decorative medium sized restaurant for buns cakes n beverages. The staff were friendly

I ordered Red Velvet Lava Cake n a variety of Donuts. I have a large experience on Red Velvet n i am fan of that. The taste not cheated me

Actually it was compared to Indore n Pondicherry taste.

The rates were average. The service was fast n memorable time passex there'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  My favorite place for all evenings. I just love sitting there with my buddies. Having tea and blueberry muffins. Chocolate brownies. And you have to try their vanilla bun which has been my all time favorite from their menu.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Had tea and bun here. The tea was good and bun was soft and tasted nice, little sweet (4/5)

The red velvet cookie was not good and a little chewy (2.5/5)

The ambience and service are good.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Food simplified.
A comfort zone kind of space.

Parking: no specific space, but the road does help
Ambience: cozy, quiet, compact, neat and well-lit
Service: Prompt and friendly
Quality & hygiene: above average. They have a limited menu serving chai and different kinds of stuffed buns as well as sweet stuffs like cake. Either ways they don't disappoint you.
Quantity: might let you down a bit. Just a bit?
Cost: affordable
Fav: Banana cake, walnut and date cake, egg submarine, Hot chocolate- satisfactory.

Easy access and smiling people.
Bun-Town."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  I've been here a while back to grab a quick snack and to cross it off my checklist.
I ordered the veg mayo bun, shakes and red velvet cookies.
The mayo bun was just okay. I was very disappointed because this place was supposed to make tasty buns!

The only saving grace were the shakes and the cookies. They were decent and scored the brownie points for this place."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Had caramel roti and egg bun which were delicious. Loved them. Also their carrot walnut tea cake was smooth, moist and tasty. Their donuts are good too.'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  I ordered for the first time after checking out some reviews, started with chocolate brownie which was amazing, no complaints for the food taste and quality, but as soon as I started eating blueberry muffin , their was hair in the second bite and I felt literally gross after that and threw it straight away in the garage. It is a big deal I am sure they must know when a customer gets any foreign particles inside food. I am addressing this so that you guys take extreme measures for hygiene , that is very important.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Had been to Bun Town on a weekday afternoon. I am not a great fan of buns but this place serves some freshly baked buns and donuts. Cozy place for sweet tooth cravings. Tried kitkat shake, Irish coffee, red velvet donut and oreo donut. Everything tasted perfect with right amount of flavors. Would love to visit this place again and again.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  If you are a dessert lover then try bun town desserts this place is filled with sweetness literally good ambiance and proper service so no complain.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Now who wouldnÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92t love this place?
Two wheeler parking available, car parking can be a problem.
ItÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92s a small cafe, can accommodate about 10-15 people. ItÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92s more of a grab a bite and go kind of cafe. ThereÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92s not a single thing I donÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92t like about this cafe.
They have varieties of donuts, muffins, cookies and obviously buns.
Chicken bun is my favorite.
All their muffins are yummyyyy! Chocolate chip muffin and blueberry being my personal favorite.
The best part about this place is, it wonÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92t even burn a hole in your pocket. For about 2-3 food items, itÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92ll cost you a maximum of about 150-180 rupees!
What are you waiting for? Head to your nearest buntown, one in btm and the other in Koramangala.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A nice cosy place to hang out, they serve buns, cupcakes, cookies, tea, coffee.
The roti buns are must try as the saffron tea from their menu .'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Bun Town , itÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92s a cute small place serves stuffed buns , pan cake , tea, coffee and snacks ... everything was nice and simple with light music...
Prices are also pocket friendly... taste was also good....
Go to bun town and chill with your friends and create memories....'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Everytime we visit Buntown we return with full satisfaction with pocket friendly rates this time we tried KitKat Bun ,Chk peri peri burger ,chk BBQ burger , Egg Bun ,evergreen Peanut Butter Milk Shake Buntown Spl MilkShake it was too good kids really liked it Tea was superb thank u Team Buntown keep it up'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  A small snack place. Ordered saffron tea- chicken bun. I think they can improve on the taste of the filling of the chicken bun. Tea was really good.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Driven by some sweet tooth urges, we ordered for brownies from here. They were selling at discounted prices probably Independence day special. We ordered one Chocolate and one red velvet brownie. Though the order arrived quite late as it was raining, that part can be considered. The packaging was good. Was literally expecting a small brownie but at 52 bucks the brownie was worth the price. It tasted really good. The Chocolate brownie was more gooey than red velvet brownie. Red velvet one was topped with nuts(wasn't necessary), it can be improved. Overall a good delivery experience.

Food: 3.9/5
Packing: 4/5
Delivery: 3/5
Value for money: 4.5/5"), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Location and Parking: located in MICO Layout,BTM ,this place cant be missed. It asks for ur attention everytime u pass from there. Two wheelers can be easily parked around the cafe

Ambience: It's a very tiny cafe. With around 3-4tables. Yet it looks cute and neat. There's a big display unit showcasing tempting desserts.

Food: We've been here a few times now. Have tried
Saffron Tea- 9/10
Badam Milk - 9/10
Cookies- 6/10 (a little hard to bite)
Oreo Milkshake- 9/10
Chocolate Cake-8/10

Value for Money and Service: The food and drinks were served quickly. We loved the taste of everything. They have a whole lot of other stuff. Different types of Buns n all. Since most contained Egg, we had few choices. All the items on the menu are quite reasonable")]

column3: 45, 14th Main, 7th Phase, Puttehahalli Palya, Opposite Of Samsung Smart Cafe, JP Nagar, Bangalore
1210, 16th Main Road, Stage 2, BTM, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  The review is solely based on juices and not on ambience.

I loved the juices here. They serve juices as is which means no added water or sugar. They have cold pressed juices and alot of healthy juices with spinach, wheatgrass, corriander. I have tried antioxidant and green tea with orange juice. Both are really good.
Antioxidant consists of pomegranate, strawberry and blue berry, is a wonderful juice served here. It not only tastes great but is Rich in minerals and extremely refreshing. Pomegranate is a great source of iron, strawberry and blue berry is known for their Antioxidant values. At just 150/- INR it is totally worth it.
Green tea and orange is good but the flavour depends upon your taste buds.

Taste- 5/5
Price- 5/5
Presentation- 3.5/5
Ambience- 3/5

cupcakesontravel.blogspot.com'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED

The mango banana shake is good, not much sweet loved it. (4/5)

Ordered Oreo milk shake and received a warm milk shake. Cooled it and had. The only good thing about it was the bottle it was packed in. (0/5)')]

column14:

  Ordered rajbhog kulfi "family" pack and got a box that literally fit between my fingers. Expected much more for 355 rupees. Forget the family, this wasn't sufficient even for one person. Also the MRP mentioned inside the pack was 250 rupees and I was charged 355 rupees and 20 rupees for delivery.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A bit costly place but no replacement for this nearby the outlet. Falooda is a must have here and the malai kulfi is so flavourful. Sitafal kulfi on the other hand i did not found it to be that great but other kulfis are.
Kulfi falooda is great but its so costly there is lassi shop nearby where you can have kulfi falooda but not as good as this so if you dont bother about cost then you should have it at asharfilal or else go for the lassi shop'), ('Rated 3.5', "RATED
  Asharfilal Kulfi - near DLF new town is a tuck shop for ice cream and kulfi. This place is well lighted and clean next to Krishna Kuteera.

Seating and Parking 
It doesn't have a place to sit and park your vehicle. For vehicle parking you can park on road as long as there is some space.

These guys have kept few stools to sit down and enjoy kulfi.

 
 
Our Kulfi

We had Pista and Regular Malai Kulfi. Kulfi was good but did not find it to be fresh.
Our kulfi was brittle and hard not as smooth as it should be.  

Recommendation: Enjoy the kulfi, it is a good place to grab sweet post lunch and dinner.

column163:
""RATED
  This review is for a take away. I ordered food from Foodpanda. My reviews are normally detailed but i would like not to waste time and energy.

Food Quality: The food was a mess. The quality of paneer and mushroom was low-grade. Both were dry and I had difficulty to chew.

Food has more oil than gravy. The amount of Oil in food container was overflowing.

Packaging and boxing: The food was packed in plastic container and was covered by polythene. Oil was spilling all over the place.

Final words: Food left all of us at a state of shock. The tasteless food didn't only ruin our meal but it also left us traumatic.

Recommendation: Please do not try this
column164:
you may fall sick.

What I did: I returned every thing and food panda or restaurant did not refund me the money. However they offered me a replacement but i did not want to risk life of my nearest and dearest who consume this food.

column309:
'RATED
  Yesterday I ordered one veg biryani and one chicken biryani by zomato app from pot biryani.The delivery time taken by pot Biryani is too much and I have to call them many times regarding the same order after some time there all contact numbers are out of coverage. So it was bad experience with pot biryani they should improve there delivery.

Now comes to the food I ordered one veg and one chicken biryani the quantity is more than inuf for a person and the taste was average not so special. Raita was flavourless and garvy which come along with biryani also so spicy. And I was expecting the biryani should be in pot but it was normally packed in the parcel package.')

column3: 766/A, 16th Main Road, 2nd Stage, BTM, Bangalore
column14: [('Rated 4.0', 'RATED\n  True natural flavored ice cream one can get it only here. I liked their black current, sitafal, Belgium walnut. The green chilli flavor was unique and I had it for first time. It was good. The shop is open till late night so if you crave for icy natural desert then check it out. Price is pretty reasonable at about 70-100 per scoop. Do also check their ongoing offers in collaboration with various deal partners. ')]

column3: 99/4, Nataraja Layout, 7th Phase, JP Nagar, Bangalore
column12: Dragon Chicken, Mutton Biryani, Mocktails, Dal Makhani, Rumali Roti, Butter Naan, Paneer Tikka
column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Cool place to have food!!
The Restaurant is located little away from main road, and in the middle of a Mango Farm.
The place is very calm and gives a nice experience .
The service is good.
The food is good.
Overall good experience.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Nice cosy place in JP Nagar. Good ambience, vast parking area, nice food and service.
Place seems to be in a mango field.. which have been well converted into a restaurant.
Will visit again to try the buffet.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  This reason being located at the residential area of jp nagar 7th phase looks like a farm house on outskirts. Trust me, ambience is so must relaxing without the hustle bustle of the city vibes. Food was damn ? delicious. Wanna visit again and again.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  The Mango Tree's ambience is great. The revamped menu was long overdue. The service is exceptional and the waiters are very professional.

Overall a great place to visit with friends or family."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Been here for a farewell party for a collegue.. Around 20 of us. Fantastic ambience, great interiors, courteous staff and very spacious. Food was perhaps average or disappointing for some them. We tried nearly all veg and non veg starters, most of them had more spice / masala to it and less taste. They do offer alcohol with offers on draught beer. I skipped the main course and desserts as some them claimed it to be bad as well. Overall a good place to spend time with friends and family but not much on the food. Need a lot of improvement to food.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Climate was very cool by sitting under a mango I prefer ever time to come your restorent soups were very tastey serviver was good I visit again and again...'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  It was a 2nd visit to this place. A calm place under the mango tree as the name says so. A perfect place to dine with family or organise kitty parties. I love the ambience here, airy and open. I got a chance to taste chicken biryani, chicken Tikka, chicken manchow soup and fresh mango juice. Everything tasted good and so was the service. Would like to come back to this place again.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  This is a very nice place built in a garden off the hustle and bustle of JP Nagar. First, the good things about Manto Tree. 

Every item served (chicken, prawns and vegetables) were fresh and good produce. Mango Tree is a great place for elderly people as car access as is right up to the doorway and there are no stairs to climb. The service is sincere, warm and prompt.

Now, the not-so-good things. We had decided to order Chinese. The Egg Manchurian was super spicy and served hot, tasted nice. The Baby Corn Manchurian in a Plum Sauce had a nice tasting sauce but was a gluggy, cornfloured mess and there was no texture of the baby corn. 

Loved the freshness of the Stir Fried Prawns but, once again, these were batter-fried and were a complete disaster. The Vegetable Fried Rice and Chicken Triple Schezwan Noodles were less than average.

I have a sneaking suspicion that Mango Tree is better with Indian food or its Chinese chef went on sudden leave.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Everything we ordered was good (except the draught beer, which was a bit flat)

Ordered:
- Dragon Chicken
- Paneer Seekh Kabab
- Chicken Reshmi Masala (Gravy)
- Egg Masala
- Butter Naan (very fluffy!)
- Makhmali Roti
- Gajar Halwa')]

column3: 6, Sri Krishna complex, Gaurav Nagar Bus Stand, 7th phase, JP Nagar, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Been there twice. Unfortunately they didn't serve food. Was highly disappointed. Second instance I was there by 3.30 and I was asked to come after 6.00. Why would they keep the restaurant open they are unwilling to serve."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Excellent Village Food Taste !!!

I tried Chicken Kebab, Keema Balls and Parota. All were great in taste and texture.
Looking forward for more in coming days.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  This place opened just few months back and I tried their food twice. Once it was a takeaway and once I went with a friend.

It's located in JP nagar 7th phase and easy to locate if you know the area but the board is quite big and you can easily identify this place.

Most of the local food outlets doesn't have good ambience or it doesn't suit for family to have a comfortable meal. This place is no exception but the food here just makes you feel that you are sitting at home and having a great meal.

I have tried chicken biriyani, kabab and chicken fry. Biriyani is just outstanding, the flavour is so subtle that you can identify every ingredient. Packed with flavours and good quantity.

Kabab was soft and fresh. Chicken fry is semi dry item and the gravy is just too good just like homemade taste.

I'm a fan of these local places as their food is prepared fresh and do not judge the place by its ambience. Do try this place and you won't be disappointed for sure."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Enjoyed Authentic rural Non Veg food. Variety of dishes to choose from. Very reasonable. From Paya Soup to Ragi Balls, Chicken Fry to Biriyani and perfect ending with Rasam rice.... loved the place.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Very taste nonveg dishes yumm.. liked pudina chicken , kabab n biryani .. must visit for non veg lovers ..... Enjoyed the food there .. LL visit again super taste'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Amazing Karnataka style military meals available here. Try out the yummy chicken kababs here.
Biryani is also a speciality. The rates are nominal as well.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Very tasty non veg dishes available... Chicken biryani is good .. loved kheema balls .. and leg soup healthy for bones.. try once there .. u LL enjoy typical Karnataka style food .. :)')]

column3: 3/7, N.G.R Complex, Arekere Main Road, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
column14: [('Rated 5.0', "RATED\n  Have ordered cakes and puffs a couple of times. The quality is very good. Honey cake is the highlight with honey dripping from the cake...just yum. Packing is also good. Just one suggestion,please include more items. Veg puffs have nice filling inside doesn't have garlic which is a plus for me.Keep up the good work.")]
